WEBVTT

00:00:12.490 --> 00:00:14.751
(Chinook is the main transport helicopter
of the Republic of Korea Army...)

00:00:14.775 --> 00:00:17.218
(and can quickly transport
large equipment and troops.)

00:00:22.809 --> 00:00:25.833
(Republic of Korea Army)

00:00:32.018 --> 00:00:32.600
(Cho A Ra)

00:01:09.973 --> 00:01:11.672
Make the impossible possible!

00:01:11.672 --> 00:01:13.644
ROK Special Warfare Command!

00:01:13.644 --> 00:01:14.975
- We stand together!
- We stand together!

00:01:14.975 --> 00:01:16.100
(Kim Ji Eun, Woo Hui Jun,
Yang Hae Ju, and Jung Yu Ri)

00:01:18.095 --> 00:01:20.357
Represent logic with action...

00:01:20.357 --> 00:01:22.783
and prove the process with results.

00:01:22.826 --> 00:01:24.751
The ROK 707th Special Missions Group!

00:01:24.828 --> 00:01:26.086
- We stand together!
- We stand together!

00:01:29.907 --> 00:01:31.825
The central force for national defense.

00:01:31.948 --> 00:01:33.303
Republic of Korea Army.

00:01:33.430 --> 00:01:34.430
- Salute!
- Salute!

00:01:34.455 --> 00:01:37.114
(Kwak Seon Hui, Han Su Bin,
Lee Eo Jin, and Jeon Yu Jin)

00:01:40.370 --> 00:01:42.165
We go, we fight, we win!

00:01:42.165 --> 00:01:43.508
Republic of Korea Navy!

00:01:43.533 --> 00:01:44.738
- Victory at all costs!
- Victory at all costs!

00:01:44.738 --> 00:01:45.853
(Won Cho Hui, Shin Jeong Min,
Park Hye In, and Pyo Yu Mi)

00:01:47.852 --> 00:01:49.293
(Park Min Hui)

00:01:49.893 --> 00:01:51.441
If it doesn't work, make it work.

00:01:51.441 --> 00:01:52.817
The ROK Marine Corps!

00:01:52.817 --> 00:01:54.014
- Victory at all costs!
- Victory at all costs!

00:01:54.014 --> 00:01:57.294
(Park Min Hui, Cho A Ra,
Lee Su Yeon, and Yoon Jae In)

00:01:57.319 --> 00:01:59.119
(Cho A Ra)

00:02:05.826 --> 00:02:07.604
Defend with life and serve with life!

00:02:07.629 --> 00:02:09.554
We go when our nation calls.

00:02:09.579 --> 00:02:10.579
The Special Mission Battalion!

00:02:10.710 --> 00:02:11.898
- Salute!
- Salute!

00:02:11.898 --> 00:02:14.792
(Cho Seong Won, Moon Ji Yeong,
Kim A Ran, and Yang Ji Ni)

00:02:15.415 --> 00:02:16.313
At ease.

00:02:17.537 --> 00:02:19.439
That concludes my report,

00:02:19.464 --> 00:02:21.800
as all 24 members of Iron Squad
stand ready to serve the people!

00:02:22.939 --> 00:02:25.496
Salute to the people!

00:02:25.496 --> 00:02:26.747
- Iron!
- Iron!

00:02:27.043 --> 00:02:28.335
- Iron!
- Iron!

00:02:40.658 --> 00:02:41.628
In 2, 3!

00:02:41.653 --> 00:02:43.163
In 1, 2, 3!

00:02:44.494 --> 00:02:45.699
Push until the end!

00:02:45.946 --> 00:02:48.298
I'd rather die if I didn't win.

00:02:52.830 --> 00:02:54.842
I might lose
if I don't put my all into this.

00:02:57.434 --> 00:02:59.313
I won't get my guard off
even for a moment.

00:03:00.226 --> 00:03:01.909
I'll step on others to win.

00:03:03.254 --> 00:03:04.485
We have no place to retreat.

00:03:07.821 --> 00:03:08.889
I'll win at any cost.

00:03:08.965 --> 00:03:09.965
Good!

00:03:10.097 --> 00:03:11.622
(The first-ever survival competition
for female troops)

00:03:12.403 --> 00:03:13.427
I'll chew all of them up.

00:03:15.796 --> 00:03:16.860
Let's go!

00:03:16.968 --> 00:03:20.207
- Don't give up!
- Keep going!

00:03:22.125 --> 00:03:24.171
- In 1, 2, 3.
- In 1, 2, 3.

00:03:25.602 --> 00:03:26.492
Come out!

00:03:28.202 --> 00:03:29.106
One more time!

00:03:32.120 --> 00:03:34.795
I'll put my life on the line.
Consider me dead already.

00:03:36.049 --> 00:03:37.718
I'm ready to risk it all to win.

00:03:39.197 --> 00:03:40.387
- Hey!
- Show them!

00:03:41.399 --> 00:03:42.399
- In 1, 2.
- In 1, 2.

00:03:46.016 --> 00:03:47.454
Start firing.

00:03:48.117 --> 00:03:49.722
(Extreme survival competition...)

00:03:49.876 --> 00:03:51.295
(among elite female troops
on an overwhelming battlefield)

00:03:51.320 --> 00:03:52.032
(Who is going to be...)

00:03:52.057 --> 00:03:52.777
(the final winner of this competition?)

00:03:56.340 --> 00:03:58.472
I'll win this battle!

00:03:58.722 --> 00:04:01.341
It's a competition to determine
the strongest female troop...

00:04:01.341 --> 00:04:02.254
in the elite squad.

00:04:02.278 --> 00:04:03.143
Everyone, stand tall!

00:04:04.044 --> 00:04:05.979
Salute to the viewers!

00:04:06.272 --> 00:04:07.574
- Iron!
- Iron!

00:04:09.691 --> 00:04:11.510
After a year of long wait,

00:04:11.535 --> 00:04:12.783
"The Iron Squad W..."

00:04:12.783 --> 00:04:17.724
has returned to determine
the strongest female troops!

00:04:20.494 --> 00:04:23.207
I've never seen women
in the military before.

00:04:23.207 --> 00:04:25.122
That's why I am even more excited
to see them.

00:04:25.122 --> 00:04:26.900
- I wonder how powerful they are.
- I know.

00:04:27.400 --> 00:04:31.115
This first episode of our show
will be aired on Armed Forces Day.

00:04:31.115 --> 00:04:32.529
- It happens to be that day.
- Geez.

00:04:32.529 --> 00:04:34.805
- It feels so special.
- We feel grateful.

00:04:34.830 --> 00:04:36.500
- It's so meaningful.
- Right.

00:04:36.500 --> 00:04:39.980
We proudly present "The Iron Squad W,"

00:04:39.980 --> 00:04:42.215
starting on Armed Forces Day.

00:04:42.240 --> 00:04:46.419
And there's one more panelist
we'd like to introduce today.

00:04:47.118 --> 00:04:52.092
She's the perfect specialist we need
for "The Iron Squad W."

00:04:52.242 --> 00:04:53.560
Iron!

00:04:55.027 --> 00:04:57.530
I'm Jang Eun Sil,
a former National Team wrestler.

00:04:57.674 --> 00:04:58.916
It's an honor to be here.

00:04:59.857 --> 00:05:03.170
She's a former National Team wrestler.

00:05:03.170 --> 00:05:06.630
"The Iron Squad" series is known
for trench fighting missions.

00:05:06.630 --> 00:05:08.512
Since wrestling skills are
essential for this,

00:05:08.512 --> 00:05:11.211
I believe she'll break it down for us
as a professional wrestler.

00:05:11.544 --> 00:05:12.936
Plus, they're all female,

00:05:12.961 --> 00:05:14.344
so I believe I can analyze...

00:05:14.368 --> 00:05:16.249
- how female physiques work.
- She's a pro.

00:05:16.928 --> 00:05:18.023
- Master Choi,
- Yes?

00:05:18.048 --> 00:05:19.796
what do you think
will be the most exciting aspect...

00:05:19.796 --> 00:05:21.788
of this season of "The Iron Squad?"

00:05:21.911 --> 00:05:24.741
For starters, we'll get to observe
female elite troops...

00:05:24.741 --> 00:05:27.938
that we haven't seen on the show before.

00:05:28.672 --> 00:05:31.868
Many people have questioned
the difficulty of the missions,

00:05:31.868 --> 00:05:33.136
considering they are female.

00:05:33.379 --> 00:05:34.334
I want to make it clear...

00:05:34.334 --> 00:05:37.103
that this will be the toughest season yet.

00:05:37.264 --> 00:05:38.742
- You can look forward to it.
- Is that so?

00:05:38.805 --> 00:05:40.240
The toughest season?

00:05:40.497 --> 00:05:45.545
I can't wait to see
the contestants for this season!

00:05:45.709 --> 00:05:47.981
Let's find out right now!

00:05:48.312 --> 00:05:49.312
I'm so excited.

00:05:53.492 --> 00:05:54.492
Where is it?

00:05:54.517 --> 00:05:56.296
(A huge tank gun
and scary-looking barbed wires)

00:05:57.374 --> 00:05:59.910
(A heavily guarded place)

00:05:59.935 --> 00:06:01.228
It starts at a military camp?

00:06:01.752 --> 00:06:03.597
(Non-Commissioned Officer Academy)

00:06:03.597 --> 00:06:04.597
It's Non-Commissioned Officer Academy.

00:06:04.597 --> 00:06:07.067
(They meet each other for the first time
at the academy.)

00:06:07.167 --> 00:06:09.336
Now they have a running track. How nice.

00:06:09.540 --> 00:06:11.238
They're coming to the academy.

00:06:11.263 --> 00:06:14.992
(They start to show up.)

00:06:15.999 --> 00:06:19.309
(Charismatic)

00:06:20.093 --> 00:06:21.794
- Look at how scared the cat has become!
- The cat looks scared!

00:06:22.771 --> 00:06:24.079
Look at the way she walks.

00:06:24.112 --> 00:06:25.452
She looks different from normal people.

00:06:26.042 --> 00:06:27.888
The way they walk looks so cool.

00:06:28.622 --> 00:06:30.457
I wonder what they are like.

00:06:30.521 --> 00:06:32.982
(What are they like?)

00:06:33.464 --> 00:06:37.431
(All the contenders are here!)

00:06:37.865 --> 00:06:42.713
(The first soldier with a tall height
walks in.)

00:06:43.020 --> 00:06:44.162
- She's tall.
- Look at her physique.

00:06:44.187 --> 00:06:45.462
She's really tall.

00:06:45.462 --> 00:06:46.773
She's pretty tall.

00:06:48.458 --> 00:06:52.215
(And the red name tag stands out.)

00:06:52.512 --> 00:06:54.553
- The red name tag.
- If one's name tag is red...

00:06:54.578 --> 00:06:56.959
- She's from the Marine Corps.
- The ROK Marine Corps.

00:06:57.594 --> 00:06:58.752
(Fixing her hat)

00:06:58.752 --> 00:07:00.553
Being organized is important for them.

00:07:00.553 --> 00:07:01.722
(Her impressive physique is noticeable
from afar.)

00:07:01.722 --> 00:07:03.089
She's really tall.

00:07:03.256 --> 00:07:04.256
Look at her.

00:07:05.158 --> 00:07:07.642
(She enters to the barrack first.)

00:07:07.667 --> 00:07:08.802
She's the first one here.

00:07:11.595 --> 00:07:12.595
The barrack.

00:07:12.916 --> 00:07:17.981
(She puts her bag down.)

00:07:18.206 --> 00:07:21.698
(She takes a seat after taking off
her eight-pointed cover.)

00:07:23.487 --> 00:07:25.078
(She scans the surroundings first.)

00:07:25.078 --> 00:07:26.680
- She looks so charismatic.
- She is so cool.

00:07:27.379 --> 00:07:29.049
Her eyes are
unlike those of ordinary people.

00:07:29.275 --> 00:07:30.443
Victory at all costs!

00:07:31.151 --> 00:07:33.620
I'm Sergeant First Class Yoon Jae In
of the ROK Marine Corps.

00:07:34.354 --> 00:07:37.691
Since the moment
I joined the Marine Corps,

00:07:37.827 --> 00:07:40.126
I've never failed at anything.

00:07:40.381 --> 00:07:43.989
I've participated
in the Mangudai Challenge.

00:07:44.014 --> 00:07:45.225
- What's that?
- What's Mangudai?

00:07:46.371 --> 00:07:50.712
It's a military challenge
that limits sleep for three days...

00:07:50.737 --> 00:07:52.839
and allows you to experience
the most extreme conditions.

00:07:53.210 --> 00:07:54.441
No sleep for three days?

00:07:54.700 --> 00:07:57.603
I was the first female
to participate in it...

00:07:57.694 --> 00:08:01.614
and was awarded as the best one.

00:08:01.711 --> 00:08:03.149
- She was awarded the best?
- She was the best one.

00:08:03.650 --> 00:08:06.052
The Marines' goal is victory.

00:08:08.086 --> 00:08:11.208
(Jae In is surprised to see something.)

00:08:11.517 --> 00:08:14.790
(She spots lockers
that she hasn't seen in a long time.)

00:08:14.861 --> 00:08:16.363
I haven't seen it in a long time too.

00:08:16.388 --> 00:08:17.994
- Have you ever used it?
- For a month, yes.

00:08:18.513 --> 00:08:20.119
- For a month?
- At a boot camp.

00:08:21.198 --> 00:08:23.753
(She stands in front of the locker
for a long time.)

00:08:23.753 --> 00:08:24.753
Well...

00:08:25.478 --> 00:08:28.315
(She seems unsatisfied.)

00:08:29.756 --> 00:08:31.648
You need to organize it well.

00:08:32.028 --> 00:08:33.190
Everyone should be in line.

00:08:33.190 --> 00:08:35.248
Being in line matters to the Marine Corps.

00:08:35.799 --> 00:08:37.450
They can't stand
when things are disorganized.

00:08:37.475 --> 00:08:39.519
(She can't hide
that she is a member of the Marine Corps.)

00:08:39.956 --> 00:08:42.222
- Here comes the second one.
- She's the second.

00:08:42.881 --> 00:08:47.898
(A powerful walking)

00:08:49.092 --> 00:08:51.605
(She enters the more organized barrack.)

00:08:51.758 --> 00:08:53.563
Victory at all costs!
I'm from 347th class.

00:08:53.794 --> 00:08:55.293
Victory at all costs!
I'm from 344th class.

00:08:55.969 --> 00:08:57.567
She must be senior.

00:08:57.911 --> 00:08:59.179
How charismatic.

00:08:59.269 --> 00:09:00.269
It's nice to see you.

00:09:00.640 --> 00:09:01.640
I'm from Class 344.

00:09:02.301 --> 00:09:03.503
I'm from Class 347.

00:09:03.528 --> 00:09:05.295
(The pecking order settled
as soon as they met.)

00:09:05.402 --> 00:09:07.881
When Marines meet,
they instantly announce their class.

00:09:07.906 --> 00:09:10.476
Even a one-class difference helps them
determine how to treat each other.

00:09:10.501 --> 00:09:11.584
Really?

00:09:12.452 --> 00:09:13.720
You're tall. How tall are you?

00:09:13.783 --> 00:09:15.188
I'm 175cm tall.

00:09:16.056 --> 00:09:17.257
I think you haven't graduated.

00:09:18.058 --> 00:09:19.058
Your hair is short.

00:09:19.690 --> 00:09:21.728
As soon as I met
Sergeant First Class Yoon, I thought,

00:09:21.871 --> 00:09:23.082
"The Marine Corps is going to win..."

00:09:23.213 --> 00:09:26.199
"because we are physically dominant."

00:09:27.840 --> 00:09:28.840
Do you work out?

00:09:29.226 --> 00:09:29.903
Yes.

00:09:29.903 --> 00:09:30.804
What kind of workout do you do?

00:09:30.829 --> 00:09:31.946
I swim.

00:09:32.322 --> 00:09:33.322
Are you a good swimmer?

00:09:33.617 --> 00:09:34.137
I am.

00:09:34.137 --> 00:09:35.508
(Eyes wide open)

00:09:35.578 --> 00:09:36.743
What about weight training?

00:09:36.873 --> 00:09:38.078
How's your stamina?

00:09:38.115 --> 00:09:39.115
Are you a good runner too?

00:09:39.385 --> 00:09:40.847
She's asking so many questions.

00:09:40.847 --> 00:09:42.048
Is she conducting an interview?

00:09:42.191 --> 00:09:43.749
I hope we'll have someone fast.

00:09:43.774 --> 00:09:45.085
She wants someone fast.

00:09:45.110 --> 00:09:47.207
(And...)

00:09:47.317 --> 00:09:48.885
I hope she doesn't look like a baby.

00:09:50.026 --> 00:09:52.358
- You have so many requirements.
- I mean...

00:09:52.923 --> 00:09:55.395
- I like you, for now, Jae In.
- You're so...

00:09:55.485 --> 00:09:56.906
- Do you?
- I like you.

00:09:57.491 --> 00:09:59.883
Sergeant First Class Yoon passes.

00:10:00.889 --> 00:10:02.190
(The third one shows up.)

00:10:02.190 --> 00:10:04.098
- Here comes the third Marine now.
- She walks so powerfully.

00:10:04.098 --> 00:10:05.670
The third member of the Marine Corps.

00:10:05.670 --> 00:10:06.995
(Don't forget to fix
your eight-pointed cover...)

00:10:07.655 --> 00:10:11.332
(before entering the barrack.)

00:10:11.404 --> 00:10:14.212
The Marines look so cool
with their cool hat.

00:10:14.408 --> 00:10:15.408
Victory at all costs!

00:10:15.703 --> 00:10:18.700
I'm Captain Cho A Ra
of the ROK Marine Corps.

00:10:19.567 --> 00:10:21.349
During my service,

00:10:21.349 --> 00:10:23.429
I served as a platoon leader
and a company commander...

00:10:23.453 --> 00:10:25.189
in the Second Division
of the Marine Corps.

00:10:25.214 --> 00:10:27.158
She was the platoon leader.

00:10:27.158 --> 00:10:29.018
I also served as a training officer...

00:10:29.042 --> 00:10:31.529
in the Marine Corps Education
and Training Group.

00:10:33.481 --> 00:10:35.133
Listen up, each platoon!

00:10:35.133 --> 00:10:37.311
On the count of 1, 2, 3, 4,

00:10:37.401 --> 00:10:39.394
move forward on number!

00:10:39.576 --> 00:10:40.576
Like this.

00:10:40.601 --> 00:10:41.903
(Even her voice sounds different
from others.)

00:10:42.464 --> 00:10:43.464
She was a training officer. Gosh.

00:10:43.637 --> 00:10:44.571
Her voice sounds like one.

00:10:44.604 --> 00:10:45.803
She was a training officer, indeed.

00:10:47.469 --> 00:10:50.485
Her first impression was
that she was docile...

00:10:50.510 --> 00:10:52.213
and looked small.

00:10:52.747 --> 00:10:56.784
I was worried
others might underestimate her.

00:10:56.784 --> 00:10:58.065
Hello.

00:10:58.146 --> 00:10:59.333
But I was soon surprised to find out
that she was a commissioned officer.

00:10:59.358 --> 00:11:01.292
She's a captain.

00:11:01.476 --> 00:11:02.790
What year did you complete your service?

00:11:02.997 --> 00:11:05.387
It was just a short time ago.

00:11:05.387 --> 00:11:06.587
- This year?
- Yes.

00:11:07.328 --> 00:11:08.328
I knew it.

00:11:08.990 --> 00:11:09.990
I'm so happy.

00:11:10.015 --> 00:11:11.286
Right?

00:11:11.409 --> 00:11:12.500
Are you a swimmer?

00:11:12.794 --> 00:11:13.794
Swimming?

00:11:14.422 --> 00:11:16.557
I prefer running.

00:11:17.004 --> 00:11:18.506
(Now they have a runner.)

00:11:18.506 --> 00:11:21.055
I hoped that a runner would join us.

00:11:21.055 --> 00:11:22.390
She seems to have good endurance.

00:11:22.704 --> 00:11:24.198
Now, I hope to have someone
with more weight on the team.

00:11:24.357 --> 00:11:26.083
- Someone with power. Yes.
- A strong member.

00:11:26.574 --> 00:11:27.989
- Someone with a larger build.
- Tell me about it.

00:11:27.989 --> 00:11:29.343
It's all about teamwork.

00:11:29.387 --> 00:11:31.622
The last one is coming.

00:11:31.700 --> 00:11:33.802
(She looks powerful already.)

00:11:34.395 --> 00:11:36.327
She does look strong.

00:11:36.497 --> 00:11:37.497
I think she's the muscle of the team.

00:11:38.199 --> 00:11:40.097
I didn't know I'd come back here again,
but here I am.

00:11:41.049 --> 00:11:44.298
(She already looks like a general.)

00:11:44.539 --> 00:11:47.805
I can sense her strength
just from her appearance.

00:11:48.003 --> 00:11:49.607
(Knocking)

00:11:50.084 --> 00:11:53.010
The Marines are waiting
for their last member to join.

00:11:53.035 --> 00:11:55.106
(The last member they've been waiting for)

00:11:55.190 --> 00:11:56.447
Just look at how powerful her presence is.

00:11:56.858 --> 00:11:58.549
She's well-built.

00:11:59.013 --> 00:12:00.013
Victory at all costs!

00:12:01.218 --> 00:12:02.218
Victory at all costs!

00:12:03.371 --> 00:12:04.371
Her physique was...

00:12:05.814 --> 00:12:06.561
great.

00:12:08.039 --> 00:12:11.145
I thought
we needed the muscle of the team,

00:12:11.212 --> 00:12:13.864
and she looked so perfect...

00:12:13.988 --> 00:12:14.988
that it gave me goosebumps.

00:12:15.423 --> 00:12:17.045
(Eyes wide open)

00:12:17.045 --> 00:12:18.936
I was glad and thought we would win.

00:12:20.060 --> 00:12:21.392
Victory at all costs!

00:12:21.957 --> 00:12:25.060
I'm First Lieutenant Lee Su Yeon
of the Marine Corps.

00:12:25.246 --> 00:12:28.012
Since I was a kid, I've been rowing,

00:12:28.312 --> 00:12:30.548
which means I'm confident in my strength.

00:12:30.672 --> 00:12:32.747
- A rower?
- A rower!

00:12:32.747 --> 00:12:34.148
- A rower is known for their strength.
- A rower!

00:12:34.148 --> 00:12:35.686
They're really powerful.

00:12:37.059 --> 00:12:39.193
(I'm all set.)

00:12:41.569 --> 00:12:44.088
(She has power in her lower body.)

00:12:44.395 --> 00:12:45.395
Gosh.

00:12:45.420 --> 00:12:46.330
By herself?

00:12:46.355 --> 00:12:47.682
She rows so powerfully on her own?

00:12:48.152 --> 00:12:50.167
It's so impressive how fast it goes.

00:12:50.835 --> 00:12:54.355
During training, I was most confident...

00:12:54.432 --> 00:12:55.432
in IBS...

00:12:56.224 --> 00:12:57.675
and trench fighting.

00:12:58.242 --> 00:12:59.477
I had to fight
against five or six opponents,

00:12:59.870 --> 00:13:00.922
and I beat them all.

00:13:01.412 --> 00:13:04.081
When two of them came at me at once,

00:13:04.645 --> 00:13:05.645
I took them down.

00:13:05.670 --> 00:13:06.550
In 2-on-1?

00:13:06.654 --> 00:13:07.605
Su Yeon.

00:13:08.346 --> 00:13:10.401
(A Ra and Su Yeon greet
each other pleasantly.)

00:13:10.880 --> 00:13:13.913
I trained Su Yeon as a training officer.

00:13:15.009 --> 00:13:16.310
And she's all clear.

00:13:17.595 --> 00:13:19.133
- She's all clear?
- "All clear?"

00:13:19.158 --> 00:13:21.032
"All clear" means she's good.

00:13:21.032 --> 00:13:22.266
- That means she's perfect, right?
- Yes.

00:13:22.319 --> 00:13:24.445
I personally know Su Yeon.

00:13:24.445 --> 00:13:25.445
- How?
- How do you know her?

00:13:25.470 --> 00:13:28.049
She went to the same high school as me,
Seoul Physical Education High School.

00:13:29.168 --> 00:13:30.466
We graduated from the same school.

00:13:30.490 --> 00:13:32.276
I think she's all clear too.

00:13:33.194 --> 00:13:34.469
- I'm looking forward to seeing her.
- You graduated from the same school.

00:13:34.469 --> 00:13:35.713
They're fellow alumni.

00:13:35.806 --> 00:13:37.815
I'm glad we have someone well-built,

00:13:37.872 --> 00:13:39.016
- just as I had hoped.
- Someone with muscles?

00:13:39.040 --> 00:13:40.040
Yes.

00:13:40.301 --> 00:13:43.387
I told everyone that we needed
someone with a great physique.

00:13:43.387 --> 00:13:45.222
I'm glad that you came as I expected.

00:13:45.980 --> 00:13:47.124
- Is that so?
- Yes.

00:13:47.149 --> 00:13:48.750
I thought you needed me too.

00:13:48.750 --> 00:13:49.991
(The Marine Corps has the muscle now.)

00:13:50.397 --> 00:13:52.263
To be honest, I thought...

00:13:54.165 --> 00:13:56.367
I thought I'd be the team leader.

00:13:57.471 --> 00:13:59.036
- A team leader.
- Oh, my.

00:13:59.770 --> 00:14:00.770
What's going on?

00:14:00.881 --> 00:14:02.006
Did you also think so?

00:14:02.490 --> 00:14:04.275
Did you think you'd be a team leader too?

00:14:06.143 --> 00:14:07.261
Yes. To a certain extent.

00:14:07.261 --> 00:14:08.261
I see.

00:14:08.810 --> 00:14:09.947
It's awkward.

00:14:10.004 --> 00:14:11.047
What do you think about it?

00:14:11.148 --> 00:14:12.616
Did you want to be a team leader?

00:14:13.121 --> 00:14:14.121
Well...

00:14:16.220 --> 00:14:17.521
I thought I would.

00:14:18.498 --> 00:14:20.257
Everyone has a leadership.

00:14:20.257 --> 00:14:21.257
What about you, Jae In?

00:14:23.611 --> 00:14:25.496
I also thought I would be one.

00:14:25.526 --> 00:14:27.565
But I'm the youngest here.

00:14:27.809 --> 00:14:29.537
I think I should step back now.

00:14:29.630 --> 00:14:31.940
Then, let me tell you about myself.

00:14:34.268 --> 00:14:37.341
I served as a military police officer
for seven years.

00:14:37.479 --> 00:14:41.779
I joined the Marine Corps in 2013.

00:14:42.716 --> 00:14:45.160
I was at the GOP...

00:14:45.185 --> 00:14:46.509
What's with those question marks?

00:14:47.164 --> 00:14:48.465
I was the first female officer.

00:14:49.197 --> 00:14:51.098
And I served as a guard too.

00:14:51.833 --> 00:14:54.725
It was a joint training with the Navy...

00:14:54.829 --> 00:14:56.571
Because I know what to do.

00:14:57.294 --> 00:14:59.897
Well... I was in the Second Division...

00:15:00.082 --> 00:15:01.749
- of the Marine Corps...
- No one gives up.

00:15:01.749 --> 00:15:02.933
- They're very competitive.
- Yes.

00:15:02.933 --> 00:15:05.136
As a training officer,

00:15:05.573 --> 00:15:07.104
I was in charge of training a battalion
and a division,

00:15:07.442 --> 00:15:10.203
as well as a company and a platoon.

00:15:10.704 --> 00:15:12.184
(Two candidates for the team leader
emerge.)

00:15:12.209 --> 00:15:14.078
Will A Ra or Min Hui become
the team leader?

00:15:14.395 --> 00:15:16.744
The tension between the two feels intense.

00:15:16.744 --> 00:15:18.966
Even though A Ra outranks everyone,

00:15:18.966 --> 00:15:21.051
Min Hui has more experience
from serving longer,

00:15:21.262 --> 00:15:24.492
which creates intense tension
between them.

00:15:26.545 --> 00:15:27.915
Do we have to decide now?

00:15:29.651 --> 00:15:30.861
Please decide it for me.

00:15:31.228 --> 00:15:32.326
Why should I do that?

00:15:33.739 --> 00:15:35.566
Please understand
that I'm very serious about this.

00:15:36.384 --> 00:15:37.692
No one gives in.

00:15:37.692 --> 00:15:39.100
Okay.

00:15:40.248 --> 00:15:42.006
Since you seem to want it so passionately,

00:15:42.506 --> 00:15:45.643
let's appoint Sergeant First Class Park
as our team leader.

00:15:46.076 --> 00:15:47.211
She gave in.

00:15:47.878 --> 00:15:49.046
I'll try my best.

00:15:50.491 --> 00:15:53.110
(The Marine Corps seems promising.)

00:15:53.180 --> 00:15:56.163
As I met my teammates,
I got more confident.

00:15:56.587 --> 00:15:58.689
Since we're here, we need to win.

00:15:59.123 --> 00:16:00.123
Please look forward to our performance.

00:16:00.391 --> 00:16:02.026
The Marine Corps will sweep
the competition.

00:16:02.897 --> 00:16:04.628
The Marine Corps seems so powerful!

00:16:05.353 --> 00:16:05.973
They really do.

00:16:06.020 --> 00:16:07.782
The team composition looks great.

00:16:08.622 --> 00:16:10.757
Here comes another troop.

00:16:11.225 --> 00:16:13.604
(Her black beret stands out.)

00:16:13.629 --> 00:16:14.805
- The beret.
- The black beret.

00:16:15.390 --> 00:16:17.309
(Entering)

00:16:17.333 --> 00:16:21.582
(Their barrack is still empty.)

00:16:21.699 --> 00:16:24.114
I think she's part of the Special Forces.

00:16:24.114 --> 00:16:26.504
(Who is she scanning the barracks?)

00:16:26.851 --> 00:16:28.235
She's beautiful.

00:16:28.235 --> 00:16:29.587
She's really beautiful.

00:16:30.071 --> 00:16:31.071
We stand together!

00:16:31.906 --> 00:16:34.358
I'm First Lieutenant Woo Hui Jun
of the ROK Special Warfare Command.

00:16:34.969 --> 00:16:36.927
As a former member
of the National Kabaddi Team,

00:16:37.064 --> 00:16:41.365
I had many opportunities to honor
my country in international competitions.

00:16:41.365 --> 00:16:44.512
- Kabaddi is very intense.
- I know.

00:16:44.537 --> 00:16:46.771
She participated
in the Hangzhou Asian game!

00:16:46.908 --> 00:16:49.573
While I was an active player,

00:16:49.650 --> 00:16:53.432
I wanted to challenge myself
with various physical missions,

00:16:53.456 --> 00:16:54.612
so I applied for this position.

00:16:54.637 --> 00:16:57.481
I was the first woman accepted
into the Special Forces,

00:16:57.779 --> 00:17:01.018
where I served
as an officer training and assisting...

00:17:01.018 --> 00:17:02.486
overseas deployment troops.

00:17:04.121 --> 00:17:05.689
I'd like to show you through my actions...

00:17:05.689 --> 00:17:07.668
rather than words
what kind of military officer I am.

00:17:08.396 --> 00:17:09.293
How cool.

00:17:09.677 --> 00:17:11.398
(Knocking)

00:17:11.474 --> 00:17:14.031
The second member of the Special Forces.

00:17:15.318 --> 00:17:16.719
- We stand together!
- We stand together.

00:17:17.434 --> 00:17:18.869
(Disciplined)

00:17:19.309 --> 00:17:20.294
I'm from 203th class.

00:17:20.508 --> 00:17:21.672
- Hello.
- Hello.

00:17:23.184 --> 00:17:24.341
We stand together!

00:17:24.959 --> 00:17:27.244
I'm Master Sergeant Kim Ji Eun
of the Special Forces.

00:17:27.488 --> 00:17:30.769
My name is Kim Ji Eun,
and I served as a master sergeant...

00:17:30.793 --> 00:17:32.883
in the Special Forces for 11 years.

00:17:32.908 --> 00:17:33.835
For 11 years!

00:17:35.890 --> 00:17:37.221
For 11 years!

00:17:37.391 --> 00:17:40.361
I served as a training officer
at the Special Warfare School,

00:17:40.386 --> 00:17:41.292
A training officer.

00:17:41.292 --> 00:17:43.411
where I trained individuals
in sniper shooting.

00:17:43.513 --> 00:17:45.469
(Master Sergeant Kim Ji Eun)

00:17:45.579 --> 00:17:46.652
Did you see where the cartridge went?

00:17:46.677 --> 00:17:47.677
I didn't see it, ma'am.

00:17:48.229 --> 00:17:49.400
- Focus on it harder.
- Yes, ma'am.

00:17:49.425 --> 00:17:51.545
- She's so charismatic.
- She is, indeed.

00:17:51.726 --> 00:17:53.237
We're known for our determination...

00:17:54.004 --> 00:17:55.004
and perseverance.

00:17:55.272 --> 00:17:57.975
I don't think any unit can match us.

00:17:58.509 --> 00:17:59.944
That's just my opinion.

00:18:00.945 --> 00:18:02.379
It's nice to see you.

00:18:02.890 --> 00:18:04.949
Where did you serve?

00:18:05.516 --> 00:18:07.985
The last place I served was
the Dongmyeong Unit in Lebanon.

00:18:08.619 --> 00:18:11.088
I was discharged as soon as I returned...

00:18:11.234 --> 00:18:12.487
from the International Peace Support
Standby Force.

00:18:12.512 --> 00:18:13.400
I see.

00:18:15.696 --> 00:18:16.811
(Glancing)

00:18:16.811 --> 00:18:19.296
Based on her appearance,

00:18:19.296 --> 00:18:21.899
she looked pretty slim.

00:18:22.256 --> 00:18:25.473
So I was worried a little.

00:18:26.837 --> 00:18:28.505
- Have you,
- Yes?

00:18:28.542 --> 00:18:31.809
by any chance, received training outside?

00:18:32.443 --> 00:18:35.142
- She's feeling doubtful.
- She has doubts.

00:18:35.142 --> 00:18:36.846
- She's doubtful.
- She's asking carefully.

00:18:36.871 --> 00:18:38.816
- She's careful.
- Don't judge a book by its cover.

00:18:38.855 --> 00:18:43.687
Haven't you had any training
in a mountain area?

00:18:44.254 --> 00:18:46.023
I did a double-time march...

00:18:46.196 --> 00:18:47.766
in a mountainous area.

00:18:47.791 --> 00:18:52.663
I experienced various training
while I was a professional athlete.

00:18:52.787 --> 00:18:54.082
(Eyes wide open)

00:18:54.082 --> 00:18:55.232
Back then...

00:18:56.100 --> 00:18:59.003
We had to climb mountains...

00:18:59.003 --> 00:19:02.006
If you don't mind me asking,
can I ask what sports you used to play?

00:19:02.406 --> 00:19:03.744
I played kabaddi.

00:19:03.744 --> 00:19:05.876
Isn't it an Indian sport?

00:19:05.973 --> 00:19:08.078
I played for over 8 or 9 years.

00:19:08.118 --> 00:19:10.124
- That's amazing.
- Oh, it's nothing.

00:19:10.149 --> 00:19:11.125
You played it for a long time.

00:19:11.181 --> 00:19:12.094
Her expression has changed.

00:19:12.118 --> 00:19:13.013
- Her expression changed.
- I know.

00:19:13.013 --> 00:19:15.319
Now, she is relieved.

00:19:15.886 --> 00:19:17.898
I guess your stamina must be good.

00:19:19.895 --> 00:19:23.472
After hearing that she was
on the National Kabaddi Team...

00:19:23.497 --> 00:19:25.329
for almost nine years,

00:19:25.586 --> 00:19:28.265
I was done worrying about our team.

00:19:28.329 --> 00:19:30.044
- Kabaddi players are strong.
- I've never seen one before.

00:19:30.044 --> 00:19:31.472
(The room has turned warmer quickly.)

00:19:31.497 --> 00:19:32.327
I'm nervous.

00:19:32.660 --> 00:19:34.789
I think I've seen one.

00:19:37.664 --> 00:19:38.419
We stand together!

00:19:38.419 --> 00:19:39.343
It's you, Hae Ju!

00:19:39.809 --> 00:19:41.378
- What are you doing here?
- They know each other?

00:19:41.555 --> 00:19:42.555
We stand together!

00:19:43.163 --> 00:19:45.499
I'm Sergeant First Class Yang Hae Ju
of the Special Forces.

00:19:45.700 --> 00:19:48.419
I served as a sniper
in the Special Forces Brigade...

00:19:48.419 --> 00:19:51.588
for 8 years and 9 months.

00:19:51.989 --> 00:19:53.657
A sniper?

00:19:53.657 --> 00:19:54.877
- That's so cool!
- That's incredible.

00:19:54.901 --> 00:19:56.784
She'll be able to defeat everyone
in the shooting mission.

00:19:56.809 --> 00:19:59.146
Someone like her is essential
for every team. A sniper.

00:19:59.466 --> 00:20:02.066
Having gone
through various extreme training,

00:20:02.333 --> 00:20:04.169
I'm confident I can complete any mission.

00:20:04.402 --> 00:20:06.104
I can achieve one shot, one kill.

00:20:06.771 --> 00:20:08.070
Seriously.

00:20:08.606 --> 00:20:09.908
Are we really on the same team?

00:20:11.193 --> 00:20:12.193
It's all clear!

00:20:13.044 --> 00:20:14.536
I believe we're all clear now.

00:20:15.209 --> 00:20:16.047
Do you know each other?

00:20:16.047 --> 00:20:19.017
Yes. We served in the same brigade.

00:20:19.484 --> 00:20:22.364
We're close in private too.

00:20:22.389 --> 00:20:23.498
(Reliable)

00:20:23.619 --> 00:20:25.173
- We have one more left?
- Yes.

00:20:25.173 --> 00:20:27.659
I think our team will be complete
with one more.

00:20:27.659 --> 00:20:30.295
I think the last one
would be like the youngest.

00:20:30.599 --> 00:20:31.453
That's my guess.

00:20:31.453 --> 00:20:33.098
It must be one
of the staff sergeants or...

00:20:33.473 --> 00:20:35.091
- A sergeant first class like me.
- Yes.

00:20:35.116 --> 00:20:36.116
Similar in rank.

00:20:36.141 --> 00:20:37.902
(Who is the last of the Special Forces?)

00:20:37.902 --> 00:20:40.501
The last soldier of the Special Forces.

00:20:44.446 --> 00:20:45.610
Who is it?

00:20:47.081 --> 00:20:48.082
(Sergeant First Class Jung Yu Ri)

00:20:48.107 --> 00:20:49.107
- Hey!
- We stand together!

00:20:49.904 --> 00:20:50.904
I'm from 239th class.

00:20:51.967 --> 00:20:55.770
I served as an Intelligence Officer
for the Special Forces for four years.

00:20:55.770 --> 00:20:57.021
- An Intelligence Officer.
- When I was a candidate,

00:20:57.198 --> 00:21:00.458
I finished the course
at the top of my class...

00:21:00.528 --> 00:21:03.194
among 191 males and females.

00:21:05.063 --> 00:21:06.297
Gosh. Yu Ri is here.

00:21:06.297 --> 00:21:07.297
We're all clear.

00:21:07.992 --> 00:21:10.011
(Ji Eun is an all-clear detector.)

00:21:10.011 --> 00:21:11.703
- "All clear."
- She must know her.

00:21:13.455 --> 00:21:14.810
You know her too?

00:21:15.277 --> 00:21:17.305
I got goosebumps a lot today.

00:21:17.418 --> 00:21:18.767
Our team is all clear.

00:21:20.241 --> 00:21:21.479
I'm excited.

00:21:21.950 --> 00:21:24.682
Which unit do you think is going
to participate in?

00:21:24.788 --> 00:21:26.518
Do you have any predictions?

00:21:26.918 --> 00:21:28.353
- Special Mission Battalion.
- Special Mission Battalion.

00:21:28.638 --> 00:21:30.188
I'm confident
that the Tarantula Unit will be here.

00:21:30.369 --> 00:21:31.656
- The Tarantula Unit.
- The Tarantula Unit.

00:21:32.223 --> 00:21:35.449
There aren't many special duty units
for females,

00:21:35.824 --> 00:21:37.262
so I think the Army will participate.

00:21:37.529 --> 00:21:39.230
- And Navy.
- And the Marine Corps.

00:21:39.664 --> 00:21:42.734
They must be here hoping
to take us down, right?

00:21:43.345 --> 00:21:45.370
I'm afraid they'll fail, though.

00:21:46.104 --> 00:21:49.040
We'll look back and wonder,
"Are they coming or not?"

00:21:49.404 --> 00:21:50.404
Look how confident they are.

00:21:50.492 --> 00:21:52.811
They might have come hoping to win,

00:21:52.907 --> 00:21:54.345
but I hope they don't hold
their hopes too high.

00:21:55.057 --> 00:21:56.765
I think all they can do is...

00:21:56.765 --> 00:21:59.250
to try their best to catch up with us.

00:21:59.374 --> 00:22:01.219
We will always stay ahead of everyone.

00:22:02.518 --> 00:22:04.320
They're so confident.

00:22:05.281 --> 00:22:06.231
ROK Special Warfare Command.

00:22:06.256 --> 00:22:08.927
(The Special Forces representing Korea:
ROK Special Warfare Command)

00:22:09.123 --> 00:22:10.662
(Meanwhile...)

00:22:10.662 --> 00:22:12.063
What would be the next unit?

00:22:13.147 --> 00:22:14.499
She's reading.

00:22:16.858 --> 00:22:17.946
(She's reading an English book.)

00:22:17.946 --> 00:22:19.304
- What's that?
- Is it an English book?

00:22:19.304 --> 00:22:20.572
"The Goldfinch?"

00:22:20.572 --> 00:22:23.011
(Who is she reading an English novel?)

00:22:24.609 --> 00:22:25.696
Victory at all costs!

00:22:25.883 --> 00:22:29.247
I'm First Lieutenant Shin Jeong Min
of the Republic of Korea Navy.

00:22:29.447 --> 00:22:30.388
Navy.

00:22:30.412 --> 00:22:32.995
Due to my dad's profession,

00:22:33.384 --> 00:22:37.121
I had to move to many different countries
every couple of years.

00:22:37.121 --> 00:22:39.591
I've never lived in Korea,

00:22:39.614 --> 00:22:42.861
which left me with a weak sense
of identity as a Korean.

00:22:43.127 --> 00:22:46.481
Out of love for the nation
that gave me life...

00:22:46.756 --> 00:22:51.411
and to strengthen my cultural identity,

00:22:51.436 --> 00:22:54.072
I applied to be
an interpretation officer in the Navy.

00:22:55.169 --> 00:22:55.777
An interpretation officer.

00:22:55.809 --> 00:22:58.253
With pride in the Navy,

00:22:58.373 --> 00:23:01.479
I want to show everyone
just how amazing it can be.

00:23:01.504 --> 00:23:02.831
First Lieutenant Shin.

00:23:03.281 --> 00:23:04.616
Okay. The second to join the unit.

00:23:04.759 --> 00:23:06.117
The second member of the Navy.

00:23:07.117 --> 00:23:08.117
Hello.

00:23:08.145 --> 00:23:10.145
(It's nice to meet you.)

00:23:13.301 --> 00:23:14.926
- Hello.
- Hello.

00:23:15.111 --> 00:23:16.606
I'm First Lieutenant Shin Jeong Min.

00:23:16.678 --> 00:23:18.263
I'm Sergeant First Class Park Hye In.

00:23:18.263 --> 00:23:19.797
- It's nice to meet you.
- Sergeant First Class Park.

00:23:19.822 --> 00:23:20.899
(Sergeant First Class Park Hye In
of the Navy)

00:23:21.346 --> 00:23:23.582
What preparations did you make for this?

00:23:23.685 --> 00:23:26.037
I ran over 5km every day.

00:23:26.094 --> 00:23:27.639
- And then...
- You ran every day?

00:23:27.664 --> 00:23:28.501
Yes, I did.

00:23:28.526 --> 00:23:29.621
(How admirable.)

00:23:30.074 --> 00:23:31.409
How do you run 5km every day?

00:23:32.076 --> 00:23:34.012
Back in the days during my service,

00:23:34.012 --> 00:23:35.133
I always came in first...

00:23:35.157 --> 00:23:36.814
among the female troops
for the Physical Fitness Test.

00:23:36.814 --> 00:23:39.450
I'm confident I can compete
against anyone.

00:23:40.896 --> 00:23:42.020
(The third one shows up.)

00:23:42.020 --> 00:23:44.422
- Here comes the third one.
- The third one.

00:23:44.681 --> 00:23:46.357
The third member of the Navy.

00:23:47.613 --> 00:23:48.857
(An insignia on her chest stands out.)

00:23:48.857 --> 00:23:49.857
Is that an insignia?

00:23:50.695 --> 00:23:51.695
Is that a badge?

00:23:51.720 --> 00:23:54.686
(What does her insignia mean?)

00:23:55.032 --> 00:23:56.668
It will be hard, but...

00:23:59.354 --> 00:24:00.354
Hello.

00:24:00.379 --> 00:24:02.573
- She has a great physique.
- Hello.

00:24:04.079 --> 00:24:05.079
It's nice to meet you.

00:24:05.149 --> 00:24:06.611
Victory at all costs!

00:24:07.411 --> 00:24:09.347
I'm Sergeant First Class Pyo Yu Mi
of the Navy.

00:24:10.138 --> 00:24:12.884
Since the peninsula is surrounded by seas,

00:24:13.040 --> 00:24:16.137
I believe that the strength
of the Navy is key...

00:24:16.137 --> 00:24:19.123
and essential for national defense.

00:24:19.123 --> 00:24:20.528
- Gosh. She looks so cool.
- She looks amazing.

00:24:20.528 --> 00:24:21.893
- Look at her cool uniforms.
- She looks awesome.

00:24:21.893 --> 00:24:24.529
Because I served as a training officer...

00:24:24.639 --> 00:24:26.534
and went through rigorous training,

00:24:26.534 --> 00:24:30.034
I'm confident in my stamina.

00:24:31.302 --> 00:24:32.915
Here comes the last one of the Navy.

00:24:34.670 --> 00:24:37.709
(The last member walks
with such discipline.)

00:24:39.010 --> 00:24:40.010
(Surprised)

00:24:40.142 --> 00:24:42.414
(All eyes are on the door.)

00:24:43.031 --> 00:24:44.259
Who is the last one?

00:24:44.259 --> 00:24:45.513
- Hello.
- Hello.

00:24:45.513 --> 00:24:46.513
Victory at all costs!

00:24:47.700 --> 00:24:51.511
(As the last one showed up,)

00:24:51.889 --> 00:24:56.084
(the other three fell silent
all of a sudden.)

00:24:57.979 --> 00:25:00.031
- She looks scary.
- She's the most charismatic.

00:25:00.031 --> 00:25:01.332
I got goosebumps.

00:25:03.134 --> 00:25:08.196
It was impressive
how she moved with such discipline.

00:25:08.196 --> 00:25:10.475
She made me very nervous.

00:25:11.042 --> 00:25:12.567
The vibes she gave off were...

00:25:12.567 --> 00:25:14.755
- Their hands went behind.
- Why?

00:25:14.949 --> 00:25:15.949
Victory at all costs!

00:25:16.639 --> 00:25:19.075
I'm Sergeant First Class Won Cho Hui
of the Republic of Korea Navy.

00:25:19.984 --> 00:25:22.484
I'm currently serving
in the Korean Coast Guard.

00:25:22.951 --> 00:25:23.951
She's an active officer.

00:25:24.005 --> 00:25:28.459
I know many special units, such as UDT,
SSU, and UDU, were on the show,

00:25:28.782 --> 00:25:34.999
but I'm here to demonstrate
how powerful a regular Navy can be,

00:25:35.243 --> 00:25:38.232
even if they're not part
of the special duty units.

00:25:38.232 --> 00:25:39.232
She's so charismatic.

00:25:39.681 --> 00:25:41.272
I'm Sergeant First Class Won Cho Hui.

00:25:41.315 --> 00:25:43.391
I'm Sergeant First Class Pyo Yu Mi
from the Class of 250.

00:25:44.517 --> 00:25:45.593
I'm from the 239th class.

00:25:45.694 --> 00:25:47.349
- How cute.
- I'm from the 247the class.

00:25:47.349 --> 00:25:47.979
I see.

00:25:47.979 --> 00:25:49.697
You're the most senior here, ma'am.

00:25:49.722 --> 00:25:52.183
(Cho Hui is the most senior member.)

00:25:52.253 --> 00:25:54.252
I knew it because I saw her combat boots.

00:25:54.277 --> 00:25:55.453
What's up with her combat boots?

00:25:55.453 --> 00:25:56.564
Why is that?

00:25:57.427 --> 00:25:58.089
What's different?

00:25:58.089 --> 00:25:59.524
- Oh, her combat boots.
- They look different.

00:25:59.824 --> 00:26:01.376
Because her boots are the older model.

00:26:01.976 --> 00:26:03.628
What do you mean by the older model?

00:26:04.666 --> 00:26:05.994
I bought them myself.

00:26:07.048 --> 00:26:08.876
You give off such powerful vibes.

00:26:08.876 --> 00:26:11.546
- You seem like a leader.
- I think you should be a team leader.

00:26:11.546 --> 00:26:13.905
Is there anyone else
who wants to be the team leader?

00:26:15.310 --> 00:26:17.675
- I also want you to be a team leader.
- I think you'd be perfect.

00:26:18.076 --> 00:26:19.911
It's settled, then.

00:26:20.001 --> 00:26:22.246
The team leader was decided
as soon as she entered.

00:26:22.744 --> 00:26:25.279
I know I have many flaws,
but I'll do my best...

00:26:25.582 --> 00:26:28.219
to be the best leader for the team.

00:26:28.983 --> 00:26:33.791
People often think that the Navy
doesn't undergo rigorous training...

00:26:33.791 --> 00:26:36.094
and that their job is
just to work on a ship.

00:26:36.094 --> 00:26:40.855
I believe this is our opportunity
to prove them wrong.

00:26:41.618 --> 00:26:45.355
If anyone thinks of the Navy
as the weakest branch,

00:26:46.211 --> 00:26:47.679
let's see what happens later.

00:26:48.806 --> 00:26:50.008
If someone hits me,

00:26:50.508 --> 00:26:51.806
I get really angry.

00:26:51.831 --> 00:26:52.880
Here comes Angry Cho Hui.

00:26:52.880 --> 00:26:54.579
I won't let anyone mess with me.

00:26:55.279 --> 00:26:57.181
Our goal is to take first place,

00:26:57.381 --> 00:26:58.883
and we're ready to take everyone down.

00:27:00.498 --> 00:27:01.538
Republic of Korea Navy.

00:27:01.563 --> 00:27:03.905
(The defender of Korean territory,
Republic of Korea Navy)

00:27:04.755 --> 00:27:06.457
This is a barrack for another unit.

00:27:07.458 --> 00:27:09.751
- Look at her long legs.
- Look at them.

00:27:09.751 --> 00:27:11.987
(Who is this tall woman?)

00:27:12.887 --> 00:27:14.008
- "Sniper!"
- She's a sniper.

00:27:14.462 --> 00:27:15.500
She's a sniper.

00:27:16.544 --> 00:27:17.544
We stand together!

00:27:17.599 --> 00:27:20.738
I'm Sergeant First Class
of the ROK 707th Special Missions Group.

00:27:20.738 --> 00:27:22.340
- She's in the 707th Group.
- I served as an espionage officer...

00:27:22.340 --> 00:27:24.175
in the Special Military Forces
for Counterterrorism, Zone One.

00:27:24.312 --> 00:27:27.715
I completed my training
as the first female sniper...

00:27:27.715 --> 00:27:32.183
and was also a professional shooter
in the prone position.

00:27:32.260 --> 00:27:35.176
My experience has greatly helped me,
especially in reading wind.

00:27:35.397 --> 00:27:40.057
I believe I am the best sniper in Korea,

00:27:40.187 --> 00:27:41.592
so there's no unit I'm worried about.

00:27:42.797 --> 00:27:43.928
(Park Bo Ram, a sniper
of the 707th Special Missions Group)

00:27:43.928 --> 00:27:45.730
Gosh. I'm looking forward
to her performance.

00:27:46.794 --> 00:27:49.472
- Yang Hae Ju of SWC is also a sniper.
- Yes.

00:27:49.497 --> 00:27:51.412
- But she was...
- But she was a professional athlete.

00:27:51.437 --> 00:27:54.238
- She was a professional shooter.
- Is it fair?

00:27:54.923 --> 00:27:56.685
(Abrupt knocking)

00:27:57.742 --> 00:27:58.742
(Happy)

00:27:58.797 --> 00:27:59.777
Bo Ram!

00:28:00.889 --> 00:28:01.783
What's going on?

00:28:04.201 --> 00:28:05.118
Bo Ram!

00:28:05.780 --> 00:28:07.261
They must have trained together.

00:28:07.425 --> 00:28:09.487
- I think they are close friends.
- I know.

00:28:09.577 --> 00:28:12.156
I saw you as soon as I opened the door.

00:28:12.273 --> 00:28:13.273
I was like, "What?"

00:28:13.604 --> 00:28:15.740
- You haven't changed.
- You are the same.

00:28:16.127 --> 00:28:18.763
They're close friends,
which will help with teamwork.

00:28:18.763 --> 00:28:20.865
Right. Teamwork is crucial for this.

00:28:21.465 --> 00:28:24.634
I was so happy to see
one of my battle buddies.

00:28:24.859 --> 00:28:29.190
We went through the entire training
together in 2012,

00:28:29.267 --> 00:28:31.543
and since we're the same age,

00:28:31.543 --> 00:28:32.661
I was really glad to have her here.

00:28:32.686 --> 00:28:33.711
They're close friends.

00:28:33.711 --> 00:28:35.580
Is this the same locker we used to use?

00:28:35.980 --> 00:28:37.515
They're being nostalgic.

00:28:38.382 --> 00:28:39.974
It used to have a higher bottom.

00:28:39.974 --> 00:28:40.851
- Right?
- Yes.

00:28:40.851 --> 00:28:43.154
Do you remember that spot
where we used to stash some sodas...

00:28:43.154 --> 00:28:45.089
- between the windows and the locker?
- Between the windows and the locker?

00:28:45.159 --> 00:28:46.624
This is funnier than that.

00:28:47.137 --> 00:28:48.943
- Remember we hid some snacks...
- With scissors?

00:28:49.604 --> 00:28:51.386
on the ceilings after punching
the board with scissors?

00:28:51.386 --> 00:28:52.284
Do you think they still do that?

00:28:52.308 --> 00:28:54.131
I broke all the boards on the ceiling.

00:28:54.699 --> 00:28:56.400
- You should keep your eyes on the corner.
- I got caught and got scolded.

00:28:56.400 --> 00:28:57.718
By a training officer.

00:28:57.743 --> 00:29:01.072
I thought every woman was averse
to hearing stories from military life.

00:29:02.077 --> 00:29:03.077
That's so interesting.

00:29:03.278 --> 00:29:04.508
Hold on. Look at that.

00:29:04.809 --> 00:29:06.077
I think someone punched it before.

00:29:06.443 --> 00:29:07.645
That board is whiter than the other ones.

00:29:08.296 --> 00:29:09.747
Is that a snack storage?

00:29:09.944 --> 00:29:12.583
I hear everyone can use
a post-exchange these days.

00:29:12.583 --> 00:29:13.583
We weren't allowed, right?

00:29:13.608 --> 00:29:15.019
- Good for them.
- Yes.

00:29:16.046 --> 00:29:17.622
"Back in the days..."

00:29:17.758 --> 00:29:19.557
Is it the same bag
you used to use as a candidate?

00:29:20.024 --> 00:29:21.726
No, it's what I got
after the night combat.

00:29:21.757 --> 00:29:24.159
- Oh, really?
- But it's a knock-off.

00:29:24.695 --> 00:29:26.664
- Oh, you're right!
- It's a knock-off.

00:29:26.998 --> 00:29:28.566
- It doesn't seem right.
- Right?

00:29:28.566 --> 00:29:31.068
They keep talking about the past.

00:29:31.912 --> 00:29:33.604
The third one
of the 707th Special Missions Group.

00:29:33.604 --> 00:29:34.783
- Let's go.
- Look at her physique.

00:29:34.808 --> 00:29:35.906
The back of her...

00:29:36.304 --> 00:29:38.843
Even the trees look aggressive here.

00:29:39.150 --> 00:29:42.043
(She seems more passionate
than anyone else.)

00:29:42.216 --> 00:29:44.509
(Knocking)

00:29:45.116 --> 00:29:45.561
Hold on.

00:29:45.585 --> 00:29:46.884
- I'm coming in.
- Gosh. She scared me.

00:29:48.019 --> 00:29:49.019
She's surprised to see her.

00:29:50.006 --> 00:29:50.792
- We stand together!
- We stand together!

00:29:50.792 --> 00:29:51.956
- Hey.
- Hello.

00:29:52.490 --> 00:29:53.758
- What's going on?
- Who is she?

00:29:54.642 --> 00:29:56.727
It's Kkang Mi.

00:29:56.924 --> 00:29:58.796
Kang Eun Mi is very famous.

00:29:59.187 --> 00:30:00.765
- Hello.
- We stand together!

00:30:01.929 --> 00:30:02.856
We stand together!

00:30:02.999 --> 00:30:04.768
I'm Sergeant First Class Kang Eun Mi...

00:30:04.768 --> 00:30:06.419
of the ROK 707th Special Missions Group.

00:30:07.500 --> 00:30:09.237
(Not only can she crush things
with bare hands, shoot with a gun,)

00:30:09.261 --> 00:30:10.794
(and do martial arts,)

00:30:10.911 --> 00:30:13.483
(but she's also a YouTuber
named kkang_raider.)

00:30:14.133 --> 00:30:14.911
My gosh!

00:30:14.911 --> 00:30:16.576
I'm from the 707th Special Missions Group.

00:30:17.289 --> 00:30:20.974
The ROK 707th Special Missions Group
will win, no matter what.

00:30:21.101 --> 00:30:22.522
I'll crush everyone.

00:30:23.453 --> 00:30:25.488
- You can take whatever bed you want.
- Which bed would you like?

00:30:25.488 --> 00:30:27.891
Which bed would you like?
Let me take my backpack away.

00:30:27.916 --> 00:30:28.808
- You can take my place.
- It's fine.

00:30:28.808 --> 00:30:29.876
Where would you like to sit?

00:30:30.827 --> 00:30:32.162
They're speaking so politely
from the start.

00:30:32.411 --> 00:30:34.197
I guess Sergeant First Class Kang is
very powerful.

00:30:34.798 --> 00:30:37.909
(The two soldiers have become so gentle.)

00:30:37.934 --> 00:30:38.735
Hold up.

00:30:38.977 --> 00:30:40.303
I have the highest rank among us?

00:30:40.328 --> 00:30:41.738
- She does!
- Yes.

00:30:42.348 --> 00:30:45.909
I was so happy.
She's my favorite senior colleague.

00:30:46.026 --> 00:30:47.644
She's so tough...

00:30:48.004 --> 00:30:48.945
that it's scary.

00:30:48.945 --> 00:30:50.180
She's so mighty.

00:30:50.714 --> 00:30:51.714
I'm so glad that she's here.

00:30:52.782 --> 00:30:55.989
It'll be easier for them
to become closer than for the other units.

00:30:55.989 --> 00:30:57.253
They already know each other, after all.

00:30:57.987 --> 00:30:59.322
Do you remember that?

00:30:59.539 --> 00:31:01.108
Your first shooting training session.

00:31:01.108 --> 00:31:02.108
You...

00:31:02.615 --> 00:31:03.363
She's going back in her day!

00:31:03.453 --> 00:31:05.362
When you first entered our unit,

00:31:05.772 --> 00:31:08.565
you had a meltdown after your first time
shooting with a revolver.

00:31:09.065 --> 00:31:10.777
You went, "I can't shoot with this!"

00:31:10.777 --> 00:31:12.569
- Bo Ram was like that?
- No, that's not it.

00:31:12.836 --> 00:31:15.038
Shooting with an athletic pistol
is different...

00:31:15.238 --> 00:31:16.539
from shooting with a military revolver.

00:31:16.539 --> 00:31:18.511
- The recoil is unreal.
- The recoil is huge.

00:31:18.608 --> 00:31:20.243
- That's true.
- It made me go like this.

00:31:20.407 --> 00:31:22.212
And I got in trouble
for having such a weak grip on it.

00:31:22.612 --> 00:31:25.230
- You tried to beat me up.
- No...

00:31:25.612 --> 00:31:26.621
It's...

00:31:26.645 --> 00:31:28.495
She beat you, right?

00:31:28.622 --> 00:31:29.919
Basically!

00:31:29.919 --> 00:31:30.919
You can basically say
that I was beaten up.

00:31:30.944 --> 00:31:31.821
"Basically!"

00:31:31.821 --> 00:31:33.066
"You can basically say
that I was beaten up!"

00:31:33.266 --> 00:31:34.991
- She beat me up with her words.
- She used words instead.

00:31:35.016 --> 00:31:35.602
I'm traumatized.

00:31:35.792 --> 00:31:38.061
It's okay to beat people up...

00:31:38.118 --> 00:31:40.734
at a shooting range. That's allowed.

00:31:40.817 --> 00:31:41.998
- It's okay?
- Is it?

00:31:42.365 --> 00:31:43.933
Because the drill itself is so dangerous.

00:31:44.057 --> 00:31:45.057
Do you want to go
to a shooting range right now?

00:31:47.373 --> 00:31:48.373
Should we go right now?

00:31:50.624 --> 00:31:51.624
Should we go right now?

00:31:51.649 --> 00:31:53.141
(No, thank you, ma'am.)

00:31:53.166 --> 00:31:54.244
Her face!

00:31:54.269 --> 00:31:56.158
(Only the senior is laughing
during this throwback talk.)

00:31:56.183 --> 00:31:57.745
(Wiping the table for no reason)

00:31:57.770 --> 00:32:01.151
Bo Ram and Hyeon Seon
have become so gentle.

00:32:01.384 --> 00:32:02.419
The last one is taking so long.

00:32:02.616 --> 00:32:04.587
I know. She must be more senior than me.

00:32:04.587 --> 00:32:06.855
She must be an officer.

00:32:07.167 --> 00:32:09.092
- We don't have many officers, though.
- We only have a few discharged ones.

00:32:09.142 --> 00:32:10.897
Who's been discharged
from the 707th Group?

00:32:11.002 --> 00:32:13.430
She could've just been a part of the unit
for a brief while.

00:32:13.997 --> 00:32:16.750
Our company commander has been discharged.

00:32:17.123 --> 00:32:19.536
We're expecting a company commander
or a captain.

00:32:20.270 --> 00:32:21.270
Here she comes.

00:32:21.295 --> 00:32:22.472
From the ROK 707th Special Missions Group!

00:32:22.972 --> 00:32:23.972
The last one!

00:32:25.639 --> 00:32:26.639
(Knocking)

00:32:26.664 --> 00:32:27.710
- She's here!
- Yes?

00:32:28.445 --> 00:32:29.445
(Excited)

00:32:29.863 --> 00:32:32.148
It can't be the company commander, right?

00:32:32.148 --> 00:32:34.084
Is it who everyone thinks she is?
Let's see.

00:32:34.375 --> 00:32:36.119
(Getting up first to welcome
the company commander)

00:32:36.119 --> 00:32:37.287
Sergeant Kang is up.

00:32:37.393 --> 00:32:38.393
My gosh!

00:32:38.418 --> 00:32:40.348
Why is everyone getting up?

00:32:40.480 --> 00:32:41.758
It's been a minute!

00:32:42.225 --> 00:32:43.225
We stand together!

00:32:43.316 --> 00:32:45.261
- She's a sergeant first class too!
- It's been a minute!

00:32:45.701 --> 00:32:47.707
- What? The youngest one is last?
- Hold up.

00:32:48.715 --> 00:32:49.799
She's the youngest?

00:32:49.943 --> 00:32:50.951
- What took you so long?
- I'm sorry.

00:32:50.951 --> 00:32:51.951
- I'm more senior than you!
- Sorry!

00:32:51.976 --> 00:32:53.670
The sun has set now.

00:32:53.820 --> 00:32:55.955
- Am I the youngest?
- Yes.

00:32:56.539 --> 00:32:59.008
Min Seon, I can't believe it!
Aren't you a police officer now?

00:32:59.008 --> 00:33:01.535
Yes, I am, but the school has been
very accommodating.

00:33:01.535 --> 00:33:03.146
That's why I can be on the show.

00:33:03.171 --> 00:33:04.914
She's currently a police officer!

00:33:05.085 --> 00:33:07.520
Did you serve in the military
with these two?

00:33:07.520 --> 00:33:08.952
We didn't train together.

00:33:08.972 --> 00:33:11.851
When I was just a military trainee,

00:33:11.851 --> 00:33:13.223
Hyeon Seon was the trainer.

00:33:13.223 --> 00:33:17.360
I remember her running faster
than the male troops in a race.

00:33:18.024 --> 00:33:19.762
- She knows how to get it done.
- Min Seon!

00:33:19.762 --> 00:33:22.432
I was a professional judo athlete
for ten years.

00:33:22.495 --> 00:33:25.565
I represented Team Korea
and trained for it.

00:33:25.565 --> 00:33:30.340
I'm a very well-balanced person
in terms of muscular strength and stamina.

00:33:30.340 --> 00:33:33.142
I believe that I can play
a significant role in leading us to win.

00:33:33.142 --> 00:33:35.144
- Is that right?
- A former judo athlete!

00:33:35.228 --> 00:33:37.146
- There's trench fighting.
- Yes, trench fighting.

00:33:37.447 --> 00:33:38.231
I can't wait to see her in it.

00:33:38.231 --> 00:33:40.149
- Judo training is tough.
- Right.

00:33:40.416 --> 00:33:43.425
I won't put
the 707th Group patch to shame.

00:33:43.953 --> 00:33:47.090
I'd like to win and share
the good news with our comrades.

00:33:47.463 --> 00:33:48.463
We're going to beat everyone.

00:33:49.224 --> 00:33:50.393
We won't lose, no matter what.

00:33:51.394 --> 00:33:52.495
Like the 707th Group members that we are.

00:33:52.829 --> 00:33:54.063
We'll just beat everyone
down to the ground.

00:33:55.217 --> 00:33:56.596
(The ROK 707th Special Missions Group is
so laid back and confident.)

00:33:56.596 --> 00:33:57.870
The 707th Group is so confident.

00:33:57.870 --> 00:34:00.802
We'll be merciless to crush everyone.

00:34:01.077 --> 00:34:02.939
I can't wait to meet
the other contestants...

00:34:02.939 --> 00:34:04.195
and go against them.

00:34:04.220 --> 00:34:05.275
I'll make them regret joining the show.

00:34:06.236 --> 00:34:07.403
Sorry, everyone.

00:34:07.547 --> 00:34:08.778
We're going to win.

00:34:08.922 --> 00:34:10.117
(The elites of the elites,
the ROK 707th Special Missions Group)

00:34:10.117 --> 00:34:11.281
The 707th Group!

00:34:11.281 --> 00:34:13.016
- They're so confident.
- They're so cool.

00:34:14.250 --> 00:34:16.019
"The Iron Squad W!"

00:34:16.019 --> 00:34:17.517
We've seen the Marine Corps,

00:34:17.596 --> 00:34:20.621
the Special Forces,
the Navy, and the 707th Group.

00:34:20.814 --> 00:34:23.459
The four units have been revealed.

00:34:23.459 --> 00:34:25.528
- Dong Hyun,
- Yes?

00:34:25.528 --> 00:34:28.401
you were very glad to see
the Marine Corps join the show.

00:34:28.417 --> 00:34:29.041
Yes.

00:34:29.065 --> 00:34:31.904
- The ROK Marine Corps of this season...
- Yes?

00:34:31.904 --> 00:34:34.137
will win.

00:34:34.137 --> 00:34:36.339
What? Already?
We're only on our first episode!

00:34:36.973 --> 00:34:37.744
This is the first episode!

00:34:37.744 --> 00:34:39.172
- We haven't even seen all of them!
- I'm sure of it.

00:34:39.172 --> 00:34:41.110
We're not even done
with introducing the teams!

00:34:41.475 --> 00:34:43.980
I'm already so excited
about the trench fighting.

00:34:43.980 --> 00:34:45.248
- Lee Su Yeon!
- Yes, Lee Su Yeon!

00:34:45.248 --> 00:34:47.313
Su Yeon really stands out.

00:34:47.313 --> 00:34:49.823
She could even take on 3 or 4 others!
I can't wait to see her fight.

00:34:50.617 --> 00:34:53.126
Dong Hyun thinks
that the ROK Marine Corps will win.

00:34:53.126 --> 00:34:54.824
As you know,

00:34:55.425 --> 00:34:56.990
I'm a huge fan of snipers.

00:34:56.990 --> 00:35:01.464
I can't wait to learn
how Bo Ram and Hae Ju know each other.

00:35:01.464 --> 00:35:03.890
I'm the most excited
about the shooting missions.

00:35:04.464 --> 00:35:06.970
I find Sergeant Won Cho Hui...

00:35:07.604 --> 00:35:09.522
- so charismatic.
- Cho Hui!

00:35:09.522 --> 00:35:10.940
The one who warned the others
not to piss her off!

00:35:10.940 --> 00:35:13.142
- Yes, the one who said that!
- The one who looked mad?

00:35:13.174 --> 00:35:15.306
- She looks so cool.
- Yes, she does.

00:35:15.331 --> 00:35:18.314
She's charismatic,
and as soon as she entered,

00:35:18.314 --> 00:35:19.749
her team accepted her as the leader.

00:35:19.749 --> 00:35:22.719
I feel like she'll show us
a lot of incredible moments.

00:35:24.437 --> 00:35:25.588
(The Special Warfare School)

00:35:25.588 --> 00:35:26.723
The Special Warfare School?

00:35:27.849 --> 00:35:29.692
It's a school to raise troops
for the Special Forces.

00:35:30.727 --> 00:35:33.363
When you enlist for the Special Forces,
you get trained here.

00:35:33.363 --> 00:35:34.664
I see!

00:35:36.768 --> 00:35:37.768
A hangar?

00:35:37.768 --> 00:35:41.337
We store hot air balloons for training.

00:35:42.536 --> 00:35:43.663
(And six unit flags are stored inside.)

00:35:43.663 --> 00:35:46.009
We see six unit flags in there.

00:35:46.173 --> 00:35:48.277
This is
where everyone is meeting each other.

00:35:48.302 --> 00:35:50.313
(The first meeting spot for the six units)

00:35:50.313 --> 00:35:52.248
The air is going to be so intense.

00:35:53.141 --> 00:35:54.183
It always is.

00:35:58.031 --> 00:35:59.722
This is the first unit.

00:36:00.480 --> 00:36:02.926
(They're wearing various patches
from special training on their uniforms.)

00:36:04.975 --> 00:36:08.213
The first unit, the Special Forces!

00:36:08.368 --> 00:36:09.799
It's the four from the Special Forces.

00:36:10.009 --> 00:36:11.511
Kim Ji Eun, Woo Hui Jun,

00:36:11.511 --> 00:36:13.202
Yang Hae Ju, and Jung Yu Ri.

00:36:16.723 --> 00:36:17.723
We will now enter.

00:36:23.848 --> 00:36:29.810
(Sitting in the center)

00:36:30.490 --> 00:36:33.122
It finally feels like it's begun
now that I'm looking at the flags.

00:36:33.122 --> 00:36:34.714
- Yes, it's finally begun.
- Yes.

00:36:35.902 --> 00:36:38.671
(The Special Forces troops are
checking out the other units.)

00:36:38.671 --> 00:36:41.100
Quite a few of the units are
the ones we expected to see.

00:36:41.100 --> 00:36:42.699
Yes, we got over half of them right.

00:36:42.868 --> 00:36:45.601
The Special Forces knew
what units would participate.

00:36:47.156 --> 00:36:49.238
I don't know which unit
of the regular ROK Army is coming, though.

00:36:49.605 --> 00:36:50.903
They must be a coalition
of different units.

00:36:51.544 --> 00:36:53.142
- "The regular ROK Army?"
- The regular ROK Army!

00:36:53.142 --> 00:36:55.014
They're just the ROK Army!

00:36:55.014 --> 00:36:56.597
They're just called "the ROK Army!"

00:36:56.597 --> 00:36:57.597
- Yes.
- Yes.

00:36:58.325 --> 00:36:59.765
Do you know anyone...

00:36:59.790 --> 00:37:04.030
from an ROK Army unit
who does special missions?

00:37:04.617 --> 00:37:06.155
I'm not sure. The ROK Army...

00:37:07.056 --> 00:37:08.435
I'm most intrigued to see
who's in that unit.

00:37:08.435 --> 00:37:11.561
A unit from the ROK Army for this show...

00:37:11.561 --> 00:37:12.561
(A regular unit is coming
and not a special one?)

00:37:13.940 --> 00:37:16.466
I realized that it wasn't
just all special duty units coming here.

00:37:17.467 --> 00:37:21.104
That made me think
that this season would be easy to win.

00:37:21.869 --> 00:37:22.805
See?

00:37:22.805 --> 00:37:24.163
The way she's talking...

00:37:24.163 --> 00:37:25.561
She saw that this unit wasn't
a special duty one...

00:37:25.585 --> 00:37:27.176
and assumed that it'd be easy!

00:37:27.176 --> 00:37:29.512
What if she loses after saying that?

00:37:30.923 --> 00:37:33.382
- They don't seem threatening at all.
- No.

00:37:33.382 --> 00:37:34.382
Totally.

00:37:36.571 --> 00:37:37.571
Should we warm up?

00:37:37.596 --> 00:37:39.839
(The Special Forces troops are so proud
to be from the Special Forces.)

00:37:40.256 --> 00:37:41.255
They must be here.

00:37:42.639 --> 00:37:46.315
Will the Special Forces troops be able
to stay this confident?

00:37:46.733 --> 00:37:47.733
The next unit!

00:37:47.758 --> 00:37:49.365
Here comes the second unit
participating in the show!

00:37:55.114 --> 00:37:56.114
It's a new one!

00:37:56.114 --> 00:37:57.304
We haven't seen these before.

00:37:57.304 --> 00:37:58.304
Are they from the ROK Army?

00:37:59.709 --> 00:38:02.011
- The ROK Army!
- The ROK Army!

00:38:02.402 --> 00:38:04.580
It's the ROK Army making an entrance.

00:38:10.603 --> 00:38:12.559
They all seem so ladylike.

00:38:13.623 --> 00:38:14.623
I think...

00:38:14.957 --> 00:38:17.326
we can probably knock them down
in one blow.

00:38:17.794 --> 00:38:18.798
Are they even strong?

00:38:20.025 --> 00:38:21.297
They look so weak.

00:38:21.531 --> 00:38:23.065
- "Are they even strong?"
- I know!

00:38:23.322 --> 00:38:25.201
"We can probably knock them down
in one blow!"

00:38:27.146 --> 00:38:31.051
(The ROK Army soldiers are
entering the hangar,)

00:38:31.051 --> 00:38:33.384
(and the Special Forces troops are
observing them.)

00:38:33.409 --> 00:38:35.278
- Look at their eyes!
- Their eyes look so scary!

00:38:37.647 --> 00:38:38.647
Sit!

00:38:38.672 --> 00:38:40.720
(They're sitting
across from the Special Forces.)

00:38:40.820 --> 00:38:42.702
(First Lieutenant Kwak Seon Hui)

00:38:42.802 --> 00:38:44.687
(First Lieutenant Han Su Bin)

00:38:44.787 --> 00:38:46.723
(First Lieutenant Lee Eo Jin)

00:38:46.823 --> 00:38:48.581
(First Sergeant Jeon Yu Jin)

00:38:49.362 --> 00:38:52.292
(There's silent tension
between the two units.)

00:38:53.041 --> 00:38:54.730
There are only two units so far,
and it's already suffocating.

00:38:54.755 --> 00:38:56.209
(The Special Forces troops are looking
at the ROK Army soldiers intently.)

00:38:56.799 --> 00:38:58.835
I didn't see them as competition.

00:38:59.368 --> 00:39:01.841
As it's not a special missions unit.

00:39:02.375 --> 00:39:04.106
That's why their expectations are so low.

00:39:06.209 --> 00:39:09.312
I don't know what kind of special missions
they've done,

00:39:09.946 --> 00:39:12.081
but that doesn't matter to us.

00:39:13.499 --> 00:39:14.617
Salute!

00:39:14.914 --> 00:39:18.254
I'm First Sergeant Jeon Yu Jin
of the ROK Army.

00:39:18.765 --> 00:39:21.901
In 2016, I was commissioned
into the Non-Commissioned Officer Academy,

00:39:21.926 --> 00:39:24.485
and I was the platoon leader
at the Army Training Center.

00:39:24.971 --> 00:39:26.510
I served at the Army Training Center
for about four years...

00:39:26.535 --> 00:39:28.764
and trained about 4,000 troops.

00:39:29.075 --> 00:39:29.942
About 4,000 troops?

00:39:30.339 --> 00:39:32.134
She was a drill sergeant
at the army training center in Nonsan.

00:39:32.799 --> 00:39:34.470
The Army is...

00:39:34.470 --> 00:39:36.202
the backbone
of a nation's military efficacy.

00:39:37.006 --> 00:39:38.774
We're all the same soldiers.

00:39:38.774 --> 00:39:41.711
There's no point in dividing us
into regular troops and special troops.

00:39:42.011 --> 00:39:43.807
Yes, they're all the same soldiers.

00:39:43.832 --> 00:39:45.848
- The Army is at the heart of it.
- That's right.

00:39:47.240 --> 00:39:49.916
(Special Forces troops
against regular ROK Army unit troops)

00:39:50.590 --> 00:39:52.612
(There's tension in the air
between the two different kinds of units.)

00:39:52.612 --> 00:39:54.690
The air suddenly feels so cold.

00:39:57.043 --> 00:40:00.033
I have a question for the ROK Army.

00:40:00.999 --> 00:40:02.100
- She has a question!
- A question!

00:40:03.365 --> 00:40:06.167
Have you been
to this Special Warfare School before?

00:40:09.047 --> 00:40:10.215
"You've never been here, have you?"

00:40:10.996 --> 00:40:12.474
Isn't she basically showing off
that she's experienced?

00:40:12.499 --> 00:40:13.358
Yes, she is!

00:40:14.840 --> 00:40:15.874
- It's our first time here.
- It's our first time.

00:40:15.874 --> 00:40:16.874
It's all of our first time here.

00:40:17.706 --> 00:40:20.906
(Of course, it is.)

00:40:22.701 --> 00:40:24.986
What was that? Was she rubbing it
in our faces that she was experienced?

00:40:25.693 --> 00:40:27.228
It caught me a bit off-guard.

00:40:29.988 --> 00:40:32.217
I could tell just by their eyes.

00:40:32.217 --> 00:40:34.229
I made eye contact with one, and...

00:40:36.762 --> 00:40:38.210
(Looking away)

00:40:38.210 --> 00:40:40.902
She looked to the side and away from me.

00:40:41.503 --> 00:40:42.503
Why did she avoid making eye contact
with me like that?

00:40:43.161 --> 00:40:45.850
The ROK Army unit just looked cute.

00:40:48.433 --> 00:40:51.149
I didn't think that I'd get
intimidated by them,

00:40:51.479 --> 00:40:53.458
but it was a bit hard...

00:40:53.672 --> 00:40:54.903
to look them in the eyes.

00:40:55.140 --> 00:40:57.352
Their eyes were so ferocious.

00:40:57.909 --> 00:41:00.088
Her eyes are so scary.
It's like they're ready to kill.

00:41:00.345 --> 00:41:02.100
- This is...
- My gosh!

00:41:02.100 --> 00:41:04.225
It's even more intense
than the last season!

00:41:04.250 --> 00:41:05.894
- I know!
- It's so intense.

00:41:06.881 --> 00:41:08.440
I'm not intimidated at all.

00:41:08.465 --> 00:41:10.669
Yes, that's why I'm looking elsewhere.

00:41:11.336 --> 00:41:12.336
I know I shouldn't be like this, but...

00:41:12.404 --> 00:41:14.559
They're undermining the ROK Army unit
right from the start.

00:41:14.919 --> 00:41:16.004
You're right!

00:41:16.004 --> 00:41:17.889
(The Special Forces unit is
undermining the ROK Army unit even more.)

00:41:18.640 --> 00:41:20.539
Who seems the weakest among them all?

00:41:20.539 --> 00:41:23.144
The darker one seems
like she has the best stamina.

00:41:23.144 --> 00:41:24.536
They're not even talking
about who seems the strongest!

00:41:24.536 --> 00:41:26.181
You can hear them
when you're sitting right across!

00:41:26.181 --> 00:41:27.449
Of course you can!

00:41:29.781 --> 00:41:32.287
The way they looked at us,
the ROK Army soldiers,

00:41:32.287 --> 00:41:37.562
seemed like they already didn't see us
as their competitors.

00:41:37.637 --> 00:41:39.127
They don't care
about what the Army unit thinks at all.

00:41:39.427 --> 00:41:40.862
Let me make this clear.

00:41:41.079 --> 00:41:42.530
The ROK Army unit is...

00:41:42.687 --> 00:41:44.966
much more capable than the Special Forces,

00:41:44.966 --> 00:41:46.701
and we'll be sure to prove that.

00:41:47.002 --> 00:41:48.907
The ROK Army unit must be
really ready to fight now.

00:41:49.200 --> 00:41:50.762
They must be so motivated.

00:41:50.762 --> 00:41:52.073
- Yes, I'm sure of it.
- Indeed.

00:41:52.073 --> 00:41:53.641
This will surely motivate them.

00:41:53.926 --> 00:41:56.521
(Seon Hui is calmly observing
the Special Forces unit.)

00:41:57.379 --> 00:42:00.045
We seem to be bigger in size than them.

00:42:00.045 --> 00:42:01.282
Yes, how big you are matters too.

00:42:01.950 --> 00:42:03.518
Based on my observations,

00:42:04.119 --> 00:42:06.021
they were smaller than us,

00:42:06.211 --> 00:42:07.722
and none of them looked
stronger than us either.

00:42:08.486 --> 00:42:12.227
I didn't feel threatened by any of them.

00:42:14.255 --> 00:42:15.389
We should get a bit nervous, though.

00:42:15.414 --> 00:42:16.398
- I can't wait to fight.
- Right.

00:42:16.398 --> 00:42:17.398
What can I do to make myself feel nervous?

00:42:19.391 --> 00:42:21.066
(The third unit is now entering.)

00:42:21.066 --> 00:42:22.066
The third unit!

00:42:24.302 --> 00:42:25.302
I'm so excited.

00:42:25.327 --> 00:42:27.042
Yes, it's the Navy!

00:42:27.042 --> 00:42:28.042
It's the Navy.

00:42:28.760 --> 00:42:29.911
It's the ROK Navy!

00:42:30.048 --> 00:42:32.047
This is the third unit to enter.

00:42:32.998 --> 00:42:34.716
They're all so tall!

00:42:35.026 --> 00:42:36.951
All of them are so tall.

00:42:38.123 --> 00:42:40.221
They're really tall, indeed.

00:42:42.568 --> 00:42:43.625
(Sergeant First Class Won Cho Hui)

00:42:43.625 --> 00:42:44.826
Won Cho Hui,

00:42:45.510 --> 00:42:46.510
Park Hye In,

00:42:47.295 --> 00:42:49.497
Pyo Yu Mi, and Shin Jeong Min!

00:42:50.765 --> 00:42:52.467
The ROK Navy unit is entering.

00:42:56.475 --> 00:42:59.111
(The ROK Navy unit is sitting
beside the Special Forces unit.)

00:42:59.111 --> 00:43:01.209
What's going to happen now?

00:43:02.877 --> 00:43:04.245
- She's scanning them right away, yes?
- That's right.

00:43:04.270 --> 00:43:05.284
(Kwak Seon Hui from the ROK Army is
actively scanning the Navy right away.)

00:43:05.897 --> 00:43:07.715
Does anyone stand out to you?

00:43:07.715 --> 00:43:09.050
- What?
- Does anyone stand out to you?

00:43:09.168 --> 00:43:10.538
The team leader, of course.

00:43:11.290 --> 00:43:12.112
The far left one?

00:43:12.136 --> 00:43:14.155
Yes, Cho Hui definitely catches
everyone's eye.

00:43:15.149 --> 00:43:16.149
She seems so strong.

00:43:17.418 --> 00:43:18.418
She's different!

00:43:19.169 --> 00:43:20.538
She's on a different level!

00:43:20.538 --> 00:43:22.133
Cho Hui is my favorite!

00:43:22.440 --> 00:43:23.440
Cho Hui is my favorite!

00:43:25.233 --> 00:43:28.387
I didn't feel threatened by any of them.

00:43:34.119 --> 00:43:37.011
When I saw the Navy unit,

00:43:38.216 --> 00:43:40.415
everyone, aside from the leader,
seemed pretty weak.

00:43:41.416 --> 00:43:43.384
I'm sure that the ROK Army will win.

00:43:44.973 --> 00:43:48.280
(Things are getting more tense
with the ROK Navy's entrance.)

00:43:49.394 --> 00:43:50.702
(Right then)

00:43:50.702 --> 00:43:53.728
I want to see what the Special Forces unit
thinks of the ROK Navy unit now.

00:43:53.728 --> 00:43:55.283
(Kim Ji Eun from the Special Forces is
paying special attention to the Navy.)

00:43:55.630 --> 00:43:57.836
I'm still not getting nervous.

00:43:59.871 --> 00:44:02.727
I feel more relaxed
each time a new unit enters.

00:44:02.727 --> 00:44:03.471
It's hard to get intimidated.

00:44:03.471 --> 00:44:05.640
- I just can't get intimidated by them.
- I felt relaxed from the start.

00:44:05.665 --> 00:44:07.242
Everyone can hear them!

00:44:08.166 --> 00:44:10.363
The color of their uniforms...

00:44:10.387 --> 00:44:12.447
just doesn't intimidate us.

00:44:13.748 --> 00:44:14.748
Of course, she's uneasy.

00:44:18.083 --> 00:44:19.177
(Scoffing)

00:44:19.177 --> 00:44:21.232
I didn't feel all that great.

00:44:21.897 --> 00:44:23.101
(Everyone's in shock.)

00:44:23.101 --> 00:44:24.101
That smirk!

00:44:24.583 --> 00:44:26.424
- Cho Hui with the smirk!
- She's so cool!

00:44:26.424 --> 00:44:28.596
- That was...
- She's so charismatic.

00:44:31.916 --> 00:44:33.067
The ones from the Special Forces unit...

00:44:33.638 --> 00:44:36.501
seemed like they were trying too hard
to look strong.

00:44:36.501 --> 00:44:38.640
I don't think that we're
any weaker than them,

00:44:38.640 --> 00:44:39.908
so why are they looking at us like that?

00:44:39.908 --> 00:44:41.119
Yes, they started at the Navy too much.

00:44:41.199 --> 00:44:42.380
(The Special Forces unit continues
chatting.)

00:44:42.380 --> 00:44:44.679
- I'm itching to move.
- They don't care about who's listening.

00:44:44.679 --> 00:44:46.147
- The Special Forces doesn't care.
- I need to get moving.

00:44:46.481 --> 00:44:48.683
I saw the Army and the Navy units,

00:44:49.517 --> 00:44:52.353
and I don't consider them
as special mission units,

00:44:52.353 --> 00:44:54.455
so I don't find them intimidating at all.

00:44:56.495 --> 00:44:58.410
(The air in the hangar is getting
more and more intense.)

00:44:58.435 --> 00:44:59.636
It's so scary.

00:45:03.822 --> 00:45:06.768
Here comes the fourth unit.

00:45:06.824 --> 00:45:08.060
The fourth unit!

00:45:08.060 --> 00:45:09.270
I'm so excited.

00:45:10.572 --> 00:45:13.598
(The ROK 707th Special Missions Group)

00:45:14.175 --> 00:45:15.343
It's the 707th Group.

00:45:15.743 --> 00:45:16.743
The 707th Group!

00:45:16.861 --> 00:45:18.112
They recognized them right away.

00:45:19.151 --> 00:45:20.481
(Sergeant First Class Kang Eun Mi)

00:45:20.481 --> 00:45:21.481
Kang Eun Mi!

00:45:22.230 --> 00:45:25.353
Sergeant Kang is here.

00:45:26.892 --> 00:45:28.089
The golden badge!

00:45:28.853 --> 00:45:30.148
- The golden badge?
- The golden badge?

00:45:30.173 --> 00:45:30.989
What's the golden badge?

00:45:30.989 --> 00:45:32.193
Only those who do the descent training
over 1,000 times get that.

00:45:32.794 --> 00:45:34.105
Over 1,000 times?

00:45:34.130 --> 00:45:36.164
Yes, and she's the most senior one
in the 707th Group.

00:45:37.365 --> 00:45:38.900
Kang Eun Mi and Jeon Min Seon!

00:45:40.501 --> 00:45:41.501
Lee Hyeon Seon.

00:45:42.422 --> 00:45:43.422
Park Bo Ram.

00:45:45.076 --> 00:45:46.076
Here they come.

00:45:47.041 --> 00:45:48.176
The 707th Group.

00:45:50.507 --> 00:45:51.749
They're all quite buff.

00:45:53.448 --> 00:45:54.716
Hello.

00:45:54.840 --> 00:45:56.784
- They're getting up to greet them.
- Finally!

00:45:56.809 --> 00:45:58.570
- We stand together!
- Because they know each other.

00:45:58.570 --> 00:45:59.110
Hello.

00:45:59.110 --> 00:46:01.256
The Special Forces and the 707th Group
know each other.

00:46:01.256 --> 00:46:03.057
- I'm from 239th class.
- I'm from the 215th class.

00:46:03.616 --> 00:46:04.522
Nice to meet you.

00:46:05.696 --> 00:46:08.983
(The other units are so confused.)

00:46:09.260 --> 00:46:11.466
My body just got up automatically.

00:46:11.576 --> 00:46:15.470
The 707th Group and the Special Forces
are like a family.

00:46:15.470 --> 00:46:18.216
That's why it's a custom for us...

00:46:18.216 --> 00:46:20.541
to state our classes
as we greet each other.

00:46:20.541 --> 00:46:21.542
Hello.

00:46:21.567 --> 00:46:23.077
- Hello.
- Hello.

00:46:24.202 --> 00:46:25.413
Hello.

00:46:26.133 --> 00:46:29.550
Things are changing rapidly
with the 707th Group's entrance!

00:46:32.432 --> 00:46:33.432
They're so cool!

00:46:33.513 --> 00:46:38.590
(The 707th Group has such a strong aura.)

00:46:39.127 --> 00:46:41.966
(The Special Forces unit seems nervous
for the first time.)

00:46:42.030 --> 00:46:43.364
The Special Forces unit is nervous!

00:46:43.364 --> 00:46:45.233
They were so chatty and happy
until just now.

00:46:46.751 --> 00:46:48.536
(The Special Forces unit
and the 707th Group are exchanging...)

00:46:48.560 --> 00:46:50.525
(mysterious eye contact.)

00:46:50.965 --> 00:46:52.310
This is a family fight.

00:46:52.543 --> 00:46:53.447
For sure.

00:46:53.652 --> 00:46:54.502
Seriously.

00:46:54.502 --> 00:46:55.600
We're...

00:46:56.174 --> 00:46:57.278
different teams here.

00:46:58.623 --> 00:47:00.713
(The Special Forces unit
and the 707th Group...)

00:47:00.737 --> 00:47:02.587
(must go against each
other on "The Iron Squad W.")

00:47:03.084 --> 00:47:04.084
Sergeant Kang.

00:47:05.951 --> 00:47:07.922
Hae Ju, the one beside Ji Eun,

00:47:09.023 --> 00:47:12.193
was my partner for five years for sniping.

00:47:14.095 --> 00:47:16.321
She was in a pair with Yang Hae Ju!

00:47:16.346 --> 00:47:18.599
They were like Park Ji Yun
and Lee Dong Gyu, then!

00:47:18.599 --> 00:47:21.135
- Yes, basically.
- Bo Ram and Hae Ju were a team.

00:47:21.473 --> 00:47:23.438
- But you're better, right?
- When it comes to shooting...

00:47:23.514 --> 00:47:25.039
I'm a better shooter than her.

00:47:25.039 --> 00:47:26.474
- That's fine, then.
- It's all good.

00:47:26.791 --> 00:47:28.593
(Looking over)

00:47:30.477 --> 00:47:33.014
She's looking away! That's a first!

00:47:33.039 --> 00:47:35.404
Hae Ju keeps avoiding eye contact with me!
That little brat.

00:47:36.181 --> 00:47:37.785
She called her a little brat!

00:47:37.810 --> 00:47:38.586
That's so...

00:47:38.586 --> 00:47:39.430
That was...

00:47:39.430 --> 00:47:42.423
Do military ladies talk so rough too?

00:47:43.421 --> 00:47:44.659
The short-haired one in the back.

00:47:44.659 --> 00:47:45.697
- The one on the right?
- Yes.

00:47:45.997 --> 00:47:47.919
I was on the same team with her.

00:47:50.331 --> 00:47:52.300
I suddenly feel so determined to win.

00:47:56.181 --> 00:47:57.905
(The 707th Group is scanning
the other units.)

00:47:57.905 --> 00:47:58.905
I know.

00:47:58.905 --> 00:47:59.905
That's the Navy.

00:48:00.514 --> 00:48:02.710
The Navy doesn't have
a special missions unit, does it?

00:48:02.710 --> 00:48:03.710
The Navy? The female soldiers?

00:48:03.751 --> 00:48:04.712
- Yes.
- No, it doesn't.

00:48:05.817 --> 00:48:08.783
I only expected to see
special mission groups here,

00:48:09.450 --> 00:48:11.986
but the Army and the Navy...

00:48:11.986 --> 00:48:13.254
also formed coalitions to participate.

00:48:14.679 --> 00:48:16.824
That gave me some confidence.

00:48:16.849 --> 00:48:17.989
(So confident)

00:48:18.993 --> 00:48:19.993
But...

00:48:20.561 --> 00:48:23.315
the ROK Army unit seems to have
the prettiest ones here.

00:48:25.498 --> 00:48:26.701
- Prettiest...
- That's...

00:48:26.701 --> 00:48:27.802
That's not a compliment.

00:48:27.802 --> 00:48:28.346
- Is it?
- No,

00:48:28.371 --> 00:48:30.638
you can't really call that
a compliment here.

00:48:30.638 --> 00:48:32.196
The ROK Army unit seems to have
the prettiest ones here.

00:48:34.245 --> 00:48:36.077
- They heard her!
- Yes, they did!

00:48:37.242 --> 00:48:40.014
All of you seem really pretty.

00:48:41.452 --> 00:48:42.260
Sorry.

00:48:42.260 --> 00:48:43.260
- Thank you.
- You're beautiful too.

00:48:44.028 --> 00:48:45.028
All of you.

00:48:48.887 --> 00:48:49.801
Look at her face!

00:48:49.801 --> 00:48:52.794
Everyone was so pretty.

00:48:53.828 --> 00:48:54.828
The Army?

00:48:55.667 --> 00:48:57.598
I didn't feel threatened by them at all.

00:48:57.623 --> 00:49:00.040
They were just pretty.

00:49:01.702 --> 00:49:04.172
I thought that they were the faces
to promote the ROK Army.

00:49:04.886 --> 00:49:07.308
I assumed that they'd be weak.

00:49:07.888 --> 00:49:09.354
(Thrown off by the tension)

00:49:09.354 --> 00:49:10.678
It's so intense!

00:49:11.696 --> 00:49:15.416
They're really crossing the line here!

00:49:15.600 --> 00:49:17.995
- Can someone else come in?
- Yes, please!

00:49:19.734 --> 00:49:20.822
Then...

00:49:21.015 --> 00:49:22.156
The Marine Corps unit...

00:49:22.280 --> 00:49:23.691
and the Special Mission Battalion unit
haven't arrived yet.

00:49:24.588 --> 00:49:25.243
What's that?

00:49:25.243 --> 00:49:26.594
What's the Special Mission Battalion?

00:49:26.594 --> 00:49:27.662
- The Special Mission Battalion?
- Yes.

00:49:28.493 --> 00:49:31.556
The most unpredictable
and mysterious unit.

00:49:31.556 --> 00:49:32.633
The Special Mission Battalion?

00:49:34.719 --> 00:49:35.719
They've arrived.

00:49:36.234 --> 00:49:37.438
Is that the Special Mission Battalion?

00:49:38.369 --> 00:49:39.273
The Marine Corps?

00:49:39.273 --> 00:49:40.575
- There are two more units to go.
- The Special Mission Battalion?

00:49:43.368 --> 00:49:46.371
(The fifth participating unit)

00:49:47.982 --> 00:49:48.982
Look at her eyes!

00:49:50.315 --> 00:49:51.586
The Special Mission Battalion?

00:49:51.611 --> 00:49:52.787
The uniforms are different.

00:49:52.812 --> 00:49:54.710
- Their uniforms look different.
- Indeed.

00:49:55.113 --> 00:49:58.009
That's not a combat uniform, is it?

00:49:58.009 --> 00:49:59.861
- I see one in black.
- What is that?

00:50:00.517 --> 00:50:01.250
What's that black uniform?

00:50:01.275 --> 00:50:03.229
The black uniform shows
that she's served on a special mission.

00:50:03.729 --> 00:50:05.264
The first one is from the Tarantula Unit.

00:50:06.031 --> 00:50:07.216
I see the badge on her chest.

00:50:08.424 --> 00:50:09.358
- The Tarantula Unit!
- The Tarantula Unit?

00:50:09.383 --> 00:50:11.637
- At last, the Tarantula Unit is here!
- Yes, I've heard of the Tarantula Unit!

00:50:15.231 --> 00:50:16.231
Who is she?

00:50:16.509 --> 00:50:17.643
She looks so charismatic!

00:50:18.341 --> 00:50:19.378
They look so strong.

00:50:23.249 --> 00:50:24.717
Here comes the Special Mission Battalion.

00:50:25.875 --> 00:50:32.548
(The mysterious Special Mission Battalion
is making everyone nervous.)

00:50:33.471 --> 00:50:38.504
(The Special Mission Battalion troops
seem very charismatic.)

00:50:38.554 --> 00:50:39.554
They're from different units.

00:50:39.742 --> 00:50:40.966
Yes, it's a mix.

00:50:40.991 --> 00:50:43.109
(Everyone's murmuring.)

00:50:43.378 --> 00:50:46.138
Like the Military Police Special Duty Team
and the CBRN Special Forces together.

00:50:46.242 --> 00:50:49.742
It seems like a collection of all troops
from Special Mission Battalions.

00:50:50.976 --> 00:50:52.444
The Special Mission Battalion...

00:50:52.778 --> 00:50:54.213
That one
in the Special Mission Battalion...

00:50:54.403 --> 00:50:55.403
is so handsome.

00:50:55.428 --> 00:50:57.049
- I thought that she was a man at first.
- Me too.

00:50:57.483 --> 00:50:59.602
- She's so...
- She looks so strong too.

00:51:00.917 --> 00:51:01.757
- Who is she?
- Look at those eyes!

00:51:01.757 --> 00:51:03.289
She's even making me want to look down!

00:51:06.529 --> 00:51:07.529
Salute!

00:51:08.286 --> 00:51:11.230
I'm Sergeant First Class Cho Seong Won
in the 35th Special Mission Battalion.

00:51:11.230 --> 00:51:12.230
Sergeant Cho Seong Won!

00:51:12.255 --> 00:51:13.566
The Tarantula Unit is...

00:51:13.640 --> 00:51:15.267
for the top one percent
of female soldiers in the country.

00:51:15.344 --> 00:51:18.970
We train
to prevent terrorist acts in Seoul.

00:51:18.995 --> 00:51:20.503
Our missions are
all about protecting the capital.

00:51:21.170 --> 00:51:23.426
From rappel training
to counter-terrorism training,

00:51:23.426 --> 00:51:24.543
counter-terrorism shooting,

00:51:25.007 --> 00:51:26.779
- She's so charismatic!
- and martial arts,

00:51:26.916 --> 00:51:28.113
I'm confident in all of them.

00:51:28.113 --> 00:51:29.208
(As a part of the top one percent,
she goes through many training sessions.)

00:51:29.725 --> 00:51:32.384
You must get the top grade
in all physical ability tests.

00:51:33.024 --> 00:51:35.921
Only the chosen ones can join the group,

00:51:36.071 --> 00:51:39.225
which is why I'm always proud
to be a part of the unit.

00:51:39.792 --> 00:51:41.126
Hold up.

00:51:41.126 --> 00:51:43.529
I'm starting to forget about Cho Hui.

00:51:43.529 --> 00:51:44.460
- Yes, me too.
- Right!

00:51:44.460 --> 00:51:46.065
- No!
- There was Cho Hui, but...

00:51:46.903 --> 00:51:50.086
(Sergeant Cho Seong Won is
catching everyone's attention.)

00:51:50.292 --> 00:51:52.137
That tarantula looks horrifying.

00:51:53.762 --> 00:51:57.996
The one beside her seems quite strong too.

00:51:58.248 --> 00:52:00.169
- Captain Moon Ji Yeong!
- Yes, I felt it too.

00:52:01.146 --> 00:52:02.314
A blue insignia means...

00:52:02.314 --> 00:52:04.516
- That she's in the Air Force.
- The Air Force!

00:52:04.516 --> 00:52:05.276
The sky?

00:52:05.300 --> 00:52:06.285
A blue insignia means
that she's in the Air Force.

00:52:07.610 --> 00:52:09.264
Why is everyone glaring at us?

00:52:09.988 --> 00:52:10.988
I'm getting scared.

00:52:12.696 --> 00:52:13.762
There's Kkang Mi too!

00:52:13.996 --> 00:52:15.661
They're so laid back.

00:52:17.129 --> 00:52:20.666
I could only feel everyone's eyes on us.

00:52:21.500 --> 00:52:23.168
They were all intimidated
by how strong we seemed.

00:52:24.770 --> 00:52:25.984
We must show them...

00:52:26.008 --> 00:52:27.673
that we're just as strong
as they think that we are.

00:52:28.344 --> 00:52:30.609
Nobody stood out to me.

00:52:32.018 --> 00:52:33.618
(Things are getting more intense...)

00:52:33.642 --> 00:52:35.579
(now that the Special Mission Battalion
has entered the hangar.)

00:52:36.382 --> 00:52:38.951
(The other units are getting
very nervous...)

00:52:39.752 --> 00:52:40.853
She's incredibly charismatic.

00:52:43.547 --> 00:52:44.624
(Checking her out)

00:52:45.257 --> 00:52:47.926
You've been here before, right?

00:52:48.879 --> 00:52:50.339
She's asking that question again.

00:52:50.364 --> 00:52:51.263
There she goes again.

00:52:52.464 --> 00:52:55.100
You've been here before, right?

00:52:56.919 --> 00:52:59.038
Yes, I came here once for basic training.

00:52:59.705 --> 00:53:01.874
I also visited the 47th training ground.

00:53:03.826 --> 00:53:06.275
- You came here to learn your techniques?
- Yes, I did.

00:53:06.275 --> 00:53:08.313
The female soldiers also really know
how to intimidate others.

00:53:08.751 --> 00:53:10.549
She's something else, indeed.

00:53:10.686 --> 00:53:13.049
- She was at the 47th training ground.
- Right.

00:53:13.074 --> 00:53:14.293
(Hae Ju suddenly made herself seem
like a trainer over Seong Won.)

00:53:14.710 --> 00:53:17.690
(Bothered)

00:53:18.090 --> 00:53:20.125
Are we supposed to talk here?

00:53:21.186 --> 00:53:23.321
Are we supposed to ask questions here?

00:53:24.647 --> 00:53:26.432
The Special Mission Battalion is no joke.

00:53:26.432 --> 00:53:27.432
(Bothered)

00:53:28.444 --> 00:53:29.932
She seemed too unserious.

00:53:29.957 --> 00:53:31.370
She seemed unserious!

00:53:32.601 --> 00:53:34.740
I wasn't sure if she was trying
to test the waters or...

00:53:36.071 --> 00:53:38.977
I was just itching to go against everyone.

00:53:39.002 --> 00:53:40.002
That's Moon Ji Yeong.

00:53:40.356 --> 00:53:42.281
(The Marine Corps is the last to enter.)

00:53:42.281 --> 00:53:43.882
Only the Marine Corps needs to enter now.

00:53:44.742 --> 00:53:47.383
It must mean something
that they're entering last.

00:53:47.383 --> 00:53:50.085
The Marine Corps entered quite early on
in the last season.

00:53:50.175 --> 00:53:52.167
- Seeing that they're last today,
- Because they're the main characters?

00:53:52.167 --> 00:53:53.792
they must be the main characters
of the season.

00:53:55.624 --> 00:53:58.006
The last unit on "The Iron Squad W!"

00:54:04.426 --> 00:54:05.574
It's the Marine Corps.

00:54:06.155 --> 00:54:07.890
(A ferocious aura)

00:54:12.816 --> 00:54:15.581
The Marine Corps unit is
the last to enter.

00:54:15.606 --> 00:54:18.554
(The ROK Marine Corps)

00:54:19.080 --> 00:54:21.499
Why are all of their shoulders so big?

00:54:22.305 --> 00:54:23.572
(Their physiques stand out,
even from afar.)

00:54:23.572 --> 00:54:24.723
They seem different, indeed.

00:54:26.849 --> 00:54:28.260
She's very tall.

00:54:28.998 --> 00:54:30.733
She looks like she's about 173cm tall.

00:54:30.733 --> 00:54:33.098
- Sergeant Yoon Jae In is...
- She's so tall!

00:54:34.900 --> 00:54:35.900
What's with the second one?

00:54:37.847 --> 00:54:38.888
(An aura that silences everyone)

00:54:38.888 --> 00:54:40.636
Su Yeon's physique looks so strong.

00:54:40.636 --> 00:54:42.708
Jae In and Su Yeon really stand out!

00:54:44.770 --> 00:54:46.962
Oh, goodness. We're all doomed.

00:54:48.996 --> 00:54:49.996
That's the Marine Corps for you.

00:54:54.667 --> 00:54:55.997
Her height!

00:54:56.659 --> 00:54:57.659
Their shoulders!

00:54:57.733 --> 00:54:59.324
What's going on?

00:54:59.324 --> 00:55:00.659
- Their physiques...
- They all seem so tall.

00:55:01.470 --> 00:55:03.428
- We have to win.
- Yes, we can win.

00:55:03.428 --> 00:55:04.897
- "What are you talking about?"
- She's getting them together.

00:55:04.897 --> 00:55:05.955
She's pulling them together.

00:55:10.126 --> 00:55:11.193
They're gulping in anxiety!

00:55:11.613 --> 00:55:13.472
Even the Special Forces unit is wary!

00:55:17.004 --> 00:55:18.004
I'm so excited for them.

00:55:20.162 --> 00:55:27.757
(Everyone in the Marine Corps seems
absolutely intimidating.)

00:55:28.787 --> 00:55:30.088
Everyone is astounded.

00:55:34.990 --> 00:55:37.162
- They're not even asking questions.
- You're right.

00:55:37.187 --> 00:55:38.187
(The silence is suffocating.)

00:55:38.768 --> 00:55:43.569
(Everyone is frozen
at the Marine Corps unit's entrance.)

00:55:44.036 --> 00:55:47.790
The Marine Corps unit seems to have
the biggest ones.

00:55:48.415 --> 00:55:50.776
Their physiques are insane.

00:55:50.776 --> 00:55:52.244
Their physiques play a huge part.

00:55:52.330 --> 00:55:54.513
It's not about fighting to live.
We have to fight to survive.

00:55:56.145 --> 00:55:57.499
(Smirking)

00:55:57.499 --> 00:55:59.017
Everyone was murmuring,

00:55:59.181 --> 00:56:01.286
which made me think
that we had great physiques.

00:56:01.924 --> 00:56:04.089
We're ready to show
what the ROK Marine Corps has.

00:56:05.387 --> 00:56:06.658
Overall,

00:56:07.555 --> 00:56:10.407
they're smaller than I expected.

00:56:11.367 --> 00:56:12.831
Yes, they're all tiny.

00:56:14.997 --> 00:56:16.335
(And so, the six units have gathered.)

00:56:16.335 --> 00:56:18.570
- All six units have entered the hangar.
- I'm so excited!

00:56:19.989 --> 00:56:23.312
(What will happen now?)

00:56:23.835 --> 00:56:26.278
We can't make any judgment
based on their appearances, anyway.

00:56:27.446 --> 00:56:28.837
- That's the answer.
- Indeed.

00:56:28.837 --> 00:56:30.916
- You can't judge a book by its cover.
- That's right.

00:56:32.895 --> 00:56:34.650
(The doors to the hangar are
opening again.)

00:56:34.650 --> 00:56:36.092
At last, the hidden unit!

00:56:36.665 --> 00:56:38.090
The strongest...

00:56:38.443 --> 00:56:39.424
hidden unit is...

00:56:39.424 --> 00:56:40.525
The hidden unit?

00:56:41.326 --> 00:56:45.568
(Everyone's turning their heads.)

00:56:45.795 --> 00:56:47.530
(Who are they?)

00:56:51.073 --> 00:56:53.305
- My gosh!
- No.

00:56:53.375 --> 00:56:54.740
- What?
- Hold up.

00:56:54.740 --> 00:56:56.104
Why do I look so weak?

00:56:56.545 --> 00:56:57.180
That's...

00:56:57.204 --> 00:56:59.077
What was that?

00:57:01.079 --> 00:57:03.131
- There!
- Let's go up.

00:57:03.131 --> 00:57:04.783
- Hello.
- Nice to meet you.

00:57:04.783 --> 00:57:05.668
- Hello!
- Salute!

00:57:05.668 --> 00:57:06.985
Nice to meet you!

00:57:06.985 --> 00:57:07.985
- Hello.
- Hi.

00:57:07.986 --> 00:57:09.264
My gosh, this is so...

00:57:09.264 --> 00:57:10.479
We need to greet them properly too.

00:57:10.479 --> 00:57:11.479
Okay, then.

00:57:11.873 --> 00:57:12.928
Stand tall, MCs!

00:57:13.992 --> 00:57:14.884
And salute!

00:57:14.884 --> 00:57:16.194
- Iron!
- Iron!

00:57:18.854 --> 00:57:19.798
Down!

00:57:20.269 --> 00:57:22.398
When we were just talking among ourselves,

00:57:22.398 --> 00:57:24.870
we talked about how cool it'd be...

00:57:25.163 --> 00:57:26.805
- to have female troops on the show.
- That's right.

00:57:26.805 --> 00:57:28.637
And you guys aren't just cool.

00:57:28.637 --> 00:57:30.208
In fact, I'm terrified.

00:57:31.182 --> 00:57:33.378
- I'm so intimidated.
- You can't even make eye contact!

00:57:34.443 --> 00:57:39.885
First off, let's introduce
and interview the six units.

00:57:40.319 --> 00:57:41.319
First,

00:57:41.687 --> 00:57:42.854
the 707th Group!

00:57:42.991 --> 00:57:45.624
It's the ROK 707th Special Missions Group.

00:57:46.111 --> 00:57:47.946
If I may ask you...

00:57:48.083 --> 00:57:50.629
about the sniper badge...

00:57:50.773 --> 00:57:52.354
As you know, I love snipers.

00:57:52.441 --> 00:57:55.584
- There's a sniper!
- I play a lot of video games,

00:57:55.584 --> 00:57:58.904
so are you the same kind of sniper
that I see in video games?

00:57:59.484 --> 00:58:00.484
That's right.

00:58:00.642 --> 00:58:02.424
You must expect yourself...

00:58:02.424 --> 00:58:04.509
to be better at shooting than anyone.

00:58:04.509 --> 00:58:06.378
- That's right.
- But is there a unit here...

00:58:06.528 --> 00:58:07.679
that you feel a bit intimidated by?

00:58:08.090 --> 00:58:10.682
Are you worried about a particular unit
for the shooting mission?

00:58:12.484 --> 00:58:15.721
No, I'm not really worried about any unit.

00:58:15.898 --> 00:58:17.155
That's a real sniper!

00:58:17.873 --> 00:58:19.281
The Marine Corps unit is annoyed.

00:58:19.281 --> 00:58:20.525
Su Yeon is annoyed.

00:58:20.525 --> 00:58:22.027
If I must tell you,

00:58:22.527 --> 00:58:26.289
Sergeant Yang Hae Ju
from the Special Forces...

00:58:26.313 --> 00:58:30.505
was my partner in sniping.

00:58:30.559 --> 00:58:31.937
I guess I can say that she's not bad.

00:58:31.937 --> 00:58:33.138
- "Not bad?"
- "Not bad!"

00:58:33.912 --> 00:58:35.346
I guess I can say that she's not bad.

00:58:36.208 --> 00:58:38.110
Were you two a gunner and her assistant?

00:58:38.393 --> 00:58:39.551
That's right.

00:58:39.576 --> 00:58:40.899
(Park Bo Ram from the 707th Group was
Yang Hae Ju's gunner.)

00:58:41.103 --> 00:58:42.914
We were a gunner and an assistant.

00:58:43.051 --> 00:58:46.618
We were the closest.
She's my most cherished younger colleague.

00:58:46.802 --> 00:58:50.322
She's very talented at shooting.

00:58:50.322 --> 00:58:51.322
She's the best.

00:58:51.467 --> 00:58:52.758
I trained her, after all.

00:58:54.263 --> 00:58:56.495
This relationship is one to watch out for.

00:58:57.229 --> 00:58:59.431
What's your honest opinion of each other?

00:58:59.535 --> 00:59:02.067
What if you were to go
against each other now?

00:59:02.501 --> 00:59:03.969
Who do you think would win?

00:59:05.003 --> 00:59:06.171
Just be honest.

00:59:07.272 --> 00:59:10.709
I wasn't just an assistant sniper.

00:59:10.709 --> 00:59:11.587
Right!

00:59:11.612 --> 00:59:13.201
Here she goes! She's strong.

00:59:13.226 --> 00:59:15.714
I wasn't just an assistant sniper.

00:59:15.739 --> 00:59:16.498
(Flinching)

00:59:16.805 --> 00:59:18.583
Right on!

00:59:19.341 --> 00:59:20.852
This is so much fun to watch!

00:59:20.852 --> 00:59:22.888
It's like watching a drama.

00:59:23.555 --> 00:59:25.824
I've been a gunner myself,

00:59:25.867 --> 00:59:29.127
- so I'm just as good as her.
- You're not an assistant forever.

00:59:29.237 --> 00:59:31.022
Sergeant Park Bo Ram...

00:59:31.047 --> 00:59:33.565
said that she was the first female gunner.

00:59:33.932 --> 00:59:35.700
But just because she's the first one...

00:59:35.700 --> 00:59:38.360
doesn't mean that she's good.

00:59:38.360 --> 00:59:39.604
This relationship is
so interesting to watch.

00:59:39.604 --> 00:59:42.207
She thinks that she's just as good.

00:59:42.407 --> 00:59:43.642
What do you think?

00:59:44.502 --> 00:59:45.988
You still have a long way to go.

00:59:45.988 --> 00:59:46.988
She still has a long way to go!

00:59:47.013 --> 00:59:48.947
She's saying that in public too?

00:59:48.947 --> 00:59:50.248
My goodness!

00:59:50.849 --> 00:59:52.160
You still have a long way to go.

00:59:52.953 --> 00:59:54.319
She still has a lot to learn!

00:59:54.319 --> 00:59:55.691
(Enraged)

00:59:56.407 --> 00:59:57.407
She's all grown up.

00:59:57.532 --> 00:59:59.257
She even has the courage
to make such a comment.

00:59:59.397 --> 01:00:01.930
She said that she could beat me
because she'd been a gunner too.

01:00:02.093 --> 01:00:03.531
But you can't really call her my rival.

01:00:03.531 --> 01:00:04.966
She's still a baby to me.

01:00:04.991 --> 01:00:06.234
- A baby!
- Just a baby!

01:00:06.234 --> 01:00:07.368
I couldn't last a second there!

01:00:07.368 --> 01:00:09.037
This is like a scene in a movie.

01:00:09.404 --> 01:00:10.696
The air is so tense.

01:00:11.606 --> 01:00:12.606
It's crazy.

01:00:12.631 --> 01:00:17.028
I'm expecting a big match
in the shooting mission.

01:00:17.028 --> 01:00:17.929
I can't wait for that!

01:00:17.954 --> 01:00:20.949
They know each other so well
that they can totally be rivals.

01:00:20.949 --> 01:00:22.083
I can't wait for it.

01:00:23.296 --> 01:00:24.209
Next...

01:00:24.719 --> 01:00:27.312
I don't know if I can say this.

01:00:27.599 --> 01:00:28.642
No way!

01:00:28.642 --> 01:00:30.178
(What is it?)

01:00:30.525 --> 01:00:31.525
What's going on?

01:00:33.695 --> 01:00:36.101
One of the Navy unit soldiers...

01:00:36.101 --> 01:00:36.898
Navy?

01:00:36.898 --> 01:00:38.166
said,

01:00:39.234 --> 01:00:40.234
"The Marine Corps is..."

01:00:42.200 --> 01:00:44.539
"just a subordinate unit to the Navy.
It's not that special."

01:00:45.263 --> 01:00:46.875
Why was I told to read that?

01:00:47.721 --> 01:00:48.600
That's bold.

01:00:48.681 --> 01:00:49.878
My gosh.

01:00:49.935 --> 01:00:51.102
- This is...
- It's so...

01:00:51.102 --> 01:00:53.048
The Navy is really getting
on the Marines' nerves!

01:00:54.883 --> 01:00:57.152
"Just a subordinate unit to the Navy.
It's not that special."

01:00:57.177 --> 01:00:58.386
That's bold.

01:00:59.718 --> 01:01:00.956
(All eyes on the Navy)

01:01:00.956 --> 01:01:02.727
That's so bold.

01:01:03.491 --> 01:01:04.959
What do I do?

01:01:04.959 --> 01:01:06.461
I feel bad just by listening to this!

01:01:07.595 --> 01:01:09.430
They must be so mad right now.

01:01:09.727 --> 01:01:12.207
(So cold)

01:01:12.383 --> 01:01:14.369
Who in the Navy said this?

01:01:14.394 --> 01:01:16.471
(Who made this bold statement?)

01:01:16.496 --> 01:01:18.172
- It's me!
- She raised her hand.

01:01:18.537 --> 01:01:19.537
It's me!

01:01:20.005 --> 01:01:21.059
- It's Hye In.
- Really?

01:01:21.059 --> 01:01:22.311
- You really said this?
- Yes.

01:01:22.336 --> 01:01:24.245
What, exactly, did you say?

01:01:25.417 --> 01:01:27.766
I said exactly what was quoted.

01:01:27.766 --> 01:01:29.005
Structurally speaking,

01:01:29.029 --> 01:01:31.155
the Marine Corps is
a subordinate to the Navy.

01:01:31.709 --> 01:01:34.455
All soldiers serve the same task,

01:01:34.618 --> 01:01:37.202
and therefore, I don't believe
that the Marine Corps is extra special.

01:01:37.227 --> 01:01:38.927
That's...

01:01:39.438 --> 01:01:41.329
She's saying
that the Marine Corps is not a big deal.

01:01:41.329 --> 01:01:45.193
I can see
Dong Hyun's face getting tense too.

01:01:45.193 --> 01:01:46.278
That's a bit...

01:01:47.085 --> 01:01:48.085
Goodness.

01:01:48.369 --> 01:01:50.369
(The Marine Corps unit is silent
after hearing the Navy's statement.)

01:01:51.476 --> 01:01:52.874
(Shocked)

01:01:53.364 --> 01:01:54.809
They're really ready to fight.

01:01:56.733 --> 01:01:58.479
You said exactly what was quoted.

01:01:58.479 --> 01:02:01.071
- She's trying to work them up.
- It's so scary.

01:02:02.500 --> 01:02:05.720
Can she take responsibility
for what she said?

01:02:07.815 --> 01:02:10.058
Why are they getting so worked up
when it's true?

01:02:10.058 --> 01:02:11.726
Here comes Angry Cho Hui.

01:02:12.257 --> 01:02:13.661
I didn't really care.

01:02:13.661 --> 01:02:14.746
- Sergeant Won!
- Cho Hui!

01:02:14.746 --> 01:02:15.997
She's back!

01:02:17.048 --> 01:02:18.048
I'm scared.

01:02:18.203 --> 01:02:19.634
They're so savage.

01:02:19.804 --> 01:02:21.236
The air is so tense.

01:02:21.970 --> 01:02:22.482
What a bold statement.

01:02:22.506 --> 01:02:23.905
If I may be honest...

01:02:24.756 --> 01:02:26.174
If I may be honest,

01:02:26.174 --> 01:02:28.810
it is true that the Marine Corps is
a subordinate unit to the Navy.

01:02:29.577 --> 01:02:30.812
It's true, but...

01:02:30.837 --> 01:02:31.696
But?

01:02:31.776 --> 01:02:33.246
our fighting power...

01:02:33.246 --> 01:02:37.252
and what we're about to show you
as the Marine Corps...

01:02:37.315 --> 01:02:41.033
will make you regret
what you've just said.

01:02:41.058 --> 01:02:42.590
She's so calm and collected
while making her point.

01:02:45.310 --> 01:02:48.529
The Marine Corps fights at the front line.

01:02:48.713 --> 01:02:50.381
And the Navy fights in the back.

01:02:50.798 --> 01:02:52.524
That's why the Marine Corps is stronger.

01:02:52.524 --> 01:02:53.524
Right.

01:02:53.901 --> 01:02:56.004
It's finally time! I'm also dying to know,

01:02:56.004 --> 01:02:59.514
as well as many troops here.

01:02:59.624 --> 01:03:01.676
Everyone's wary of this particular unit.

01:03:02.610 --> 01:03:05.296
Let me introduce you
to the Special Mission Battalion!

01:03:05.296 --> 01:03:06.414
The Special Mission Battalion!

01:03:06.414 --> 01:03:07.414
- The Special Mission Battalion!
- It's the Special Mission Battalion.

01:03:08.349 --> 01:03:11.019
What kind of missions do they take on?

01:03:11.019 --> 01:03:12.554
They only take on special ones.

01:03:15.393 --> 01:03:17.825
The Special Mission Battalion troops are
finally coming up.

01:03:21.399 --> 01:03:23.564
Seong Won is tall.

01:03:24.549 --> 01:03:28.299
(The Special Mission Battalion unit is
finally revealing itself.)

01:03:28.496 --> 01:03:30.672
I really want to know what that unit does.

01:03:30.672 --> 01:03:33.011
I can't wait to hear
about what missions they take on.

01:03:33.011 --> 01:03:34.342
They're different from the others.

01:03:35.610 --> 01:03:37.412
Defend with life and serve with life!

01:03:37.412 --> 01:03:39.814
We go when our nation calls.

01:03:40.148 --> 01:03:41.333
We're the Special Mission Battalion.

01:03:41.426 --> 01:03:42.643
- Salute!
- Salute!

01:03:42.927 --> 01:03:44.152
"Defend with life!"

01:03:44.315 --> 01:03:46.788
"Defend with life and serve with life."

01:03:53.828 --> 01:03:54.828
Down.

01:03:56.301 --> 01:03:58.069
I'm Yang Ji Ni,
the Sergeant First Class...

01:03:58.069 --> 01:03:59.600
in the Capital Mechanized
Infantry Division.

01:03:59.692 --> 01:04:01.206
My expertise is in collecting information.

01:04:01.206 --> 01:04:02.337
- Collecting information?
- Collecting information!

01:04:02.337 --> 01:04:04.829
I'm Captain Moon Ji Yeong...

01:04:04.829 --> 01:04:06.341
in the 16th Fighter Wing of ROK Air Force.

01:04:06.462 --> 01:04:08.176
I'm a military police officer.

01:04:08.339 --> 01:04:09.456
A military police officer!

01:04:09.514 --> 01:04:11.616
I'm Sergeant First Class Kim A Ran...

01:04:11.616 --> 01:04:13.681
from the 55th Security Corps.

01:04:14.582 --> 01:04:18.186
My duty is confidential.

01:04:18.370 --> 01:04:19.370
- What?
- Confidential?

01:04:19.787 --> 01:04:21.479
If it's confidential,
she must be in the intelligence unit.

01:04:21.479 --> 01:04:22.157
It's confidential!

01:04:22.157 --> 01:04:23.405
There's another one of those.

01:04:23.430 --> 01:04:25.657
(Kim A Ran of the 55th Security Corps
in the Presidential Security Service)

01:04:26.023 --> 01:04:27.078
The Presidential Security Service?

01:04:29.673 --> 01:04:30.673
Does she work at the Blue House?

01:04:31.543 --> 01:04:33.525
I'm Sergeant First Class Cho Seong Won...

01:04:33.525 --> 01:04:35.270
of the 35th Special Mission Battalion.

01:04:35.607 --> 01:04:37.238
My duty is a national secret.

01:04:37.388 --> 01:04:38.840
A national secret!

01:04:38.917 --> 01:04:40.582
That's incredible.

01:04:40.685 --> 01:04:43.277
This is like the Headquarters
of the Intelligence Detachment.

01:04:43.678 --> 01:04:44.678
We have someone
with a confidential duty...

01:04:45.580 --> 01:04:46.881
and another with a national secret duty.

01:04:47.040 --> 01:04:48.783
Confidential and a national secret.

01:04:49.307 --> 01:04:52.583
(The Special Mission Battalion has troops
with various special mission roles.)

01:04:52.640 --> 01:04:55.152
I thought that it was...

01:04:55.346 --> 01:04:57.959
four members from the Tarantula Unit,

01:04:57.959 --> 01:04:59.564
but it was just a coalition.

01:04:59.589 --> 01:05:00.615
(She didn't expect a coalition
of Special Mission Battalion troops.)

01:05:01.014 --> 01:05:02.330
They're basically all on their own.

01:05:04.462 --> 01:05:05.633
- They're either the best or the worst.
- Exactly.

01:05:05.633 --> 01:05:07.702
They'll either have great teamwork
or the worst teamwork.

01:05:07.727 --> 01:05:08.536
I think so too.

01:05:08.580 --> 01:05:10.221
Yes, it's one or the other.

01:05:10.246 --> 01:05:12.665
- That's a good observation.
- I know.

01:05:12.814 --> 01:05:16.577
The unit that I've only heard about is
finally here.

01:05:16.978 --> 01:05:17.978
Sergeant Cho Seong Won.

01:05:18.003 --> 01:05:18.913
- Yes, sir.
- Yes.

01:05:19.180 --> 01:05:21.025
Everyone's wary of Seong Won.

01:05:21.025 --> 01:05:23.574
- Yes, I'm so intrigued about her.
- The 35th Special Mission Battalion...

01:05:23.574 --> 01:05:26.354
is the legendary Tarantula Unit...

01:05:26.490 --> 01:05:27.888
of female Special Mission Battalion
troops, yes?

01:05:28.656 --> 01:05:29.656
Yes, that's right.

01:05:30.558 --> 01:05:31.759
The Tarantula Unit!

01:05:31.759 --> 01:05:32.759
The Tarantula Unit...

01:05:32.977 --> 01:05:34.529
That sounds terrifying!

01:05:34.529 --> 01:05:36.864
The 35th Special Mission Battalion...

01:05:37.098 --> 01:05:39.734
guards the capital city of Seoul.

01:05:39.784 --> 01:05:42.500
We train to protect Seoul...

01:05:42.525 --> 01:05:45.206
from threats of terrorism
and serve to protect the city.

01:05:45.436 --> 01:05:48.543
I'm in a special unit
for special missions for female troops,

01:05:48.543 --> 01:05:51.712
but my role is a national secret,
so I cannot tell you what it is.

01:05:52.317 --> 01:05:53.317
That's inspiring.

01:05:54.185 --> 01:05:57.021
Is the Tarantula Unit
the only Special Mission Battalion...

01:05:57.021 --> 01:05:59.287
of female soldiers in Korea?

01:05:59.437 --> 01:06:01.619
Yes, the Tarantula Unit is
currently the only one.

01:06:02.940 --> 01:06:04.959
The Tarantula Unit. That's cool.

01:06:06.360 --> 01:06:07.641
As the Tarantula Unit
and the 707th Group...

01:06:07.665 --> 01:06:10.765
both train to prevent acts of terrorism,

01:06:11.299 --> 01:06:13.434
I'm most wary of her.

01:06:14.645 --> 01:06:16.013
I was so curious about them!

01:06:16.013 --> 01:06:18.239
They must be powerful
in all sorts of ways, then.

01:06:19.539 --> 01:06:20.808
And so,

01:06:20.808 --> 01:06:22.710
we've revealed all six units...

01:06:22.710 --> 01:06:26.113
competing in this season
of "The Iron Squad W."

01:06:26.113 --> 01:06:28.516
We'll have to watch them compete...

01:06:28.516 --> 01:06:30.084
to see who's stronger and weaker.

01:06:30.084 --> 01:06:32.753
But we've never had...

01:06:32.963 --> 01:06:34.655
- such a tense first meet.
- I know!

01:06:35.308 --> 01:06:36.858
- Seriously.
- It was such an intense first meet.

01:06:36.858 --> 01:06:39.393
It was so intense that it was suffocating.

01:06:39.393 --> 01:06:42.029
Even just watching them was a struggle.

01:06:43.831 --> 01:06:47.034
Two new units have been introduced
to "The Iron Squad W."

01:06:47.134 --> 01:06:49.220
It's the ROK Army
and the Special Mission Battalion.

01:06:49.413 --> 01:06:53.107
The ROK Army must be very angered...

01:06:53.132 --> 01:06:55.847
to have been undermined
for being a non-special mission unit.

01:06:56.177 --> 01:06:58.279
- I know.
- I'm sure...

01:06:58.516 --> 01:07:01.446
that they're dying to prove themselves
to everyone now.

01:07:01.589 --> 01:07:02.950
"Everyone's underestimating us?"

01:07:02.950 --> 01:07:04.215
"We'll prove you wrong, then."
They must be thinking that,

01:07:04.215 --> 01:07:07.555
which, I presume,
will make them very strong.

01:07:08.813 --> 01:07:11.569
(After the first meeting
of all six units...)

01:07:11.569 --> 01:07:12.760
Are they starting on a mission?

01:07:13.531 --> 01:07:15.797
(They're looking very tense...)

01:07:16.020 --> 01:07:18.466
They're moving
to the first mission ground.

01:07:18.466 --> 01:07:19.400
Will they have trench fights now?

01:07:19.400 --> 01:07:20.972
Maybe. That's our signature mission.

01:07:20.972 --> 01:07:22.260
(The masters are waiting for the troops
on the mission ground.)

01:07:22.841 --> 01:07:24.529
- There they are!
- The masters.

01:07:24.554 --> 01:07:26.684
(Master Choi Young Jae)

01:07:28.687 --> 01:07:30.378
(The 24 troops of "The Iron Squad W"
are all lined up.)

01:07:30.378 --> 01:07:31.479
- I'm nervous.
- This should be fun.

01:07:32.707 --> 01:07:33.707
The Special Forces!

01:07:35.983 --> 01:07:37.218
The ROK Army.

01:07:38.753 --> 01:07:39.954
The ROK Navy.

01:07:41.659 --> 01:07:42.794
The ROK 707th Special Missions Group.

01:07:44.926 --> 01:07:45.926
The Special Mission Battalion.

01:07:47.728 --> 01:07:49.330
The ROK Marine Corps.

01:07:52.300 --> 01:07:53.701
A team-based survival game...

01:07:53.971 --> 01:07:54.971
in search of the strongest female troops,

01:07:55.309 --> 01:07:56.309
"The Iron Squad W."

01:07:57.922 --> 01:08:01.142
Troops of the six units
representing Korea's female troops,

01:08:01.409 --> 01:08:02.409
welcome to the show.

01:08:03.003 --> 01:08:05.372
The honor of your unit is on the line,

01:08:05.530 --> 01:08:08.316
so please do your best
to fight until the end.

01:08:09.891 --> 01:08:10.891
They look so determined!

01:08:11.295 --> 01:08:12.326
They look savage.

01:08:12.497 --> 01:08:14.655
The first mission of "The Iron Squad W..."

01:08:14.799 --> 01:08:17.892
The first mission will now be announced.

01:08:18.002 --> 01:08:18.899
What will it be?

01:08:19.036 --> 01:08:20.828
- With a big benefit on the line,
- Already?

01:08:20.828 --> 01:08:21.828
you'll climb the rope...

01:08:22.233 --> 01:08:23.233
that's 11m tall.

01:08:23.581 --> 01:08:25.009
They're climbing the 11m rope!

01:08:25.009 --> 01:08:27.068
- That's quite high.
- Climbing up 11m isn't easy.

01:08:27.068 --> 01:08:28.836
That's as high as the fifth floor
of a building.

01:08:28.899 --> 01:08:32.283
That's the height
where humans feel the most fear.

01:08:32.597 --> 01:08:34.665
Why are they fighting for a benefit
from the first mission?

01:08:34.665 --> 01:08:36.310
There weren't any benefits
in the initial tester missions previously.

01:08:36.310 --> 01:08:37.310
Exactly.

01:08:38.181 --> 01:08:39.679
We're doing this right now?

01:08:40.411 --> 01:08:41.555
From the start?

01:08:41.975 --> 01:08:44.511
I was quite stunned to be told
that I had to climb the rope.

01:08:45.102 --> 01:08:47.822
I didn't expect us
to be climbing a rope...

01:08:47.822 --> 01:08:49.790
in the first pre-game mission.

01:08:51.539 --> 01:08:55.154
You'll climb the 11m rope in two rounds.

01:08:55.179 --> 01:08:56.063
Two rounds!

01:08:56.063 --> 01:08:59.166
One person from each unit
will climb the rope.

01:09:00.001 --> 01:09:02.136
Round 1 will be a 1-on-1 race.

01:09:02.436 --> 01:09:05.640
Two soldiers from two units
will start climbing the ropes at once.

01:09:05.973 --> 01:09:08.509
The soldier who rings
the bell first will win.

01:09:09.649 --> 01:09:10.755
In Round Two,

01:09:11.112 --> 01:09:13.180
the three finalists...

01:09:13.471 --> 01:09:15.416
- will climb the ropes at once.
- At once!

01:09:15.416 --> 01:09:18.719
And the rankings will be determined
in the order of them ringing the bells.

01:09:21.422 --> 01:09:22.894
- The same people?
- Yes, the same team representatives.

01:09:22.894 --> 01:09:23.991
Will they even have energy after that?

01:09:23.991 --> 01:09:25.343
- Won't they be exhausted?
- Their forearm muscles are...

01:09:25.343 --> 01:09:26.661
- bound to be exhausted after Round One.
- Totally, right?

01:09:27.695 --> 01:09:29.797
I climb ropes for fun after lunch.

01:09:29.927 --> 01:09:31.932
I can't possibly lose.

01:09:32.615 --> 01:09:35.135
As soon as I saw the ropes, I got excited.

01:09:35.770 --> 01:09:37.705
I was ready to have fun.

01:09:37.730 --> 01:09:39.507
Climbing 11m isn't easy.

01:09:40.007 --> 01:09:41.142
Before we begin the races,

01:09:41.167 --> 01:09:43.660
I'll announce the big winning benefit.

01:09:43.918 --> 01:09:46.213
They have to win the benefit
to have a smooth start.

01:09:46.671 --> 01:09:48.616
They're getting competitive now.

01:09:48.819 --> 01:09:52.048
The winning benefit
of climbing the 11m rope is...

01:09:53.317 --> 01:09:54.317
What is it?

01:09:54.342 --> 01:09:57.668
(What's the big benefit?)

01:09:58.137 --> 01:10:01.440
a chance to choose your opponent.

01:10:01.465 --> 01:10:03.531
Yes, a chance to choose their opponent!

01:10:03.728 --> 01:10:04.799
That's huge.

01:10:04.799 --> 01:10:06.434
In the following mission,

01:10:06.927 --> 01:10:08.769
the top three units will go
in the winning order...

01:10:08.880 --> 01:10:11.639
to choose the unit
that they want to go against.

01:10:12.506 --> 01:10:13.774
We have to win.

01:10:13.774 --> 01:10:15.810
- We have to intimidate everyone.
- Right on.

01:10:15.893 --> 01:10:18.045
We get a chance to choose our opponents...

01:10:18.345 --> 01:10:19.447
when we don't even know
what the next mission will be.

01:10:19.472 --> 01:10:21.782
We have to win first place
and nothing else.

01:10:21.866 --> 01:10:22.917
We have to win first place.

01:10:23.087 --> 01:10:24.952
A chance to choose your opponent is
a very powerful benefit.

01:10:24.952 --> 01:10:26.353
Yes, right from the start too.

01:10:27.462 --> 01:10:28.506
(They're having an 11m climbing race
for a chance to choose their opponents.)

01:10:28.506 --> 01:10:29.857
Let's begin the 11m climbing race.

01:10:30.291 --> 01:10:31.291
This race is...

01:10:31.516 --> 01:10:32.516
Who's going now?

01:10:33.260 --> 01:10:34.795
The first race!

01:10:34.999 --> 01:10:36.731
Two units will play
against each other first.

01:10:37.898 --> 01:10:39.233
- The Navy...
- The Navy!

01:10:39.233 --> 01:10:40.101
will go against the Army.

01:10:40.126 --> 01:10:41.135
The Navy against the Army!

01:10:42.058 --> 01:10:44.038
This is a battle between the rivals.

01:10:44.038 --> 01:10:45.296
(Two non-special units are fighting
for their pride.)

01:10:45.606 --> 01:10:46.707
Each unit representative...

01:10:46.993 --> 01:10:47.993
may now step forward.

01:10:49.043 --> 01:10:50.275
Here come the representatives.

01:10:50.275 --> 01:10:51.275
Who will they be?

01:10:53.297 --> 01:10:55.206
Hye In is representing the Navy!

01:10:55.231 --> 01:10:56.100
Park Hye In.

01:10:56.100 --> 01:10:58.919
(And who will go against her
as the Army's representative?)

01:10:58.919 --> 01:11:00.287
The Army is putting...

01:11:00.524 --> 01:11:02.490
- Han Su Bin forward.
- First Lieutenant Han Su Bin.

01:11:02.969 --> 01:11:04.504
The representatives
from the Army and the Navy,

01:11:05.292 --> 01:11:06.794
please say something before you go.

01:11:08.228 --> 01:11:10.364
First Lieutenant Han Su Bin
of the ROK Army!

01:11:10.865 --> 01:11:12.366
I'll do my best!

01:11:12.967 --> 01:11:14.969
I'm confident about my muscular strength.

01:11:15.676 --> 01:11:18.562
I'm trained in jiu-jitsu,
MMA, and climbing,

01:11:18.587 --> 01:11:20.775
and I love all sorts of sports.

01:11:20.938 --> 01:11:22.159
I was confident that I'd win.

01:11:22.184 --> 01:11:23.803
She has so much leverage
if she's a rock climber.

01:11:24.231 --> 01:11:26.280
Sergeant First Class Park Hye In
of the ROK Navy!

01:11:26.280 --> 01:11:28.049
I'll show you my best!

01:11:28.883 --> 01:11:30.685
"I must win, no matter what."

01:11:31.185 --> 01:11:32.586
That was the only thing on my mind.

01:11:34.057 --> 01:11:35.756
Their pride is on the line.

01:11:35.756 --> 01:11:37.358
Han Su Bin against Park Hye In!

01:11:37.922 --> 01:11:38.793
Ready?

01:11:38.793 --> 01:11:41.362
- I feel like the Army will do better.
- She's a rock climber, after all.

01:11:41.362 --> 01:11:42.580
- She must be better.
- I know.

01:11:43.267 --> 01:11:44.999
- It's so high!
- It's so tall!

01:11:45.549 --> 01:11:48.079
(The race has begun.)

01:11:48.104 --> 01:11:49.087
Off they go.

01:11:49.547 --> 01:11:50.741
Let's go!

01:11:51.195 --> 01:11:52.506
Her foot got tangled right at the start!

01:11:52.506 --> 01:11:53.758
- Right from the start!
- It got stuck!

01:11:53.758 --> 01:11:54.842
- She got stuck, right?
- Something caught her foot.

01:11:54.842 --> 01:11:56.677
Su Bin's foot got stuck in something.

01:12:00.918 --> 01:12:01.918
(Startled)

01:12:01.943 --> 01:12:02.667
Let's go!

01:12:02.667 --> 01:12:03.484
Come on!

01:12:03.484 --> 01:12:05.219
- You're doing great!
- Oh, no!

01:12:07.031 --> 01:12:09.337
(Unlike Park Hye In,
who got off to a smooth start,)

01:12:10.147 --> 01:12:11.456
(Han Su Bin's foot got stuck
right at the start.)

01:12:11.456 --> 01:12:13.460
She needs to untangle her foot first.

01:12:13.460 --> 01:12:14.728
Is she just pulling that with her?

01:12:14.728 --> 01:12:15.728
It was a disaster.

01:12:17.021 --> 01:12:17.922
She's going to drag it with her?

01:12:17.922 --> 01:12:19.166
- No, it fell off.
- My goodness.

01:12:19.567 --> 01:12:22.136
- You're doing great!
- Park Hye In is in the lead.

01:12:22.419 --> 01:12:24.164
Hye In, who's taller, is in the lead.

01:12:25.663 --> 01:12:27.908
She shouldn't wrap
her foot around that many times.

01:12:28.345 --> 01:12:31.178
She seems to know
how to wrap her foot around the rope,

01:12:31.178 --> 01:12:32.680
but she seems a bit sloppy at it.

01:12:33.259 --> 01:12:35.128
That means that she has to use
her forearm muscles even more.

01:12:35.947 --> 01:12:36.947
(Su Bin is a little unstable.)

01:12:36.972 --> 01:12:38.719
Su Bin is falling behind.

01:12:39.644 --> 01:12:40.765
(Hye In is staying stable
and continuing her climb up.)

01:12:40.765 --> 01:12:43.134
Hye In is so stable!

01:12:43.134 --> 01:12:44.758
Yes, she is!

01:12:45.451 --> 01:12:47.695
But Su Bin is relying
solely on her forearm muscles.

01:12:48.395 --> 01:12:49.395
We won.

01:12:49.420 --> 01:12:51.265
We're going to win in Round One so easily.

01:12:51.765 --> 01:12:53.400
I was so sure that we were going to win.

01:12:53.614 --> 01:12:55.402
All I was thinking was
that I had to keep climbing quickly.

01:12:56.270 --> 01:12:58.172
It wasn't going as easily as I expected.

01:12:58.632 --> 01:13:00.441
The Army is...

01:13:00.605 --> 01:13:01.709
You got this!

01:13:01.734 --> 01:13:03.244
Just keep it up!

01:13:04.117 --> 01:13:04.814
Right on!

01:13:04.814 --> 01:13:06.180
The Navy is in the lead.

01:13:06.180 --> 01:13:07.388
(Hye In is still in the lead.)

01:13:07.419 --> 01:13:08.419
Come on!

01:13:10.261 --> 01:13:12.553
But Hye In is starting to get a bit tired.

01:13:12.553 --> 01:13:13.420
She's slowing down!

01:13:13.461 --> 01:13:14.763
Keep up your pace!

01:13:14.805 --> 01:13:16.824
She has to keep that pace up.

01:13:17.358 --> 01:13:18.010
Stay calm.

01:13:18.034 --> 01:13:19.463
- You got this!
- Keep it up!

01:13:19.488 --> 01:13:20.728
Is she going to turn the table around?

01:13:21.195 --> 01:13:22.563
Su Bin is catching up!

01:13:22.563 --> 01:13:26.090
- Stay calm.
- Come on!

01:13:26.090 --> 01:13:26.897
Your leg!

01:13:26.897 --> 01:13:28.469
- She caught up!
- She caught up to her!

01:13:28.585 --> 01:13:29.585
One more time!

01:13:31.576 --> 01:13:34.508
I just looked up
and kept climbing for my life.

01:13:34.775 --> 01:13:36.587
- Keep going!
- Keep pushing!

01:13:37.321 --> 01:13:38.746
- The last push!
- One more time!

01:13:38.771 --> 01:13:39.370
Su Bin!

01:13:39.370 --> 01:13:40.981
- One more time!
- One more pull!

01:13:41.372 --> 01:13:42.883
Just a little more!

01:13:44.010 --> 01:13:45.010
You're doing great!

01:13:45.076 --> 01:13:45.953
The last push!

01:13:45.953 --> 01:13:47.087
- Come on!
- You're almost there!

01:13:47.087 --> 01:13:48.656
- Who will win?
- They're so close to finishing!

01:13:49.020 --> 01:13:50.991
(Su Bin from the Army?)

01:13:50.991 --> 01:13:53.193
Will the Army turn the game around?

01:13:53.894 --> 01:13:55.963
The one to ring the bell first wins!

01:13:56.784 --> 01:13:57.784
They're neck to neck!

01:13:58.802 --> 01:14:00.334
(Su Bin from the Army won.)

01:14:00.531 --> 01:14:01.912
(No way!)

01:14:02.136 --> 01:14:04.104
Su Bin, from the Army, won!

01:14:04.722 --> 01:14:05.449
You got this!

01:14:05.449 --> 01:14:07.065
(Su Bin turned the game around and won.)

01:14:07.065 --> 01:14:08.642
Okay, nice!

01:14:08.642 --> 01:14:09.642
This is enough to scare them!

01:14:11.515 --> 01:14:12.515
I did it!

01:14:13.453 --> 01:14:15.055
"I did my part as soon as I got here."

01:14:15.375 --> 01:14:16.609
That was what I was thinking.

01:14:17.751 --> 01:14:19.420
She totally did her part there.

01:14:19.445 --> 01:14:20.738
Great job.

01:14:20.788 --> 01:14:22.259
- It was so close.
- You're so cool!

01:14:22.259 --> 01:14:23.259
You did great.

01:14:25.276 --> 01:14:26.794
I was incredibly disappointed.

01:14:27.261 --> 01:14:30.201
(Hye In, of the Navy, lost.)

01:14:30.431 --> 01:14:32.099
I could've done better.

01:14:33.267 --> 01:14:34.902
- Sorry.
- It's okay.

01:14:35.099 --> 01:14:36.237
You don't need to be sorry.

01:14:36.870 --> 01:14:38.238
(Han Su Bin of the Army
against Park Hye In of the Navy)

01:14:38.296 --> 01:14:40.507
- The Army is going to the next round.
- The Army is going to the finals.

01:14:41.141 --> 01:14:42.141
The next race will be...

01:14:42.203 --> 01:14:43.277
The second race!

01:14:43.277 --> 01:14:45.296
(Which units will play
in the second race?)

01:14:45.813 --> 01:14:46.981
The second race is...

01:14:47.985 --> 01:14:49.683
- between the Marine Corps...
- The Marine Corps!

01:14:49.787 --> 01:14:51.385
- and the Special Forces.
- The Special Forces!

01:14:52.786 --> 01:14:55.089
Each team representative
will now step forward.

01:14:57.791 --> 01:14:59.159
Kim Ji Eun of the Special Forces.

01:14:59.159 --> 01:15:00.294
The team leader!

01:15:00.932 --> 01:15:02.062
(Which Marine Corps troop will go
against Ji Eun?)

01:15:02.062 --> 01:15:03.062
From the Marine Corps...

01:15:04.898 --> 01:15:05.898
What was with the laugh?

01:15:08.073 --> 01:15:08.996
The tallest one!

01:15:09.187 --> 01:15:10.070
Yoon Jae In!

01:15:10.070 --> 01:15:11.905
- That's...
- Jae In is ten centimeters taller.

01:15:12.339 --> 01:15:14.842
Master Sergeant Kim Ji Eun
of the Special Forces!

01:15:15.142 --> 01:15:16.410
I'll do as I always do.

01:15:17.076 --> 01:15:18.333
I've been climbing ropes...

01:15:18.357 --> 01:15:21.615
since I first joined the Special Forces
about 11 years ago.

01:15:21.642 --> 01:15:22.750
I'm not all that worried.

01:15:23.817 --> 01:15:25.786
Sergeant First Class Yoon Jae In
of the Marine Corps!

01:15:26.186 --> 01:15:28.756
I'll show you my real class
as it's the first round.

01:15:29.623 --> 01:15:32.660
I'm the type to always hate losing.

01:15:32.863 --> 01:15:36.196
I felt like I had to win in this race,
no matter what.

01:15:36.273 --> 01:15:38.766
The two troops' physical gap is quite big.

01:15:38.766 --> 01:15:40.667
Jae In is exactly ten centimeters
taller than Ji Eun.

01:15:40.891 --> 01:15:42.670
An 11m rope climbing race...

01:15:42.970 --> 01:15:45.272
between the Marine Corps
and the Special Forces...

01:15:45.839 --> 01:15:46.839
will now begin.

01:15:47.541 --> 01:15:48.541
Make the impossible...

01:15:48.679 --> 01:15:50.210
- Possible!
- Possible!

01:15:50.361 --> 01:15:52.546
- Let's go, the Special Forces!
- Bring it on!

01:15:53.547 --> 01:15:55.724
If it doesn't work...

01:15:55.749 --> 01:15:57.351
- Make it work!
- Make it work!

01:15:57.376 --> 01:15:58.228
Cheers!

01:15:58.253 --> 01:15:59.367
- You got this!
- The slogans!

01:15:59.906 --> 01:16:01.078
They sound so similar!

01:16:01.103 --> 01:16:03.490
"Make the impossible possible"
and "If it doesn't work, make it work."

01:16:03.490 --> 01:16:04.254
Let's go!

01:16:04.254 --> 01:16:05.812
- They're basically the same!
- Come on!

01:16:06.493 --> 01:16:07.384
Ready?

01:16:07.384 --> 01:16:08.737
(Which unit will win?)

01:16:08.762 --> 01:16:10.297
I wonder how they'll climb the ropes.

01:16:10.388 --> 01:16:14.338
(So nervous)

01:16:15.121 --> 01:16:16.121
(The race has begun.)

01:16:16.121 --> 01:16:17.171
It's begun!

01:16:17.321 --> 01:16:19.063
We have the Marine Corps on the right...

01:16:19.063 --> 01:16:20.374
- and the Special Forces on the left!
- Right on!

01:16:20.374 --> 01:16:21.809
- You got this!
- Ji Eun...

01:16:22.476 --> 01:16:24.611
- Nice!
- That's a great pace!

01:16:24.636 --> 01:16:25.879
You're so confident!

01:16:26.410 --> 01:16:27.999
(Meanwhile,)

01:16:28.265 --> 01:16:29.383
(Jae In of the Marine Corps wrapped
her foot around incorrectly.)

01:16:29.383 --> 01:16:30.484
Why?

01:16:30.484 --> 01:16:31.548
- What?
- That's a bit...

01:16:31.656 --> 01:16:32.656
Oh, no!

01:16:32.681 --> 01:16:34.488
- She wrapped the rope around wrongly.
- The Marine Corps!

01:16:34.775 --> 01:16:35.833
What's going on?

01:16:35.833 --> 01:16:36.907
- Just do what you always do.
- She made a mistake.

01:16:36.907 --> 01:16:37.844
Why didn't she do what she always does?

01:16:37.868 --> 01:16:38.868
What's going on?

01:16:39.857 --> 01:16:40.760
That's going to make it very difficult.

01:16:40.760 --> 01:16:42.426
- It's not going to work.
- She's using both of her feet.

01:16:42.451 --> 01:16:43.797
That's even harder.

01:16:43.917 --> 01:16:45.750
(Ji Eun, from the Special Forces,
is far ahead.)

01:16:45.750 --> 01:16:47.044
Ji Eun is so fast!

01:16:47.364 --> 01:16:49.369
- Ji Eun!
- She's clearly experienced.

01:16:49.960 --> 01:16:51.138
(Unstoppable)

01:16:51.138 --> 01:16:52.473
She's going up so quickly!

01:16:52.806 --> 01:16:54.575
Ji Eun is doing great.

01:16:54.975 --> 01:16:57.111
- She's incredibly fast.
- She's unbelievable!

01:16:57.111 --> 01:16:58.295
Master Sergeant Kim of the Special Forces!

01:16:59.163 --> 01:17:00.848
- She's like an elevator.
- I can't believe her speed.

01:17:01.258 --> 01:17:02.258
She's insane!

01:17:03.914 --> 01:17:04.914
How does she do that?

01:17:06.344 --> 01:17:10.591
Of course, someone
who climbs ropes daily is different.

01:17:10.854 --> 01:17:11.854
She's gone so far.

01:17:12.396 --> 01:17:13.396
- A Special Forces troop is different.
- Stay far in the lead!

01:17:13.421 --> 01:17:14.228
Nice!

01:17:14.228 --> 01:17:15.462
- That's so cool.
- Go farther up!

01:17:15.659 --> 01:17:17.431
Put your feet up higher!

01:17:17.431 --> 01:17:18.665
Keep your feet up even higher.

01:17:19.347 --> 01:17:22.333
- Make sure to place one foot on top well.
- Nice!

01:17:22.659 --> 01:17:23.781
Nice!

01:17:24.338 --> 01:17:25.572
Nice!

01:17:25.636 --> 01:17:27.151
The Marine Corps!

01:17:27.731 --> 01:17:28.879
Dong Hyun's Marine Corps!

01:17:28.879 --> 01:17:30.411
Our expectations for the unit are
definitely dropping!

01:17:30.436 --> 01:17:32.169
(So disappointed)

01:17:32.276 --> 01:17:33.147
Right on!

01:17:33.292 --> 01:17:34.511
(Ji Eun easily won.)

01:17:34.511 --> 01:17:35.413
She definitely won.

01:17:35.413 --> 01:17:36.550
Right on!

01:17:36.820 --> 01:17:38.185
Use your feet to come down slowly.

01:17:38.819 --> 01:17:40.754
- Marine Corps!
- That's the Special Forces for you!

01:17:41.519 --> 01:17:42.519
Nice.

01:17:42.689 --> 01:17:43.987
She looks so stable, even on her way down.

01:17:44.855 --> 01:17:45.855
That's the Special Forces for you.

01:17:46.226 --> 01:17:47.226
(Screaming)

01:17:47.718 --> 01:17:48.906
(Startled)

01:17:49.460 --> 01:17:51.465
The Special Forces unit was way ahead
and won so easily.

01:17:51.465 --> 01:17:53.367
- She was so fast!
- She's unbelievable.

01:17:53.767 --> 01:17:55.035
Nice!

01:17:55.060 --> 01:17:56.690
(The Special Forces unit beat
the Marine Corps unit so easily.)

01:17:57.104 --> 01:17:58.305
We definitely intimidated them.

01:17:58.462 --> 01:17:59.573
I felt so proud,

01:18:00.174 --> 01:18:01.678
even though it was just the first round
that I won.

01:18:02.826 --> 01:18:04.111
You're so strong.

01:18:05.145 --> 01:18:06.246
- Nice!
- Breathe.

01:18:06.456 --> 01:18:08.706
- You can take the gloves off now.
- Yes, take them off.

01:18:08.893 --> 01:18:10.401
(Meanwhile, the Marine Corps unit is
looking very serious.)

01:18:10.401 --> 01:18:12.019
The Marine Corps unit isn't so happy.

01:18:12.920 --> 01:18:14.555
The Marine Corps!

01:18:15.622 --> 01:18:16.757
- Stay strong!
- Jae In!

01:18:16.782 --> 01:18:18.895
Oh, goodness.

01:18:19.732 --> 01:18:20.732
This is disappointing.

01:18:21.828 --> 01:18:23.197
Why did she try to switch her foot?

01:18:24.965 --> 01:18:27.534
I couldn't wrap the rope around my foot,

01:18:27.834 --> 01:18:29.002
which threw me off.

01:18:29.636 --> 01:18:31.171
And that slowed me down more and more.

01:18:31.939 --> 01:18:34.040
- I'm really sorry.
- It's okay.

01:18:34.298 --> 01:18:35.298
Good work.

01:18:36.153 --> 01:18:37.578
I know that you're disappointed,
but it's okay.

01:18:37.655 --> 01:18:39.823
I couldn't even climb all the way up.

01:18:40.914 --> 01:18:43.817
Ji Eun of the Special Forces is
now a finalist.

01:18:44.051 --> 01:18:45.219
The Marine Corps!

01:18:45.552 --> 01:18:47.391
The last race of Round One is...

01:18:47.391 --> 01:18:49.356
between the Special Mission Battalion
and the 707th Group.

01:18:49.546 --> 01:18:50.546
The Special Mission Battalion!

01:18:50.838 --> 01:18:52.125
This race...

01:18:52.176 --> 01:18:54.428
is one to watch out for.
We can't predict a winner.

01:18:54.428 --> 01:18:56.630
Each team representative
may now step forward.

01:18:57.067 --> 01:18:59.566
(The representative
of the ROK 707th Special Missions Group)

01:18:59.566 --> 01:19:01.702
Lee Hyeon Seon
of the ROK 707th Special Missions Group!

01:19:01.727 --> 01:19:02.903
Hyeon Seon.

01:19:03.634 --> 01:19:07.891
(Everyone's looking at the one going
against the 707th Group.)

01:19:10.027 --> 01:19:11.712
(Sergeant First Class Cho Seong Won)

01:19:11.844 --> 01:19:12.844
The Tarantula Unit!

01:19:12.869 --> 01:19:14.331
Here comes the Tarantula Unit!

01:19:14.331 --> 01:19:15.292
- From the first game!
- The Tarantula Unit!

01:19:15.292 --> 01:19:16.617
Seong Won will represent
the Special Mission Battalion.

01:19:17.584 --> 01:19:18.528
Her eyes...

01:19:18.528 --> 01:19:19.990
They're already playing the Joker card!

01:19:19.990 --> 01:19:21.291
This won't be easy.

01:19:22.222 --> 01:19:23.222
She seems so strong.

01:19:24.628 --> 01:19:26.393
I have no idea who's going to win.

01:19:26.393 --> 01:19:29.062
I feel like the 707th Group will do well,
just as the Special Forces did.

01:19:29.663 --> 01:19:31.532
Sergeant First Class Lee Hyeon Seon
of the ROK 707th Special Missions Group!

01:19:31.932 --> 01:19:33.050
I will represent logic with action...

01:19:33.050 --> 01:19:35.669
and prove the process with results.

01:19:37.096 --> 01:19:38.639
Sergeant First Class Cho Seong Won
of the Special Mission Battalion.

01:19:38.822 --> 01:19:40.274
I'll show you what a savage is!

01:19:40.774 --> 01:19:41.774
The 707th Group!

01:19:41.799 --> 01:19:43.844
I was ready to beat them
in the first mission.

01:19:44.411 --> 01:19:45.546
I had to intimidate them.

01:19:46.413 --> 01:19:47.914
The last race of Round One,

01:19:47.914 --> 01:19:48.744
Lee Hyeon Seon of the 707th Group...

01:19:48.768 --> 01:19:49.983
against Cho Seong Won
of the Special Mission Battalion.

01:19:50.584 --> 01:19:51.584
Ready?

01:19:51.864 --> 01:19:52.864
My goodness.

01:19:53.277 --> 01:19:55.522
With the fellow troops' support...

01:19:56.262 --> 01:19:57.457
Let's go, 707th Group!

01:19:57.724 --> 01:19:59.326
You got this, 707th Group!

01:19:59.693 --> 01:20:01.461
Let's go, Special Mission Battalion!

01:20:01.654 --> 01:20:03.429
They're both going to be so good.

01:20:03.429 --> 01:20:04.930
(The race has begun.)

01:20:04.955 --> 01:20:06.799
On the left is Seong Won
of the Tarantula Unit.

01:20:06.799 --> 01:20:08.734
And on the right,
we have Hyeon Seon of the 707th Group.

01:20:08.734 --> 01:20:09.734
Oh, gosh.

01:20:09.734 --> 01:20:11.203
She slipped!

01:20:12.711 --> 01:20:14.503
Hyeon Seon!

01:20:14.503 --> 01:20:15.239
She slipped.

01:20:15.239 --> 01:20:16.609
You're so fast!

01:20:17.043 --> 01:20:18.043
Oh, gosh.

01:20:18.311 --> 01:20:20.179
I missed the rope...

01:20:20.446 --> 01:20:22.048
when I tried to wrap my foot around it
the second time.

01:20:22.171 --> 01:20:24.483
I wasted some time there.

01:20:24.483 --> 01:20:26.352
- It's okay.
- Take your time!

01:20:26.352 --> 01:20:28.421
Hyeon Seon made a mistake at the start.

01:20:28.446 --> 01:20:29.896
Here goes Seong Won of the Tarantula Unit.

01:20:29.904 --> 01:20:30.419
Seong Won.

01:20:30.913 --> 01:20:32.541
- She's so stable.
- She looks so calm.

01:20:32.541 --> 01:20:34.093
- You got this!
- You're doing great!

01:20:36.446 --> 01:20:37.981
(Hyeon Seon is making up for her slip
by working her arms harder.)

01:20:37.981 --> 01:20:39.161
Her arm strength is...

01:20:39.161 --> 01:20:40.161
Her arms are helping her catch up.

01:20:40.810 --> 01:20:41.810
(Neck to neck)

01:20:41.835 --> 01:20:43.135
They're neck to neck!

01:20:43.135 --> 01:20:44.500
Hyeon Seon is also doing well!

01:20:45.504 --> 01:20:46.629
- They're both good!
- It's a tie!

01:20:46.629 --> 01:20:47.973
- They're tied!
- It's neck to neck!

01:20:48.471 --> 01:20:50.242
What an intense race!

01:20:50.543 --> 01:20:52.645
You need to speed up!

01:20:52.895 --> 01:20:54.246
- Seong Won!
- You need to speed up!

01:20:54.914 --> 01:20:56.292
- Hyeon Seon!
- Come on!

01:20:56.545 --> 01:20:57.783
Faster!

01:20:58.443 --> 01:21:00.312
- They're both so good!
- Hyeon Seon is so good!

01:21:00.312 --> 01:21:01.854
- You need to speed up!
- They're neck to neck!

01:21:02.679 --> 01:21:04.123
Seong Won takes over!

01:21:04.123 --> 01:21:05.291
Faster!

01:21:06.208 --> 01:21:07.396
Come on!

01:21:07.396 --> 01:21:09.729
- It's neck to neck! You can win!
- Come on!

01:21:10.363 --> 01:21:12.531
Hyeon Seon is speeding up again!

01:21:13.466 --> 01:21:15.201
You got this!

01:21:15.404 --> 01:21:16.969
You're almost there!

01:21:18.421 --> 01:21:19.896
Seong Won is just slightly faster!

01:21:19.896 --> 01:21:21.050
- The gap is minimal!
- They're neck to neck.

01:21:21.050 --> 01:21:22.274
- You're so close!
- The last push!

01:21:22.952 --> 01:21:24.844
- One more push!
- One more time!

01:21:24.844 --> 01:21:26.876
- Please!
- You're almost there!

01:21:28.070 --> 01:21:29.181
You're almost done.

01:21:30.573 --> 01:21:32.051
(But her hand has slipped
off of the bell.)

01:21:32.076 --> 01:21:32.985
Her hand slipped!

01:21:33.089 --> 01:21:33.953
- Her hand slipped!
- It slipped?

01:21:33.953 --> 01:21:34.677
- No!
- It slipped!

01:21:34.677 --> 01:21:35.677
She was too rushed!

01:21:35.702 --> 01:21:36.799
She needs to ring the bell to win.

01:21:38.508 --> 01:21:39.892
One more time!

01:21:39.892 --> 01:21:41.123
One more time!

01:21:41.123 --> 01:21:42.294
It's not too late!

01:21:42.695 --> 01:21:44.053
Hyeon Seon, one last push!

01:21:44.053 --> 01:21:45.564
Let's go, 707th Group!

01:21:46.769 --> 01:21:47.900
- Who's going to win?
- Please!

01:21:47.900 --> 01:21:49.101
Hyeon Seon is going for the bell!

01:21:49.126 --> 01:21:51.203
(Who's going to win?)

01:21:51.228 --> 01:21:52.438
Who's the winner?

01:21:52.438 --> 01:21:53.863
(Nervous)

01:21:53.863 --> 01:21:54.863
- Who's the winner?
- The winner is...

01:21:56.438 --> 01:21:57.974
(Seong Won,
of the Special Mission Battalion, wins.)

01:21:58.100 --> 01:21:59.295
(Seong Won beat Hyeon Seon by a hair.)

01:21:59.295 --> 01:22:00.479
They were neck to neck!

01:22:00.623 --> 01:22:02.281
The Special Mission Battalion!

01:22:02.281 --> 01:22:04.000
She just hit the bell with her fist.

01:22:04.000 --> 01:22:05.661
(Cheering)

01:22:05.661 --> 01:22:06.752
Be careful!

01:22:06.752 --> 01:22:07.887
The Special Mission Battalion is good
at climbing ropes too.

01:22:08.621 --> 01:22:10.556
That's Seong Won for you.

01:22:10.990 --> 01:22:12.892
Not only is she big,
but she's also amazing at climbing ropes.

01:22:13.272 --> 01:22:14.611
She's not an easy opponent.

01:22:16.395 --> 01:22:19.532
I felt threatened
because Hyeon Seon was so fast,

01:22:19.965 --> 01:22:23.536
but my teammates cheered me on
to climb just a bit farther up,

01:22:23.826 --> 01:22:25.237
which led me to my victory.

01:22:25.838 --> 01:22:27.239
That's the Tarantula Unit for you.

01:22:27.873 --> 01:22:29.842
Hyeon Seon is good enough
to be in the finals too.

01:22:29.867 --> 01:22:30.619
I know.

01:22:30.910 --> 01:22:32.511
But her opponent in Round One was
way too good.

01:22:33.863 --> 01:22:37.049
(Lee Hyeon Seon, of the 707th Group,
lost by a hair.)

01:22:37.074 --> 01:22:39.151
I didn't expect myself to lose at all.

01:22:39.455 --> 01:22:41.043
(Cho Seong Won
of the Special Mission Battalion wins.)

01:22:41.043 --> 01:22:42.388
Seong Won won.

01:22:44.423 --> 01:22:46.792
The 11m climbing race
with a huge benefit for the next mission,

01:22:46.846 --> 01:22:47.660
Benefit!

01:22:47.660 --> 01:22:49.061
a chance to choose your own opponent,

01:22:49.528 --> 01:22:51.297
on the line.

01:22:51.297 --> 01:22:52.531
This is a huge benefit!

01:22:52.531 --> 01:22:54.423
We'll now begin Round Two.

01:22:54.423 --> 01:22:56.235
This is the final round.

01:22:56.235 --> 01:22:58.537
- I can't tell who's going to win.
- Seriously!

01:22:59.338 --> 01:23:01.841
Ji Eun was way too fast.

01:23:02.879 --> 01:23:04.610
Only three players remain.

01:23:04.834 --> 01:23:06.143
Seong Won
of the Special Mission Battalion,

01:23:06.143 --> 01:23:07.143
Ji Eun of the Special Forces,

01:23:07.168 --> 01:23:08.347
and Su Bin of the Army.

01:23:08.714 --> 01:23:10.916
The three units will go
against each other simultaneously.

01:23:10.942 --> 01:23:13.018
It's the Special Mission Battalion,
the Special Forces, and the Army.

01:23:13.953 --> 01:23:14.953
Ready?

01:23:14.978 --> 01:23:17.166
(Ready for the race)

01:23:17.233 --> 01:23:18.624
Special Forces!

01:23:18.624 --> 01:23:19.959
Kim Ji Eun!

01:23:19.959 --> 01:23:21.394
- You got this!
- You got this!

01:23:21.861 --> 01:23:23.225
Special Mission Battalion!

01:23:23.225 --> 01:23:24.830
The Tarantula Unit!

01:23:24.830 --> 01:23:25.721
Let's go!

01:23:25.721 --> 01:23:27.059
Han Su Bin of the Army! Let's go!

01:23:27.059 --> 01:23:28.234
- Come on!
- Come on!

01:23:30.041 --> 01:23:31.303
- Who will win?
- The race has begun!

01:23:31.303 --> 01:23:32.638
The final round, Round Two!

01:23:32.638 --> 01:23:34.006
Yes, they're starting together!

01:23:34.984 --> 01:23:36.742
The Tarantula Unit is on the left.

01:23:36.767 --> 01:23:37.910
The Army is in the middle.

01:23:38.094 --> 01:23:39.345
The Special Forces unit is on the right!

01:23:39.370 --> 01:23:40.530
(Which unit will win in the race?)

01:23:40.963 --> 01:23:43.519
- It's neck to neck!
- I can't tell who's going to win!

01:23:43.519 --> 01:23:44.519
They're going at about the same speed.

01:23:44.544 --> 01:23:45.851
They're incredibly fast.

01:23:47.221 --> 01:23:49.054
Ji Eun of the Special Forces
is speeding up!

01:23:49.054 --> 01:23:50.689
She's unbelievably fast!

01:23:50.689 --> 01:23:52.057
Put your legs farther up!

01:23:53.559 --> 01:23:54.559
Seong Won!

01:23:54.584 --> 01:23:56.005
(Seong Won is stretching her legs
to make each pull bigger.)

01:23:56.005 --> 01:23:57.840
- Faster!
- Go faster!

01:23:57.840 --> 01:23:59.064
You have to go faster!

01:23:59.064 --> 01:24:00.342
Look up as you go!

01:24:01.194 --> 01:24:03.502
Ji Eun, of the Special Forces unit,
is the fastest!

01:24:03.502 --> 01:24:04.904
I can't believe how fast she is!

01:24:04.929 --> 01:24:06.846
Ji Eun is going right up!

01:24:06.846 --> 01:24:08.941
- She's unbelievably fast.
- How can she go so fast?

01:24:09.434 --> 01:24:11.076
That's the Special Forces unit for you.

01:24:11.214 --> 01:24:12.344
One more time!

01:24:12.344 --> 01:24:13.909
Don't stop until the end!

01:24:13.909 --> 01:24:14.909
Your feet!

01:24:14.909 --> 01:24:16.749
- Watch your feet!
- Seong Won is catching up!

01:24:16.774 --> 01:24:18.317
(Seong Won is catching up to Ji Eun.)

01:24:19.952 --> 01:24:21.497
- You got this!
- You're too slow!

01:24:21.497 --> 01:24:22.945
- You're slowing down.
- Just a little more!

01:24:23.405 --> 01:24:24.590
Ji Eun of the Special Forces!

01:24:24.590 --> 01:24:25.558
She's incredibly fast!

01:24:25.558 --> 01:24:26.892
And Seong Won is in second place.

01:24:27.393 --> 01:24:28.765
Seong Won is catching up!

01:24:28.790 --> 01:24:29.790
(Seong Won is going crazy now.)

01:24:30.229 --> 01:24:31.229
She's in a rush!

01:24:31.394 --> 01:24:32.394
She's rushing!

01:24:33.262 --> 01:24:35.334
I could see Seong Won climbing up.

01:24:36.135 --> 01:24:37.870
I realized that I couldn't slow down.

01:24:38.804 --> 01:24:40.940
I felt like I could catch up to her.

01:24:41.272 --> 01:24:42.708
- The last round!
- Good luck!

01:24:42.708 --> 01:24:44.253
(Seong Won and Ji Eun are
fighting for the top two spots.)

01:24:44.278 --> 01:24:45.311
Seong Won is catching up!

01:24:45.710 --> 01:24:47.580
Ji Eun?

01:24:47.580 --> 01:24:48.681
Or Seong Won?

01:24:49.448 --> 01:24:51.027
- Stay relaxed until the end!
- One more push!

01:24:51.027 --> 01:24:52.027
Push one more time!

01:24:52.484 --> 01:24:53.484
She's threatened!

01:24:54.706 --> 01:24:56.655
- Seong Won's reach is so long.
- Yes.

01:24:56.680 --> 01:24:58.007
(Who will win?)

01:24:58.032 --> 01:24:58.857
Gosh!

01:24:59.689 --> 01:25:01.103
- Keep going until the end!
- One more!

01:25:01.117 --> 01:25:01.728
You got this!

01:25:01.753 --> 01:25:03.355
Use your feet!

01:25:04.013 --> 01:25:04.763
(Who will be the winner
of the rope climbing race?)

01:25:04.763 --> 01:25:06.465
Who will be the final winner?

01:25:07.396 --> 01:25:09.234
Will it be Ji Eun?
She's reaching for the bell!

01:25:10.019 --> 01:25:11.770
Come on!

01:25:12.001 --> 01:25:14.106
Will it be Ji Eun or Seong Won?

01:25:15.941 --> 01:25:17.286
Ji Eun rang the bell first.

01:25:17.286 --> 01:25:18.544
The Special Forces unit wins.

01:25:18.975 --> 01:25:19.975
They're all so strong.

01:25:20.136 --> 01:25:21.313
Seong Won was just a hair behind.

01:25:21.730 --> 01:25:23.282
Great work!

01:25:23.307 --> 01:25:24.307
Nice!

01:25:25.250 --> 01:25:28.120
The secret to my victory was
my stamina and confidence.

01:25:28.120 --> 01:25:30.089
I was very satisfied with the result.

01:25:30.689 --> 01:25:31.689
Make the impossible...

01:25:31.714 --> 01:25:33.182
- Possible!
- Possible!

01:25:33.182 --> 01:25:34.400
(A victorious cry)

01:25:36.555 --> 01:25:37.800
(Startled)

01:25:37.800 --> 01:25:39.431
She almost tore my eardrums.

01:25:39.865 --> 01:25:42.224
Sorry, but she almost tore my eardrums!

01:25:42.601 --> 01:25:44.460
- My ears are bleeding.
- She's incredible.

01:25:44.861 --> 01:25:46.005
(So proud)

01:25:46.538 --> 01:25:47.538
She's like an elk.

01:25:48.004 --> 01:25:49.708
(Deafening)

01:25:50.462 --> 01:25:51.507
- Seong Won is second.
- Nice!

01:25:51.507 --> 01:25:52.895
- Great job!
- The Special Mission Battalion is second.

01:25:52.895 --> 01:25:53.979
Be careful on your way down.

01:25:53.979 --> 01:25:55.114
I was so close to winning.

01:25:55.371 --> 01:25:56.252
It was so close.

01:25:56.252 --> 01:25:57.633
She did so well!

01:25:57.633 --> 01:25:59.598
(It was so close.)

01:25:59.885 --> 01:26:00.858
You're almost there!

01:26:00.882 --> 01:26:02.201
The last one is Su Bin of the ROK Army.

01:26:02.226 --> 01:26:03.722
Come down slowly.

01:26:04.306 --> 01:26:05.767
Ji Eun, of the Special Forces unit,
wins first place.

01:26:05.791 --> 01:26:07.026
Seong Won,
of the Tarantula Unit, is second.

01:26:07.026 --> 01:26:08.560
And Su Bin of the ROK Army is third.

01:26:08.585 --> 01:26:09.528
That's incredible.

01:26:09.828 --> 01:26:11.597
You heard Ji Eun's scream, right?

01:26:11.597 --> 01:26:12.164
- Yes.
- Indeed.

01:26:12.164 --> 01:26:13.966
- I thought that was an elk crying.
- Me too!

01:26:13.966 --> 01:26:18.037
The Special Forces unit
kept mocking the others,

01:26:18.120 --> 01:26:20.339
so I wasn't expecting its soldiers
to be all that good.

01:26:20.522 --> 01:26:23.931
But Ji Eun is so savage!

01:26:24.153 --> 01:26:25.811
Her savage spirit is a trained one...

01:26:26.311 --> 01:26:27.487
from 11 years of serving in the military.

01:26:27.487 --> 01:26:29.585
Are you saying that you'll root
for the Special Forces unit...

01:26:29.609 --> 01:26:30.549
and not the Marine Corps?

01:26:30.549 --> 01:26:31.784
Have you changed your favorite unit?

01:26:31.881 --> 01:26:32.881
For now...

01:26:33.522 --> 01:26:35.154
Let me trust the Marine Corps
one more time.

01:26:35.154 --> 01:26:36.655
Let me give the Marine Corps
another chance.

01:26:37.961 --> 01:26:39.892
How the Special Forces unit...

01:26:40.218 --> 01:26:42.661
uses the chance to choose
its opponents is...

01:26:42.661 --> 01:26:44.963
something to look out for.

01:26:44.963 --> 01:26:46.365
That's a huge benefit.

01:26:47.018 --> 01:26:49.601
First of all, the unit that gets picked...

01:26:50.002 --> 01:26:52.071
- is bound to feel insulted.
- Yes, that can't be helped.

01:26:52.071 --> 01:26:53.071
They can't help but feel insulted.

01:26:53.096 --> 01:26:55.040
- It'll hurt their pride.
- It'll definitely hurt their pride.

01:26:55.506 --> 01:26:56.375
That's right.

01:26:56.375 --> 01:26:57.375
(The chance to pick their opponents can be
really insulting to the chosen opponents.)

01:26:57.967 --> 01:26:59.545
(It's nighttime at the base now.)

01:26:59.545 --> 01:27:00.589
- The sun has set.
- It's nighttime.

01:27:00.589 --> 01:27:01.589
My goodness.

01:27:03.269 --> 01:27:06.542
(The troops of "The Iron Squad W"
are gathering around.)

01:27:07.286 --> 01:27:08.377
(What awaits the troops...)

01:27:08.377 --> 01:27:12.495
(in this pitch darkness?)

01:27:14.150 --> 01:27:17.790
(A giant trench)

01:27:17.986 --> 01:27:19.068
- At night?
- In the trench?

01:27:19.068 --> 01:27:19.798
Right on!

01:27:19.798 --> 01:27:21.366
A female trench fight...

01:27:22.278 --> 01:27:25.121
(The Special Forces Unit)

01:27:25.321 --> 01:27:28.074
(The Special Mission Battalion)

01:27:28.374 --> 01:27:31.143
(The ROK Army Unit)

01:27:31.343 --> 01:27:34.146
(The ROK Navy Unit)

01:27:34.346 --> 01:27:37.093
(The ROK 707th Special Missions Group)

01:27:37.400 --> 01:27:40.092
(The ROK Marine Corps Unit)

01:27:40.596 --> 01:27:43.011
A team-based survival game
in search of the strongest female troops,

01:27:43.011 --> 01:27:44.011
"The Iron Squad W."

01:27:45.791 --> 01:27:46.791
The next mission is...

01:27:48.680 --> 01:27:49.680
trench fighting.

01:27:50.268 --> 01:27:51.196
Trench fighting.

01:27:51.196 --> 01:27:52.464
It's trench fighting!

01:27:52.555 --> 01:27:54.066
It's time, at last.

01:27:54.967 --> 01:27:56.335
This is my expertise.

01:27:57.061 --> 01:27:58.303
There was no way that I was going to lose.

01:27:58.303 --> 01:27:59.101
Really?

01:27:59.101 --> 01:28:00.015
- That's so...
- Right on!

01:28:00.015 --> 01:28:01.577
- She's wearing something on her head!
- Yes!

01:28:01.577 --> 01:28:04.573
- Right on!
- Everyone's here to watch you, Su Yeon!

01:28:04.573 --> 01:28:06.102
Yes, we bought the tickets
to come to this fight!

01:28:06.127 --> 01:28:07.127
Exactly!

01:28:07.206 --> 01:28:10.686
(The trench fighting has gotten
an upgrade.)

01:28:10.842 --> 01:28:12.103
That's a huge trench.

01:28:12.718 --> 01:28:13.976
It's deeper too.

01:28:14.089 --> 01:28:15.271
(It's deeper and wider.)

01:28:18.056 --> 01:28:20.092
This is the biggest trench
of all the ones we've had on the show.

01:28:20.092 --> 01:28:21.391
Is this a group fight?

01:28:21.391 --> 01:28:22.391
- Maybe.
- What will it be?

01:28:23.095 --> 01:28:24.095
Why is it so big?

01:28:24.262 --> 01:28:25.664
It's so big and deep.

01:28:26.331 --> 01:28:27.766
It's a lot wider than I expected.

01:28:27.766 --> 01:28:28.834
Everyone's astounded.

01:28:28.834 --> 01:28:30.469
We're going to end up
using all of our energy here.

01:28:31.503 --> 01:28:33.328
The bigger the trench,
the more tiring it will be.

01:28:33.328 --> 01:28:34.494
- It'll be an exhausting fight.
- Indeed.

01:28:34.519 --> 01:28:35.958
You don't just end the fight
in the trench.

01:28:35.958 --> 01:28:37.743
You have to push your opponent out,
after all.

01:28:39.050 --> 01:28:40.285
The first round...

01:28:41.613 --> 01:28:44.012
will be a 2-on-2 trench fight.

01:28:44.519 --> 01:28:46.084
- A 2-on-2 fight?
- A 2-on-2 fight!

01:28:46.796 --> 01:28:47.896
(A 2-on-2 Trench Fight)

01:28:47.896 --> 01:28:49.188
A 2-on-2 trench fight!

01:28:50.092 --> 01:28:51.790
Two troops from each unit will play.

01:28:52.558 --> 01:28:54.860
You'll play 2 rounds of this 2-on-2 fight.

01:28:55.561 --> 01:28:57.129
Two units will go against one another,

01:28:57.353 --> 01:29:01.200
and the winning unit
will advance to the final round.

01:29:02.301 --> 01:29:04.480
All four troops of a unit must play.

01:29:04.480 --> 01:29:05.320
That's right.

01:29:05.320 --> 01:29:07.539
The units will play 2-on-2 fights
in Round 1,

01:29:07.703 --> 01:29:10.475
and the unit that wins both times
will advance to the final round.

01:29:11.383 --> 01:29:12.778
After two fights,

01:29:13.055 --> 01:29:14.379
if the two units end in a tie,

01:29:14.922 --> 01:29:18.325
the representatives from each unit
will play a 1-on-1 fight.

01:29:18.350 --> 01:29:19.818
- A 1-on-1 fight?
- They'll play 1-on-1?

01:29:20.552 --> 01:29:23.922
The three surviving units
will advance to the finals.

01:29:24.867 --> 01:29:27.526
- It'll be key not to end up in a tie.
- For sure.

01:29:27.526 --> 01:29:29.361
- That'll be too draining.
- It'll leave them exhausted.

01:29:29.386 --> 01:29:30.786
(They must play an additional game
in the case of a tie.)

01:29:31.102 --> 01:29:32.831
Round One of trench fighting.

01:29:33.632 --> 01:29:35.534
We will now decide
which unit will play against which.

01:29:35.704 --> 01:29:36.969
Which unit goes against which
will determine everything.

01:29:36.969 --> 01:29:39.071
The Special Forces unit,
which has won first place...

01:29:39.141 --> 01:29:40.806
in the 11m climbing race,

01:29:40.831 --> 01:29:43.108
will get to choose
its opponent team first.

01:29:43.108 --> 01:29:44.108
The Special Forces!

01:29:44.643 --> 01:29:46.612
Kim Ji Eun of the Special Forces,

01:29:47.579 --> 01:29:50.388
please choose the unit to go against.

01:29:51.016 --> 01:29:52.814
Will she choose the unit
that we're expecting her to choose?

01:29:55.482 --> 01:29:56.959
- She looked at the Navy!
- The Navy?

01:29:56.959 --> 01:29:57.959
Cho Hui?

01:29:58.423 --> 01:29:59.825
It looks like we're going to end up
going first.

01:29:59.923 --> 01:30:02.464
- The Navy.
- She has a feeling.

01:30:02.489 --> 01:30:04.709
Why? Do they look at us?

01:30:04.991 --> 01:30:06.702
I think the Special Forces will choose us.

01:30:07.013 --> 01:30:08.288
- I have a feeling.
- You do?

01:30:08.288 --> 01:30:10.256
- They need to get prepared.
- Oh, gosh.

01:30:11.040 --> 01:30:12.241
They had a meeting.

01:30:12.708 --> 01:30:16.595
The Navy's soldiers have
relatively smaller builds...

01:30:16.620 --> 01:30:19.048
and shorter heights.

01:30:19.382 --> 01:30:20.382
That's why...

01:30:20.407 --> 01:30:22.852
Right. The Navy soldiers are lighter.

01:30:22.852 --> 01:30:25.552
The physique does matter
when they do trench fighting.

01:30:25.552 --> 01:30:26.552
Right.

01:30:27.033 --> 01:30:29.425
I think it'll require less stamina.

01:30:30.470 --> 01:30:34.096
I think the Navy is an easy match.

01:30:34.363 --> 01:30:37.466
Personally, I think
we should choose the Army.

01:30:37.466 --> 01:30:40.466
- The Army and Navy.
- It's not like there's a well-built one,

01:30:40.466 --> 01:30:42.071
so I'll go for the Army.

01:30:42.772 --> 01:30:46.175
We narrowed it down to two units.

01:30:46.655 --> 01:30:49.812
I think it's better to save energy
in the beginning.

01:30:50.299 --> 01:30:52.949
- Strategically.
- Yes, so let's choose one of the two.

01:30:53.482 --> 01:30:55.985
Please choose the unit to go against.

01:30:55.985 --> 01:30:58.054
Will they choose
between the Army and the Navy?

01:30:58.184 --> 01:30:59.011
She's looking at someone.

01:30:59.011 --> 01:31:00.256
We, the Special Forces...

01:31:01.307 --> 01:31:02.550
(The Navy?)

01:31:02.575 --> 01:31:04.397
Which team will they choose?

01:31:04.397 --> 01:31:05.397
(The Army?)

01:31:07.967 --> 01:31:09.231
We, the Special Forces,

01:31:10.289 --> 01:31:11.534
will fight against the Navy.

01:31:11.534 --> 01:31:13.102
- The Navy.
- We will fight against the Navy.

01:31:13.102 --> 01:31:14.575
So, Cho Hui was right.

01:31:14.600 --> 01:31:15.838
- They made a hard-nosed choice.
- Right.

01:31:15.975 --> 01:31:18.241
What's the reason you chose the Navy?

01:31:18.674 --> 01:31:20.376
Strategically,

01:31:20.643 --> 01:31:24.914
we decided to save energy
as much as possible.

01:31:25.374 --> 01:31:28.417
She just hurt the Navy's pride.

01:31:28.508 --> 01:31:30.790
- She said that too openly.
- She didn't even hide it.

01:31:30.790 --> 01:31:33.656
Why are they trying to make
each other have a psychological war?

01:31:34.857 --> 01:31:35.992
Save up energy?

01:31:36.178 --> 01:31:39.261
To be honest, I didn't feel good.

01:31:40.549 --> 01:31:42.865
We decided not to use too much energy
from the beginning.

01:31:43.599 --> 01:31:45.735
We'll prove that you were wrong.

01:31:47.267 --> 01:31:51.107
They think they can beat us undoubtedly,

01:31:51.544 --> 01:31:52.719
and it made me sneer.

01:31:52.719 --> 01:31:54.608
- It's Angry Cho Hui.
- Angry Cho Hui!

01:31:54.633 --> 01:31:57.279
The next is the Special Mission Battalion,
which won second place...

01:31:57.813 --> 01:31:58.748
in the climbing 11m rope,

01:31:59.181 --> 01:31:59.970
Cho Seong Won.

01:31:59.994 --> 01:32:01.467
It's the Special Mission Battalion's turn
to choose an opponent.

01:32:01.492 --> 01:32:03.919
We will fight against the Army.

01:32:04.453 --> 01:32:06.058
It's really sad!

01:32:06.058 --> 01:32:07.923
The Army was placed third.

01:32:08.624 --> 01:32:09.725
Too bad.

01:32:10.716 --> 01:32:12.228
We will fight against the Army.

01:32:12.281 --> 01:32:13.874
(Snorting)

01:32:14.497 --> 01:32:17.533
We're the few selected from general units.

01:32:17.769 --> 01:32:20.820
("General unit" was mentioned again.)

01:32:21.162 --> 01:32:23.131
We'll show you how special we are.

01:32:24.007 --> 01:32:27.109
- They all speak so bluntly.
- It's scary.

01:32:28.366 --> 01:32:30.199
(It's no joke.)

01:32:31.944 --> 01:32:34.183
We'll show you
that they're not so special.

01:32:34.208 --> 01:32:35.618
How cool.

01:32:36.252 --> 01:32:39.121
Honestly,
it didn't feel nice to hear that.

01:32:39.622 --> 01:32:41.390
They said they were selected...

01:32:41.494 --> 01:32:44.126
from general units
because they were special.

01:32:44.499 --> 01:32:47.903
I wanted to show them
how more special general units can be.

01:32:47.928 --> 01:32:49.098
Right.

01:32:49.388 --> 01:32:50.750
Automatically,

01:32:50.750 --> 01:32:54.203
the 707th Group and the Marines will
compete against each other.

01:32:54.537 --> 01:32:57.773
People say the Marines are strong,

01:32:57.823 --> 01:33:01.444
but we'll show you
how overwhelmingly we can outdo them.

01:33:02.178 --> 01:33:04.380
But the Marines have Lee Su Yeon.

01:33:05.514 --> 01:33:09.785
We even think trench fighting is
for the Marines.

01:33:09.969 --> 01:33:12.321
We can beat any unit.

01:33:13.456 --> 01:33:16.659
So, it's a general unit
against special forces.

01:33:16.659 --> 01:33:17.827
- Right.
- It happened to be like that.

01:33:17.852 --> 01:33:18.861
(The 2-on-2 trench fighting:
The Marines vs. the 707th Group)

01:33:18.885 --> 01:33:19.862
(The Army
vs. the Special Mission Battalion)

01:33:19.886 --> 01:33:20.796
(The Navy vs. the Special Forces)

01:33:21.530 --> 01:33:23.165
Before we start trench fighting,

01:33:24.296 --> 01:33:27.369
I'll announce a great benefit.

01:33:27.394 --> 01:33:28.904
A great benefit?

01:33:29.175 --> 01:33:32.808
The winner of the trench fighting will...

01:33:33.576 --> 01:33:34.844
get a total of two benefits.

01:33:36.512 --> 01:33:37.646
- What?
- Two?

01:33:37.646 --> 01:33:38.606
- Two from the beginning?
- He gives out...

01:33:38.630 --> 01:33:40.483
too many benefits.

01:33:41.841 --> 01:33:43.486
(Tempting)

01:33:43.658 --> 01:33:46.212
There are two benefits?
That's very tempting.

01:33:46.212 --> 01:33:48.724
It really is. We must take first place
this time.

01:33:48.724 --> 01:33:50.292
We should give our all.

01:33:51.193 --> 01:33:52.561
We must win, no matter what.

01:33:54.430 --> 01:33:55.998
The first benefit is...

01:33:56.442 --> 01:33:58.868
the right to choose the opponent
of the first main mission,

01:33:59.768 --> 01:34:01.303
where the first team to be eliminated
will be decided.

01:34:03.606 --> 01:34:04.597
It's very important.

01:34:04.597 --> 01:34:06.475
The right to choose the opponent
for the first main mission.

01:34:07.276 --> 01:34:08.276
It's good.

01:34:09.435 --> 01:34:11.714
As soon as the first benefit
was mentioned,

01:34:11.714 --> 01:34:14.049
I decided to win, no matter what.

01:34:14.650 --> 01:34:15.650
The second benefit is...

01:34:15.675 --> 01:34:17.319
The first one is big enough.

01:34:17.383 --> 01:34:20.593
that it will help you understand
the main mission in advance.

01:34:20.873 --> 01:34:22.134
This is...

01:34:22.159 --> 01:34:23.192
It's the operation map.

01:34:24.393 --> 01:34:26.666
The winner will get the right to decide
the opponent and the operation map too?

01:34:26.666 --> 01:34:27.666
The winning team gets everything it needs.

01:34:27.691 --> 01:34:29.532
- It's like letting them survive.
- Right.

01:34:29.762 --> 01:34:30.903
An operation map?

01:34:32.151 --> 01:34:34.069
Getting an operation map in advance...

01:34:34.173 --> 01:34:38.374
means we'll have enough time
to discuss and get ready.

01:34:38.564 --> 01:34:39.875
So, we must win at all costs.

01:34:41.340 --> 01:34:42.340
(Which unit will win the two benefits?)

01:34:42.365 --> 01:34:44.280
This means that the winning team
in the trench fighting...

01:34:44.280 --> 01:34:46.972
will pass the next mission...

01:34:46.972 --> 01:34:48.817
- Right.
- with a high probability.

01:34:49.862 --> 01:34:51.693
- It's...
- The benefits are too mighty.

01:34:51.718 --> 01:34:52.888
Definitely.

01:34:53.756 --> 01:34:55.491
The first round of the trench fighting.

01:34:55.768 --> 01:34:57.269
- It is...
- This is...

01:34:57.373 --> 01:34:59.328
- the 707th Group...
- The 707th Group!

01:34:59.472 --> 01:35:00.472
against the Marines.

01:35:00.629 --> 01:35:02.535
The first round is the 707th Group
versus the Marines?

01:35:02.535 --> 01:35:03.535
- What?
- Wait!

01:35:03.560 --> 01:35:05.768
- Su Yeon will fight already!
- Oh, my!

01:35:05.768 --> 01:35:06.768
They'll fight in the first round.

01:35:06.793 --> 01:35:08.470
The first round is like finals.

01:35:09.583 --> 01:35:11.674
The members of each team.

01:35:11.974 --> 01:35:13.909
Enter the trench.

01:35:14.927 --> 01:35:16.189
(The 707th Group:
Park Bo Ram and Lee Hyeon Seon)

01:35:16.189 --> 01:35:18.847
- Park Bo Ram and Lee Hyeon Seon.
- Bo Ram and Hyeon Seon.

01:35:18.847 --> 01:35:21.420
(How will the teamwork
of the two from the same class?)

01:35:21.928 --> 01:35:24.397
(Who from the Marines will fight?)

01:35:25.164 --> 01:35:26.222
Lee Su Yeon!

01:35:26.906 --> 01:35:28.724
- From the first round...
- I got goosebumps.

01:35:29.291 --> 01:35:30.826
The time has come at last.

01:35:31.453 --> 01:35:34.953
I wanted to avoid
First Lieutenant Su Yeon.

01:35:35.174 --> 01:35:37.800
She obviously has a big frame.

01:35:38.077 --> 01:35:39.435
I thought it wouldn't be easy.

01:35:40.136 --> 01:35:42.598
(Everyone is alert
to Su Yeon from the Marines.)

01:35:42.695 --> 01:35:44.340
It'll be quite a spectacle.

01:35:44.365 --> 01:35:45.808
I'm most interested in this battle.

01:35:47.009 --> 01:35:48.344
The participating members.

01:35:48.370 --> 01:35:50.179
State your rank and name.

01:35:51.280 --> 01:35:53.983
Sergeant First Class Park Bo Ram
of the ROK 707th Special Missions Group!

01:35:54.750 --> 01:35:58.120
We'll prove why the 707th Group is
called the strongest in the world!

01:35:58.687 --> 01:36:01.590
Sergeant First Class Lee Hyeon Seon
of the ROK 707th Special Missions Group!

01:36:02.884 --> 01:36:04.193
I'll fight with all my might,

01:36:04.193 --> 01:36:06.228
even at the risk of my life!

01:36:07.863 --> 01:36:10.332
Captain Cho A Ra of the Marines!

01:36:10.776 --> 01:36:12.271
I'll blow them away in an instant!

01:36:12.961 --> 01:36:13.873
- The voice...
- First Lieutenant Lee Su Yeon...

01:36:13.873 --> 01:36:15.437
of the Marines!

01:36:17.006 --> 01:36:18.651
I've already grown tired of waiting.

01:36:18.676 --> 01:36:19.844
I'll finish it quickly.

01:36:20.616 --> 01:36:22.268
(It's Su Yeon, indeed.)

01:36:22.268 --> 01:36:24.391
- "I'm tired of waiting."
- It's...

01:36:24.415 --> 01:36:26.485
- just like "Wild Bee."
- I'm tired of waiting, wild bee

01:36:26.745 --> 01:36:28.851
She's tired of waiting like a wild bee.

01:36:29.315 --> 01:36:32.588
(Their determination shows
how relaxed the strong are.)

01:36:32.998 --> 01:36:35.691
I wondered
how their hidden strength would be.

01:36:35.721 --> 01:36:37.726
I was looking forward to it.

01:36:38.271 --> 01:36:40.329
(First Lieutenant Park Bo Ram,
First Lieutenant Lee Hyeon Seon)

01:36:40.353 --> 01:36:42.353
(Captain Cho A Ra,
First Lieutenant Lee Su Yeon)

01:36:42.828 --> 01:36:44.050
(They're anticipating
to see Su Yeon's fight.)

01:36:44.050 --> 01:36:45.451
Su Yeon...

01:36:45.451 --> 01:36:48.020
But Bo Ram from the 707th Group is also...

01:36:48.020 --> 01:36:50.590
very high and quite well-built.

01:36:50.590 --> 01:36:52.929
- Right.
- So, I think...

01:36:52.954 --> 01:36:57.880
she can be a match for Su Yeon
if she has stamina and strategies.

01:36:57.905 --> 01:37:00.172
It's a 2-to-2 match,

01:37:00.197 --> 01:37:02.675
and Bo Ram and Hyeon Seon
have been friends and comrades...

01:37:02.675 --> 01:37:04.119
- Right.
- for a long time.

01:37:04.199 --> 01:37:05.992
So, they may have good teamwork.

01:37:05.992 --> 01:37:06.992
- Right.
- It's 2-to-2, after all.

01:37:07.022 --> 01:37:11.364
I wonder if Su Yeon will be
able to break the teamwork.

01:37:11.364 --> 01:37:12.858
- They're superior in terms of physique.
- Anyway,

01:37:12.858 --> 01:37:15.431
trench fighting requires
not only strength...

01:37:16.023 --> 01:37:19.268
but also teamwork and strategies.

01:37:19.898 --> 01:37:22.989
(War clouds gather on the trench.)

01:37:23.702 --> 01:37:25.040
She's taking her shirt off.

01:37:25.845 --> 01:37:29.178
I am here representing the 707th Group.

01:37:30.479 --> 01:37:31.780
So, I'll win, no matter what.

01:37:33.582 --> 01:37:35.050
Bo Ram also has a good body build.

01:37:35.617 --> 01:37:37.586
I'll show them
how invincible the 707th Group is.

01:37:39.021 --> 01:37:40.189
I'll win, no matter what.

01:37:41.690 --> 01:37:45.761
We'll show you
the Marines' capability and our strength.

01:37:48.063 --> 01:37:49.063
Full of determination.

01:37:50.556 --> 01:37:53.619
(Unrivaled body build)

01:37:54.155 --> 01:37:56.458
Other units? Beat us if you can.

01:37:57.611 --> 01:37:58.887
Look at the muscles.

01:37:59.174 --> 01:38:00.776
I decided to show them
how great the Marines are.

01:38:02.101 --> 01:38:04.880
She's already different
even when she takes her shirt off.

01:38:05.311 --> 01:38:07.850
- Su Yeon...
- Oh, my. It's not good.

01:38:10.185 --> 01:38:11.250
They're strong.

01:38:11.753 --> 01:38:12.753
The 2-on-2 trench fighting.

01:38:12.778 --> 01:38:14.990
- The 707th Group against the Marines.
- We'll begin now.

01:38:16.592 --> 01:38:18.227
Please show us how strong you are, Bo Ram.

01:38:18.252 --> 01:38:21.797
(Which unit will take the lead
in the first round?)

01:38:21.987 --> 01:38:22.987
Ready.

01:38:24.133 --> 01:38:25.334
It began!

01:38:26.412 --> 01:38:28.203
The 707th Group against the Marines.

01:38:29.171 --> 01:38:30.606
Su Yeon. It's a man-to-man fight!

01:38:31.417 --> 01:38:33.642
Nice.
They better eliminate one first.

01:38:34.660 --> 01:38:37.079
It's a 2-to-1 battle now!

01:38:38.684 --> 01:38:40.048
We have to come up with a strategy.

01:38:40.232 --> 01:38:41.784
It's either attacking only one person...

01:38:41.784 --> 01:38:44.853
or having a 1-to-1 fight individually.

01:38:45.086 --> 01:38:46.872
I think it'll take forever
if we fight individually.

01:38:46.872 --> 01:38:47.872
Right.

01:38:47.960 --> 01:38:50.559
There's a boar in the Marines unit.

01:38:51.110 --> 01:38:52.651
A boar in the Marines?

01:38:52.651 --> 01:38:54.053
If she says that...

01:38:54.053 --> 01:38:55.197
- Boar?
- She didn't mention the name,

01:38:55.221 --> 01:38:57.399
but we all know who she talked about.

01:38:57.565 --> 01:38:59.227
- Boar?
- It's a team battle...

01:38:59.778 --> 01:39:00.778
This is what I think.

01:39:01.073 --> 01:39:02.902
We should attack one of them together...

01:39:02.902 --> 01:39:06.407
and have her fall out of the battle.

01:39:08.481 --> 01:39:11.230
(Bo Ram and Hyeon Seon attack
Su Yeon together.)

01:39:11.230 --> 01:39:13.348
Bo Ram is fighting Su Yeon in the front,

01:39:13.348 --> 01:39:14.716
and Hyeon Seon is at the back.

01:39:14.716 --> 01:39:16.685
(Su Yeon is surrounded
by the 707th Group fighters.)

01:39:16.685 --> 01:39:17.763
Push her harder!

01:39:17.788 --> 01:39:18.851
Push them away!

01:39:19.425 --> 01:39:20.289
Together!

01:39:21.967 --> 01:39:22.835
Push them away!

01:39:22.835 --> 01:39:23.625
She doesn't budge.

01:39:24.292 --> 01:39:25.194
She's strong.

01:39:26.160 --> 01:39:27.696
Su Yeon...

01:39:27.897 --> 01:39:29.417
- Harder!
- won't budge an inch.

01:39:29.765 --> 01:39:32.201
- She's really firm.
- She's unwavering.

01:39:33.507 --> 01:39:34.670
She's withstanding it.

01:39:34.695 --> 01:39:36.371
- Let's go!
- Isn't she crazy?

01:39:36.371 --> 01:39:37.806
- One more!
- Push them back!

01:39:37.806 --> 01:39:39.775
(The 707th Group
tenaciously attacks Su Yeon.)

01:39:41.176 --> 01:39:42.377
Attack the legs!

01:39:42.377 --> 01:39:43.679
(The 707th Group manages
to bring Su Yeon down.)

01:39:43.679 --> 01:39:45.144
- She fell.
- They made her fall!

01:39:45.144 --> 01:39:46.415
Su Yeon fell.

01:39:46.415 --> 01:39:47.960
(The pincer movement
of the 707th Group is tough.)

01:39:47.960 --> 01:39:49.384
Wait. They're pressing her down!

01:39:49.501 --> 01:39:50.589
- Bo Ram!
- Press her down!

01:39:51.116 --> 01:39:52.955
A Ra should do something too!

01:39:53.325 --> 01:39:54.423
- That's it!
- Change the position.

01:39:54.423 --> 01:39:57.459
- She's pushing A Ra away!
- Lift her up!

01:39:57.459 --> 01:39:59.328
Bo Ram is pressing A Ra down.

01:40:00.170 --> 01:40:02.693
While Bo Ram is distracted,

01:40:03.884 --> 01:40:05.896
Su Yeon gets out!

01:40:06.080 --> 01:40:07.731
- She's out.
- It's 1-on-1 now!

01:40:07.731 --> 01:40:09.132
No, that's going to be so hard!

01:40:09.793 --> 01:40:11.315
(It's A Ra against Bo Ram
and Su Yeon against Hyeon Seon.)

01:40:11.340 --> 01:40:12.836
Hyeon Seon is going strong!

01:40:13.454 --> 01:40:15.038
Su Yeon against Hyeon Seon!

01:40:15.249 --> 01:40:16.840
She must be an athlete.
Did she train in ssireum before?

01:40:16.944 --> 01:40:18.809
Hyeon Seon, you have to stay strong!

01:40:19.042 --> 01:40:21.345
Grab her! Flip her over.

01:40:22.179 --> 01:40:23.917
Will Su Yeon show her monstrous strength?

01:40:23.917 --> 01:40:25.005
Su Yeon!

01:40:25.005 --> 01:40:26.023
(Right then)

01:40:27.093 --> 01:40:28.208
Su Yeon fell!

01:40:28.208 --> 01:40:29.603
Look at Hyeon Seon!

01:40:29.603 --> 01:40:32.155
The 707th Group's strength
is unbelievable!

01:40:33.800 --> 01:40:36.156
Hyeon Seon has technique!

01:40:36.516 --> 01:40:38.265
Right on!

01:40:38.265 --> 01:40:39.463
