01:45:02.425 --> 01:45:03.425
This is...

01:45:03.450 --> 01:45:04.828
(Which team is going to win?)

01:45:04.853 --> 01:45:07.734
(To be continued next week)

01:45:08.068 --> 01:45:10.344
(This is all for today.)

01:45:10.344 --> 01:45:11.498
No way!

01:45:11.523 --> 01:45:12.769
- Come on!
- Seriously?

01:45:12.769 --> 01:45:13.672
Why would you not show us the whole fight?

01:45:13.672 --> 01:45:15.769
What was that about?

01:45:15.769 --> 01:45:17.707
You need to pause the video...

01:45:17.860 --> 01:45:19.543
after the fight!

01:45:19.653 --> 01:45:20.948
What will happen to Su Yeon?

01:45:20.948 --> 01:45:23.446
Sure, we're curious,

01:45:23.446 --> 01:45:25.238
but Dong Hyun is going to die
of curiosity by next week!

01:45:25.238 --> 01:45:26.132
Seriously!

01:45:26.156 --> 01:45:27.560
The Marine Corps...

01:45:28.008 --> 01:45:29.943
I'm still unsure if I should bring
my red name tag or not!

01:45:30.120 --> 01:45:31.488
I need to know!

01:45:32.022 --> 01:45:33.760
Bo Ram is something else.

01:45:33.760 --> 01:45:35.425
- I know!
- She's so stubborn.

01:45:35.425 --> 01:45:37.517
You're right. We can't predict
the winner anymore.

01:45:37.700 --> 01:45:39.963
How will this battle end?

01:45:40.066 --> 01:45:42.732
The result of the 707th Group
against the Marine Corps...

01:45:42.856 --> 01:45:46.036
will be revealed next week.

01:45:46.333 --> 01:45:47.571
Everyone, stand tall!

01:45:47.674 --> 01:45:49.706
Salute to the viewers.

01:45:49.706 --> 01:45:51.041
- Iron!
- Iron!

01:45:54.254 --> 01:45:56.380
(A 2-on-2 trench fight:
The 707th Group vs. the Marine Corps)

01:45:56.880 --> 01:45:58.666
(The 707th Group's unbelievable power
and breathtaking charisma)

01:45:59.015 --> 01:46:00.985
(The 707th Group is taking over the game
against the Marine Corps right away.)

01:46:01.185 --> 01:46:02.753
If I don't fight for life,

01:46:02.753 --> 01:46:03.287
I'm going to lose.

01:46:03.366 --> 01:46:04.136
Stay strong!

01:46:04.276 --> 01:46:05.679
(Which unit will win,
the 707th Group or the Marine Corps?)

01:46:05.779 --> 01:46:07.710
The next battle is
between the Special Mission Battalion...

01:46:07.734 --> 01:46:08.809
and the ROK Army.

01:46:09.025 --> 01:46:10.427
She's so fit.

01:46:10.927 --> 01:46:12.472
I'm looking forward
to watching Seong Won fight.

01:46:12.497 --> 01:46:14.822
I need to show
why we're the Special Mission Battalion.

01:46:14.847 --> 01:46:17.344
Today's the day everyone will stop
undermining non-special mission units.

01:46:17.369 --> 01:46:19.369
I'll drown you in the trench
and tear you apart.

01:46:19.394 --> 01:46:21.288
(The pride of the two units is
on the line.)

01:46:21.488 --> 01:46:22.488
(So ferocious)

01:46:22.569 --> 01:46:24.274
(Things have gotten...)

01:46:24.274 --> 01:46:25.539
(more intense and ferocious.)

01:46:25.639 --> 01:46:27.468
(Who will become the final winner
of the trench fights?)

01:46:28.248 --> 01:46:29.380
(The start of an intense mission...)

01:46:29.580 --> 01:46:31.448
(to determine the first unit
to be eliminated)

01:46:32.499 --> 01:46:33.817
This is the mission.

01:46:33.917 --> 01:46:35.786
This is ours.

01:46:36.086 --> 01:46:37.821
We're going to make it
to the next round easy.

01:46:37.921 --> 01:46:39.580
(Running for their lives)

01:46:39.780 --> 01:46:41.815
(The missions have become harder.)

01:46:42.860 --> 01:46:45.118
(An intense battle
to fight for the units' reputation)

01:46:45.188 --> 01:46:47.541
I was thrown off by how endless it seemed.

01:46:47.841 --> 01:46:50.400
(Only the strongest ones can survive
through this extreme mission.)

01:46:50.400 --> 01:46:51.745
Get in!

01:46:51.845 --> 01:46:53.704
(Get through the endless obstacles.)

01:46:54.738 --> 01:46:55.436
Come on!

01:46:55.542 --> 01:46:56.570
(Monstrous strength)

01:46:56.871 --> 01:46:58.008
In 1, 2, 3!

01:46:58.100 --> 01:46:59.773
(March for your lives.)

01:46:59.973 --> 01:47:00.973
Get yourself together!

01:47:00.973 --> 01:47:02.416
Get closer! Come on!

01:47:04.321 --> 01:47:07.154
(Desperate struggles for survival)

01:47:08.407 --> 01:47:10.155
(It's not over...)

01:47:10.155 --> 01:47:11.833
(until it is.)

01:47:11.887 --> 01:47:13.541
(An unexpected result)

01:47:15.001 --> 01:47:16.341
(Which unit will be eliminated first?)

